INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('653','JavaScript Developer  AngularJS at Webtrekk GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>In this position, you will strengthen one of our agile development teams and create user friendly single-page B2B web applications and highly performant JavaScript plugins to be used on our customer&rsquo;s websites.</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Get involved in all phases of the product lifecycle: requirements analysis, design process, implementation and testing.</li><br /><li>You will develop new and optimise existing modules/libraries always with an eye on usability, responsiveness and maintenance.</li><br /><li>Create proof of concepts and MVP&rsquo;s</li><br /></ul>','Webtrekk GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('654','Frontend Developer at keylight GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>What we are looking for</strong></p><br /><p>We are looking for motivated candidates with unique talents who want to achieve great things with us! You should have a genuine interest in new technologies and a willingness to learn.</p><br /><p>Specifically,&nbsp;you are a perfect fit if:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>You completed a degree in either design or computer science / mathematics / physics or equivalent and already have implemented smaller projects on your own</li><br /><li>You dare to discover and apply new exciting technologies,</li><br /><li>You are very experienced with&nbsp;HTML/CSS</li><br /><li>You have a good feeling for&nbsp;the small yet&nbsp;important parts of webdesign such as font sizes, margins, or colors</li><br /><li>You master the basics of standard web technologies such as jQuery or AngularJS</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What you can expect from us:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You will be part of an amazing team in a true start-up environment at the heart of Berlin</li><br /><li>With many exciting projects with different challenges and new technologies,</li><br /><li>A competitive salary</li><br /><li>Interesting colleagues</li><br /><li>Flexible working hours</li><br /><li>An unlimited amount of free beer</li><br /></ul><br /><p>We look forward to receiving your application!</p>','keylight GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('655','Senior Frontend Engineer - JavaScript (React) (m/f) at uberall GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>DESCRIPTION</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>As Senior Frontend Engineer / Senior Frontend Developer you will be working on our Digital Marketing Software (SaaS) and be a part of a highly skilled agile team. As a collaborative team member you will have a voice in our daily stand ups that will be listened and helps us to provide the best solution for our partners and clients.</li><br /></ul><br /><br /><p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Participate in full life-cycle software development of our innovative and unique cloud solution for Digital Marketing</li><br /><li>Work closely with Product and Design to develop and implement new features and products &amp; engage in feature discussions, product planning, collaboration with others, etc.</li><br /><li>Maintain our website, our number one promotional tool. We need it to be clear, look great, load fast, and most importantly, effectively explain what we do</li><br /><li>Build extensible widgets, pushing for the simplest integration of our latest functionality</li><br /><li>Develop our web-apps that our customers use every day to manage anywhere from 50 to 10s of thousands of business listings</li><br /><li>Build a reference connection to our extensive Rest API that both our partners and our own client apps us</li><br /></ul>','uberall GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('656','Data Warehouse Engineer at Europe''s leading online fashion platform at Zalando SE (Berlin, Germany)','<p><br><strong>The opportunity</strong><br><br>As a Zalando Data Warehouse Engineer you will become a critical part of one of the most innovative teams in ecommerce. You will consult and support different stakeholders across the entire company by providing data-driven solutions to business and technical challenges. You''ll join our accomplished team of experts in integrating data from many sources into our single-point-of-truth data warehouse. And you will have the freedom to launch your own open source projects, contribute to others'' projects, build internal community around your interests, and strengthen your personal brand-while receiving meaningful support at every step.<br><br><strong>What we''re looking for</strong><br><br></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have demonstrated your programming skills in Python, Java, or PL/SQL for at least 2 years</li><br /><li>Experience maintaining, refactoring and extending large code bases</li><br /><li>A preference for agile methodologies</li><br /><li>A passion for working with relational databases: reading, writing and optimizing complex statements; modelling data structures, and designing ETL processes</li><br /><li>The ability to communicate effectively with diverse teams</li><br /><li>Fluent in English</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>Your responsibilities</strong><br><br></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Develop expertise in understanding our business processes and the many related requirements</li><br /><li>Collaborate with our analysts to create and implement new initiatives based on our stakeholder requirements</li><br /><li>Act as a liaison between your team and other teams within Zalando Tech</li><br /><li>Maintain, optimize and extend our data warehouse infrastructure using Oracle, Exasol and PostgreSQL databases</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>What you can expect from us</strong><br><br></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Internal tech talks, skills-building courses and technical "People Leads" who help you achieve mastery</li><br /><li>Personal branding support: From preparing conference talks and blog posts to industry networking Community: hack weeks, movie nights, +70 self-organized tech guilds and more</li><br /><li>Competitive salary</li><br /><li>40% Zalando shopping discount and commuter discount</li><br /><li>Relocation assistance for internationals</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>About Zalando</strong><br><br><br>Zalando is Europe''s leading online fashion platform, doing business in 15 markets. Delivering first-class shopping experiences to our +15 million customers requires moving fast - with microservices, Agile processes &amp; autonomous teams - and using cutting edge, open source technologies. We are passionate about what we do and have fun while doing it. And we are willing to experiment and make mistakes: It''s how we grow.<br><br>Want to join us? Then go ahead and apply!<br><br>If you need guidance or have any questions about our hiring processes, please contact recruiter Antonia Samanns.</p>','Zalando SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('657','Junior Javascript Engineer (Berlin) at mycs GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Help us revolutionize E-commerce by building real-time 3D customization tools with a world class team of creative, smart and passionate people in the heart of Berlin!</p><br /><p>mycs is changing the way we buy things online. Our vision is to revolutionize E-commerce. All our products are sold using photorealistic, real-time 3D customization tools. In the past, we have built Massivkonzept, the leading online shop for customized furniture. mycs builds on this experience and is currently building a team in Berlin, focusing on building cutting edge technology and improving the E-commerce customer experience.</p><br /><p>We are looking for a enthusiastic</p><br /><p><strong>Junior JavaScript Developers (React/Node.js) (m/f)</strong></p><br /><p>As one of our Junior JavaScript Developer (m/f) you will play an important role in our development team and help us create a fabulous E-commerce platform with cutting edge 3D customization tools.</p><br /><p><strong>YOUR TASKS</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You design and implement efficient and reusable software and web-applications for our Ecommerce platform with its demanding real-time 3D customization tools</li><br /><li>You work closely with our international, highly skilled and professional development team in an agile development environment</li><br /><li>You identify and address performance issues</li><br /><li>You train yourself continuously to ensure that your skills are up to date</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>OUR OFFER</strong></p><br /><p>Join a creative, smart, self-motivated, and experienced group of people at a successful company where your input will make a real difference. We offer a competitive compensation package, flexible working times, and great opportunity for advancement and long-term career building. We invest in the personal development of our people and provide high-end equipment for their work.</p><br /><p>We work in short cycles in order to adapt our software continuously to our business needs. We like to use the newest available technologies and mainly use open source solutions when it comes to development. We work in small, agile teams using methodologies such as SCRUM, Kanban, pair programming, TDD/BDD and continuous integration/deployment. Your ideas are always welcome, even if they mean that we have to change a lot of code to make things better. Besides a dynamic, highly motivated international team, you will find minimal hierarchies, quick decision-making and a pleasant working atmosphere.</p><br /><p>For more details: <a title="Jobs @ mycs" href="https://de.mycs.com/career" rel="nofollow">https://de.mycs.com/career</a></p>','mycs GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('658','Backend Developer (m/f) at Rocket Internet SE (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>CATERWINGS&nbsp;is a food start-up which connects the most exciting street food, popup caterers and restaurants to businesses for office lunches, team meetings, parties and events. We want to bring excitement for the food served in offices!</p>','Rocket Internet SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('659','Engineering Manager, DACH Region at GoEuro Travel GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><em><span>We are searching for a passionate Engineering Manager with hands-on </span></em><em><span>Java development skills who loves to work with smart people and wants to develop a fantastic team</span></em><em><span> to join our Coverage Team for the DACH Region.</span></em></p><br /><p><strong>About GoEuro</strong></p><br /><p><span>Driven by our team of over 200 people from more than 40 different countries, GoEuro is changing the way we travel across Europe. With GoEuro you can compare and book trains, buses and flights to anywhere in Europe with one simple search, on mobile, app or desktop. By offering transparent pricing and easy booking, GoEuro makes travel planning simple, flexible and personal.</span></p><br /><p><span>With over 500 European transportation partners across 12 countries, GoEuro is one of Europe&rsquo;s fastest growing travel companies backed by 10 million monthly users and the world&rsquo;s leading tech investors.</span></p><br /><p><strong>As a Software Engineering Manager at GoEuro you will&hellip;</strong><strong><br></strong></p><br /><p><span>&hellip; be responsible together with the Product Owner and the Country Manager for providing the best possible transportation options for the DACH region to our consumers. You will assure to have a happy and high performing team and jump-in with hands-on development support every now and then. You will be directly managing talented engineers, develop and mentor them in technical and non-technical aspects, work closely with our travel providers and the other Tribes in GoEuro.</span></p><br /><p><strong>The following tasks are waiting for you:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li><span>Work closely with providers: integrate new ones and maintain the existing partners</span></li><br /><li><span>Improve our provider platform to simplify and streamline our complex tasks and make our system that integrates hundreds of APIs even more resilient</span></li><br /><li><span>Manage a talented team of software developers, grow and develop it</span></li><br /><li><span>Lead projects across multiple teams: product, business development, design, desktop and mobile web, native apps, APIs</span></li><br /><li><span>Establish best practices for cross-team collaboration and software development processes</span></li><br /><li><span>Debug and solve difficult technical problems and troubleshoot performance issues</span></li><br /><li><span>Lead by example in software quality</span></li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What can you expect from joining GoEuro?</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li><span>Play an integral role in a fast-moving company taking on an enormous challenge</span></li><br /><li><span>An office in the centre of Berlin&rsquo;s thriving startup scene</span></li><br /><li><span>Flat hierarchies and everyday opportunities to learn, grow and develop</span></li><br /><li><span>A diverse team of over 40 nationalities</span></li><br /><li><span>Free lunches, yoga, German and English lessons and more</span></li><br /><li><span>Competitive compensation and relocation support</span></li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Are you the great Engineering Manager we are looking for?</strong></p><br /><p><em><span>We''re excited to receive your application!</span></em></p>','GoEuro Travel GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('660','Senior PHP Developer at AUTO1 (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>What you will do:<br></strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Develop state of the art, innovative applications/services in PHP on an enterprise level</li><br /><li>Design software architecture and implement critical software tools, e.g. for our internal logistics platform or our purchasing app</li><br /><li>Constantly improve yourself by learning new technologies and concepts following best industry practices</li><br /><li>Take technical responsibility for projects within an international environment</li><br /><li>Work in agile environment consistently focusing on improvements</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What you will learn:<br></strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>How to build technical solutions and confront them with production traffic</li><br /><li>How to work in a high scalable environment and with complex code</li><br /><li>Deliver features end-to-end, from product decisions until deployment to live production</li><br /></ul>','AUTO1');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('661','Full-Stack Web Apps Developer, Software Engineer (m/f) at Software & Support Media GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Putting ideas into practice.<br>Loving challenges.</p><br /><p>For our Berlin-based development team, we are now looking for a</p><br /><p><strong>Full-Stack Web Apps Developer, Software Engineer (m/f).</strong></p><br /><br /><p><strong>Your mission</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Design and implement the back-end for new and existing customer-facing products. Day to day you will be using the MEAN stack, Python and other technologies.</li><br /><li>50% of your time will be on company back-end systems and B2B services (mostly MEAN stack), developing new micro services to fit in with existing legacy systems.</li><br /><li>Improve the DevOps environment for our existing back-end applications and help improve our development workflow.</li><br /><li>You will create scalable and secure twelve-factor apps that are fully under test and easy to deploy as microservices.</li><br /></ul>','Software & Support Media GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('662','Javascript Developer for NetSuite (m/f) at mycs GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Help us revolutionize E-commerce by building real-time 3D customization tools with a world class team of creative, smart and passionate people in the heart of Berlin!</p><br /><p>mycs is changing the way we buy things online. Our vision is to revolutionize E-commerce. All our products are sold using photorealistic, real-time 3D customization tools. In the past, we have built Massivkonzept, the leading online shop for customized furniture. mycs builds on this experience and is currently building a team in Berlin, focusing on building cutting edge technology and improving the E-commerce customer experience.</p><br /><p>We are looking for a enthusiastic</p><br /><p><strong>Junior JavaScript Developers (React/Node.js) (m/f)</strong></p><br /><p>As one of our Junior JavaScript Developer (m/f) you will play an important role in our development team and help us create a fabulous E-commerce platform with cutting edge 3D customization tools.</p><br /><p><strong>YOUR TASKS</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Develop and maintain our ES6 codebase to improve and add functionality using Suite Script 1.0 and 2.0</li><br /><li>Implement and change business processes in NetSuite using the UI</li><br /><li>Develop integrations with other systems using RESTLets and webservices</li><br /><li>Manage existing SuiteBundles and identify new bundles or third-party applications to improve upon existing processes</li><br /><li>Integrate into the existing team and take responsibility for your projects</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>OUR OFFER</strong></p><br /><p>Join a creative, smart, self-motivated, and experienced group of people at a successful company where your input will make a real difference. We offer a competitive compensation package, flexible working times, and great opportunity for advancement and long-term career building. We invest in the personal development of our people and provide high-end equipment for their work.</p><br /><p>We work in short cycles in order to adapt our software continuously to our business needs. We like to use the newest available technologies and mainly use open source solutions when it comes to development. We work in small, agile teams using methodologies such as SCRUM, Kanban, pair programming, TDD/BDD and continuous integration/deployment. Your ideas are always welcome, even if they mean that we have to change a lot of code to make things better. Besides a dynamic, highly motivated international team, you will find minimal hierarchies, quick decision-making and a pleasant working atmosphere.</p><br /><p>For more details: <a title="Jobs @ mycs" href="https://de.mycs.com/career" rel="nofollow">https://de.mycs.com/career</a></p>','mycs GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('663','Senior PHP Developer - Anti Fraud Detection (m/f) at Digital Performance GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<ul><br /><li>Build and lead a development team in an agile fashion by utilising servant leadership</li><br /><li>Get your hands on the code and actively drive the system architecture</li><br /><li>Play a key part in how our fraud detection/prevention related applications are developed</li><br /><li>Translate use cases into stories or even epics</li><br /><li>Implement metrics for all services to monitor your teams&rsquo; success</li><br /><li>Implement code reviews and be responsible for your teams&rsquo; code quality</li><br /><li>Work together with our System Administration team to deliver highly available services in our own data center</li><br /><li>Analysing complex problems and constantly improving our technologies</li><br /><li>Coordinate the needs and requirements from stakeholders</li><br /><li>Work closely together with the management team</li><br /></ul>','Digital Performance GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('664','Software Engineer - Backend (Ruby) at Babbel (Berlin, Germany)','<p><span>Hallo! Bonjour! Hi!</span></p><br /><p>We believe that everybody should have the chance to learn a foreign language. Languages are about much more than simple everyday communication, they are a unique window into a rich world of diverse and colourful cultures. Babbel exists to offer everybody the chance to learn languages.</p><br /><p>Babbel offers 14 learning languages - from English to Indonesian - and, since founding in 2007, we have grown to become the market leader in app-based language learning. There are 450 of us from over 41 different countries working hard to keep this going - we call ourselves &lsquo;Babbelonians&rsquo;.</p><br /><p>We want to achieve and create even more. That&rsquo;s where you come in.</p><br /><p>As our Backend focused Software Engineer, you will be self-motivated, full of ideas as well as energy and drive the engineering of Babbel&rsquo;s new products and services.</p><br /><p><span>So, from one kind of language to another, we are looking to talk with passionate and dedicated </span><strong>Software Engineers</strong><span> who speak our languages&hellip;.</span><strong>Ruby/Rails and JavaScript</strong><span>. Of course, we understand that with any language comes dialect, and we particularly enjoy listening to </span><strong>React.JS and Redux.JS</strong><span> dialects. Polyglots who also speak</span><strong> HTML/CSS</strong><span> are also welcome to join our party too. Experience in J</span><strong>S and Ruby testing frameworks</strong><span> using </span><strong>BDD/TDD</strong><span> as well as solid knowledge in </span><strong>REST-based API</strong><span>. Bonus points are on offer for those with </span><strong>AWS</strong><span> services experience, knowledge of other server side frameworks like</span><strong> Sinatra or Node.js</strong><span> or </span><strong>DevOps</strong><span> experience.</span></p><br /><p>More broadly, we are looking for smart, passionate engineers who can share in our goal of widening access to language learning. You care about maintaining a clean code base and strive for technical excellence in the build of our product. Above all else, you are always personally learning and developing, and you have the maturity and skill base to make timely and sustainable individual contributions. And finally, excellent verbal and written English skills are must.</p><br /><p>If this sounds interesting, why not learn more about the exciting culture that we are building in our Engineering teams. &nbsp;</p><br /><p><span>To see first hand what life is like as a Babbelonian check out our twitter pages </span><a href="https://twitter.com/BabbelBytes" rel="nofollow"><span>@BabbelBytes</span></a><span> and </span><a href="https://twitter.com/BabbelJobs" rel="nofollow"><span>@BabbelJobs</span></a></p><br /><p>Apply now and a Babbelonian will be in touch soon.</p>','Babbel');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('665','PHP Web Developer at digidip (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Do you love web development? Do you enjoy solving complex problems? Do you want to work long-term in Berlin with awesome people from all over the world in a growing environment and on a kick-ass product? Do you also have a great sense of humor? If your answer to these questions is yes, then join our team and experience a wide range of new and exciting challenges!</p><br /><p>digidip is a fast-growing international tech company and already the european leader in monetizing high quality websites within a private network environment. Our technology helps websites to make the most of their content and monetize it in the simplest way.</p>','digidip');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('666','Web Designer at Perdoo GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>What we do</strong></p><br /><p>Work is changing for the better and we want to be at the forefront of that movement: Improving working life for employees across all disciplines in all types of organizations. We want to make everyone count and care about how teams can get the best out of themselves.</p><br /><p>Perdoo is an Enterprise Goal Management system trusted by thousands of employees and hundreds of organizations worldwide. We''ve built our software around OKRs (Objectives &amp; Key Results), a management framework that allows companies to engage, challenge and align their workforce by managing and aligning their goals.</p><br /><p><strong>Job description</strong></p><br /><p>As a Web Developer&nbsp;(m/f) at Perdoo, you&rsquo;ll be responsible for all client-side activities of our product. You&rsquo;ll be working very closely with our CTO to build a fast, stable and reliable client. We allocate a lot of time to staying up to date with the latest technologies and frameworks and expect you to thrive on that.</p><br /><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong>:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Create&nbsp;user interfaces for our enterprise grade web client&nbsp;using standard HTML/CSS practices</li><br /><li>Create and maintain a style guide to enforce a consistent look and quality</li><br /><li>Set up and manage a reusable component library</li><br /><li>Support our UX designers in creating product defining user interactions</li><br /><li>Stay on top of industry trends and help evangelize our brand among the tech world</li><br /></ul>','Perdoo GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('667','Software Developer  Devops (m/f) at Smartfrog Services GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>We&rsquo;re looking for talented and motivated people to join our team!</p><br /><p><strong>What we offer</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>A dynamic office environment at an international tech startup in the heart of Berlin</li><br /><li>The chance to help build an exciting new brand and develop new products</li><br /><li>A young and agile business with flat hierarchies</li><br /><li>Great potential to develop your career</li><br /><li>Flexible hours and working arrangements</li><br /><li>Attractive compensation package</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Location: Berlin<br>Start: ASAP; fulltime</p><br /><p><strong>Your role</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Work closely with the Operations team to provide adequate tooling (provisioning, deployment, monitoring).</li><br /><li>Work closely with Developers to provide support tool regarding deployment and build of their software (Maven, NPM).</li><br /><li>Work closely with QA team to support CI/CD tooling.</li><br /><li>Develop dashboard and reporting tools for better visualisation of the health of our development processes and platform.</li><br /><li>Participate in Operation duty and work closely with the maintenance of our cloud platform.</li><br /></ul>','Smartfrog Services GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('668','Senior Fullstack Developer (m/f) Java Script - Berlin at intive-Kupferwerk GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Your Profile</strong></p><br /><br /><br /><p>Full stack developers will have a range of responsibilities from shaping and implementing digital products to ensuring that we stay on the leading edge of technology.&nbsp;Our engineers contribute across the full technology stack, from database and DevOps infrastructure that supports continuous deployment, over native apps, to front end development. As a Senior Software Engineer you will work in a cross-functional team with the Product Owner, Designers and Senior Engineers to co-develop the digital products.</p><br /><br /><p><strong>Responsibility</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Use agile engineering practices and modern development technologies to rapidly develop creative and efficient solutions that delivers against the product as outlined by the Product Owner</li><br /><li>Collaborate with other agile team members to steer technology choices towards a leading edge setup that delivers against the longer term needs and vision from the Product Owner</li><br /><li>Identify, suggest and conduct technology enabled product experiments in collaboration with the Product Owner</li><br /><li>Provide technology expertise in discussions with stakeholders</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What we offer</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>A job position with a bright future in a fast growing company and innovative industry</li><br /><li>Exciting products for national and international leading customers as well</li><br /><li>Demanding projects regarding usability, design and technology</li><br /><li>A role with responsibilities and creative freedom at same time</li><br /><li>Being part and working in a competent and motivated team</li><br /><li>Individual training and education to improve your skills</li><br /><li>Harmonic work/life balance</li><br /><li>Competitive salary</li><br /></ul><br /><br /><hr><br /><br /><p><strong>Facts</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Start time: ASAP</li><br /><li>permanent employment</li><br /><li>40 hours / week</li><br /><li>&bdquo;Your Office&ldquo;: Berlin&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Regular travel activities: to our developer centers in Germany and Poland</li><br /><li>Further information available for you in our Jobs FAQ site <a href="http://www.intive-kupferwerk.com/" rel="nofollow">www.intive-kupferwerk.com</a></li><br /></ul>','intive-Kupferwerk GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('669','Frontend Developer (m/f) at HeavenHR (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Our mission at HeavenHR is to provide the only software businesses need to manage their Human Resources. Our goal is to help companies save time and focus on what they are really good at. From onboarding to payroll, we connect all separate HR processes into a single and easy-to-use platform.</p><br /><p>HeavenHR is a young SaaS start-up backed by well-known VC funds and experienced business angels. To continue our rapid growth, we are looking for Frontend Developers who enjoy working in a dynamic environment and want to join us in building a great software from scratch.</p><br /><p>Our top values:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Be active and productive</li><br /><li>Respect</li><br /><li>Fun</li><br /><li>Keep calm and amaze</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Your responsibilities:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Establish an easy-to-use platform with great user experience</li><br /><li>Ensure accessibility, usability and performance for desktop website</li><br /><li>Optimize website responsiveness for mobile and tablet</li><br /><li>Build an excellent product on a technical and qualitative level</li><br /><li>Initiate the development of new processes and solutions, realizing own ideas and shaping your own way of working</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Your background:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>2+ years of experience in building web applications</li><br /><li>Experience with Web Standards (HTML5, CSS3), Semantic HTML, CSS pre-processor</li><br /><li>Good knowledge of JavaScript and ReactJS</li><br /><li>Experience with testing frameworks</li><br /><li>Knowledge of GIT</li><br /><li>Working experience in Continuous Integration/Deployment is a plus</li><br /><li>BS degree in Computer Science or related technical field or equivalent practical experience</li><br /><li>Proactive, goal-oriented, energetic with an independent way of working</li><br /><li>Fluent in English</li><br /><li>Willingness to relocate to Berlin (if applicable)</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Why you should join the team:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Open mindset for new technologies and processes</li><br /><li>Opportunity to work in an agile environment with lean processes (fast and small iterations)</li><br /><li>Being part of an international team of smart and enthusiastic developers</li><br /><li>Office in the hip neighborhood of Kreuzberg</li><br /><li>New, stylish and fast equipment</li><br /><li>Free drinks, great coffee and fruit baskets</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Up for a challenge?</p><br /><p>We are looking forward to receiving your application!</p>','HeavenHR');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('670','Senior Software Engineer at a fast growing ecommerce startup at Oberlo (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>We&rsquo;re looking for a dedicated, methodical, and versatile backend engineer with experience and passion for solving tough problems with scalable height performance code. We need someone who can quickly adapt to shifting approaches, situations, and priorities. You will need to be able to work in a team with fellow engineers to create a highly scalable, distributed web application that serves millions of requests a day.</p><br /><p>We are building a new tech-hub in Berlin beside our headquarter in Vilnius.</p>','Oberlo');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('671','Tech Lead with Spanish language knowledge (m/f) at Rocket Internet SE (Berlin, Germany)','<p>A leading Telco player is creating a new digital unit that will have the independence to build and shape the company&rsquo;s e-commerce experience as well as e-care/m-care applications. The unit will work under full agile methodology in a young, fast-paced environment with the objective to deliver a state-of-the-art digital experience, and will operate under direct CEO sponsorship to facilitate the delivery of its mission.</p>','Rocket Internet SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('672','Frontend Developer at Minodes (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>From a technology perspective, we have thousands of sensors with our own firmware installed in our customers&rsquo; retail stores around the world. We process terabytes of data via machine learning algorithms and provide a self-service &nbsp;platform for our analytics solutions. We offer a great opportunity for personal and professional growth in a multicultural environment. We work, learn and develop while having lots of fun on the way.<br><br>Join our team as a&nbsp;<strong>Frontend Developer</strong>.<br><br><strong>What we do all day:</strong><br>We create a beautiful self-service platform for our analytics solutions using modern tools and libaries such as React, Redux, Webpack, Babel and write JavaScript in ES6. We work in cross-functional teams in order to create a premium experience for our customers. We believe that being a good developer is not so much a question of skills, but more a question of mindset. If you are passionate like us, you love to learn, work and share knowledge with your team, you will be a good fit.</p>','Minodes');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('673','Mobile Developer Android, Team Platform Innovation (m/f) at HRS Innovation Hub (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>We are looking for a Berlin based&nbsp;<strong>Mobile Developer Android, Team Platform Innovation (m/f)&nbsp;</strong>who is keen on delivering world-class mobile applications dedicated for the travel and hospitality business.</p><br /><p>At&nbsp;<strong>HRS GROUP</strong>&nbsp;&ldquo;We love to make it happen&rdquo;: We are the world&rsquo;s leading hotel solutions provider and enable business and leisure travelers to search, book and stay in control of their hotel accommodation. It is our goal to make the booking experience simple and smart. Our booking portals combine more than 850,000 accommodations worldwide and form the basis for our innovative end-to-end solutions we are offering to global corporations. The HRS GROUP continues to expand and employs more than 1,500 people in 27 offices across the world &ndash; including Cologne, Shanghai, London, Mumbai and Sydney.</p><br /><p>The <strong>HRS Innovation Hub</strong> delivers integrated solutions to the three business areas of the HRS Group: End Consumer Products, Global Hotel Solutions and Hotel Solutions. Our international team is cross-functional and comprised of experts in the fields of Agile Product Management, Data Science, Software Engineering, UX Design and Systems Engineering. The multi-tenancy microservices architecture of the underlying technical platform is powered by hundreds of microservices - partially containerized or server-less - in the Amazon Web Services cloud. Among the various AWS technologies, those services make use state of the art technologies such as Apache Spark, ElasticSearch, Java 8, NodeJS, ReactJS, Redis and Scala.</p><br /><p><strong>The challenge you are up for</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Write high-quality code, conduct and participate in code reviews, and follow strong engineering principles and standards</li><br /><li>Cooperate closely with QA Engineers, Product Managers, and Frontend and Backend Engineers</li><br /><li>Research the technical feasibility of new ideas and actively suggest technology improvements</li><br /><li>Improve performance of the App, both technology-wise and business-wise</li><br /><li>Contribute to our quality processes by writing automated unit and integration tests for use in continuous integration</li><br /></ul>','HRS Innovation Hub');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('674','Senior JavaScript Engineer - (HTML/CSS, React, Angular/Angular 2 or Ember) at Zalando SE (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>You Are Ready To Make An Impact</strong></p><br /><p>Zalando is transforming from Europe&rsquo;s leading e-commerce company into a <a href="https://annual-report.zalando.com/2015/#en/platform" rel="nofollow">multi-service platform for fashion</a>. From Fashion Store to Brand Solutions to Business Assurance and Smart Logistics, you will be building the technologies that are utilized as a base for further products and aim to connect all people and parts of the fashion ecosystem.</p><br /><p>We live <a href="https://tech.zalando.de/blog/radical-agility-study-notes/" rel="nofollow">Radical Agility</a> - a software development methodology that allows engineers to get work done while management keeps their distance. Along with our guiding set of principles - Autonomy, Mastery, Purpose - we entrust you and your team to shape the future of Zalando.</p><br /><p>Your individual impact at Zalando is limitless. It is not only about growth and improvement, it is about inventing new things. We strongly believe that providing useful code to the world is a virtue.Along with you, we strive to learn from and contribute to <a href="http://zalando.github.io/#welcome" rel="nofollow">open source</a> software for the betterment of Zalando and the tech community.</p><br /><p><strong>You Are Setting Standards</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Variety.</strong> As part of your onboarding, you will get to know some and join one of our teams that matches your interests and skills. As a team, you will build, scale and continuously improve a variety of web applications that redefine the user experience of our customers and partners.</p><br /><p><strong>Autonomy.</strong> Based on our microservices architecture, you and your team will own your code. You will decide together on the technologies and tools to utilize as well operate large-scale web applications on PaaS/SaaS cloud (AWS).</p><br /><p><strong>Purpose.</strong> You and your team will work truly cross-functional with an entrepreneurial mindset and drive the whole development cycle according to its purpose - from implementation to testing and maintenance.</p><br /><p><strong>Mastery</strong>. You will join a team that is dedicated to delivering the highest standards when it comes to the scalability, performance and user-centricity of our software. You will add value through innovation by leveraging current trends in software design, frameworks and RESTful web services.</p>','Zalando SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('675','Senior Software Engineer, Payment System at GoEuro Travel GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><em>We are searching for an excellent software engineer with a passion for software-craftsmanship and <strong>experience in payment systems</strong>. The ideal candidate should enjoy building scalable solutions within a strong, cross-functional, agile development team.</em></p><br /><p><strong>About GoEuro</strong></p><br /><p>Driven by our team of over 200 people from more than 40 different countries, GoEuro is changing the way we travel across Europe. With GoEuro you can compare and book trains, buses and flights to anywhere in Europe with one simple search, on mobile, app or desktop. By offering transparent pricing and easy booking, GoEuro makes travel planning simple, flexible and personal.</p><br /><p>With over 500 European transportation partners across 12 countries, GoEuro is one of Europe&rsquo;s fastest growing travel companies backed by 10 million monthly users and the world&rsquo;s leading tech investors.</p><br /><p><strong>As a Senior Software Engineer at GoEuro you will:</strong></p><br /><p>Be part of an international, talented and agile team that is building the payment system for our users. We are currently accepting all major credit cards as well as PayPal but we are looking for ways to expand and offer more options for our users in the future.</p><br /><p>Even though we are very proud of what we have achieved at GoEuro already, there is still a lot of room for improvement and many interesting technical challenges to overcome before going forward. That''s why we are searching for you!</p><br /><p><strong>The following tasks are waiting for you:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Play a leading role in the architecture and building of our core payment system.</li><br /><li>Work with a massive amount of payments with multiple partners.</li><br /><li>Design and develop a scalable and secure payment system.</li><br /><li>Implement scalable and accurate accounting data - backend.</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Our offer</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>An office in the centre of Berlin&rsquo;s thriving startup scene</li><br /><li>Flat hierarchies and everyday opportunities to learn, grow and develop</li><br /><li>A diverse team of over 40 nationalities</li><br /><li>Free lunches, yoga, German lessons and more</li><br /><li>Competitive compensation and relocation support</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Are you the great Software Engineer we are looking for?</strong></p><br /><p>We''re excited to receive your application!</p>','GoEuro Travel GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('676','DevOps Engineer (m/w) at SysEleven GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Wie herrscht man &uuml;ber mehr als 4000 Server? Wie sorgt man daf&uuml;r, dass alle Systeme rekonstruierbar und integer sind? Wenn das Fragen sind, mit denen Du Dich schon immer beruflich auseinandersetzen wolltest, dann suchen wir Dich!</p><br /><p><strong>Deine Aufgaben:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Entwicklung und Umsetzung der Konzepte f&uuml;r die Automatisierung und Orchestrierung von komplexen Kundensetups</li><br /><li>Entwicklung neuer Standards und Best Practices</li><br /><li>Unterst&uuml;tzung unserer Architekten bei der Planung von Kundenprojekten</li><br /><li>M&ouml;glich machen, was unm&ouml;glich erscheint</li><br /><li>Dokumentation von Best Practices und Workflows</li><br /><li>Verringerung von Ausfallzeiten und Rekonstruktionszeiten</li><br /></ul>','SysEleven GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('677','Technical Product Manager (m/f) at PARKU - The Parking App (Berlin, Deutschland)','<ul><br /><li>You take ownership of technical product roadmap, manage product backlog, define requirements for new features</li><br /><li>Validation of decisions (market analysis/benchmarks, user research, KPI monitoring, A/B testing)</li><br /><li>Ensure transparency among stakeholders</li><br /><li>Work with development teams using agile frameworks (Scrum and Kanban)</li><br /><li>Prepare user stories, sketches, wireframes etc. to communicate your ideas and requirements</li><br /><li>Monitor the customer satisfaction throughout our different platforms and keep improving it</li><br /><li>Work closely with Designers to dive deep into user experience to make even the most mundane interaction a delightful experience</li><br /><li>You drive and scale the rollout of all consumer facing platforms</li><br /><li>You collaborate closely with management about product strategy and upcoming projects and work on the interface between IT and business stakeholders</li><br /></ul>','PARKU - The Parking App');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('678','Lead/Sr Frontend Developer at the most exciting tech startup in Berlin! at Taxfix (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>What is Taxfix?</strong></p><br /><p>Taxfix is a well-funded tech startup in the heart of Berlin. It is our mission to make tax declarations easy!</p><br /><p>We believe that everybody, regardless of their income, deserves to get the maximum out of their tax returns. We have a vision that by using Taxfix, everyone will be able to submit their taxes, with the best results possible, in a matter of minutes from their mobile phone. We have developed our first public prototype and we got great feedback. The Taxfix app will soon be launched!</p><br /><p><strong>The team</strong></p><br /><p>Our team has a proven record in creating products that help people improve their lives. We share a passion for product development and a great user experience. We are a nice, small and international team, with a hard-working attitude, non-bureaucratic processes and open communication.</p><br /><p>We work in a multidisciplinary product team and we build elegant user interfaces using an exciting tech stack of React Native for our iOS app and future Android app. We use modern JavaScript across our stack, from our node.js API to our React Native view layer and React-based internal tools.</p><br /><p><strong>The role:</strong></p><br /><p>We are looking for an experienced and talented React Native Developer to join the team and take Taxfix to the next level.</p><br /><p>You will collaborate closely with a multidisciplinary team to define and ship the look, feel and interaction across our apps.</p><br /><p>You will implement custom UI components for our conversational interface across the product and on multiple platforms.</p>','Taxfix');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('679','Full Stack Software Engineer at FATMAP (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Build a 3D Map and Adventure Platform for the Outdoors</strong></p><br /><p>We are building the best 3D mapping platform for adventure. Are you a skier, boarder, runner or biker? Do you want to work on the future of outdoor maps?</p><br /><p>To build the best outdoor map platform we need to have an incredible underlying technology stack. We are investing in an infrastructure that is built to be the best in class, right down to the smallest micro-service. We already have some serious technology powering FATMAP, but there is much more in the pipeline, and that''s where you come in.&nbsp;</p><br /><p><strong>What you''ll be working on</strong></p><br /><p>As a 3D mapping platform built to support adventure, we have an ever increasing number of supporting services and technologies. You''ll be coming onboard to develop these services, and to help us become the tool of choice for everyone''s outdoor adventures. You will be applying your skills across many products and services and you could be working on anything from our user API to our CI infrastructure, using the many different technologies and tools at your disposal.</p><br /><p>Here are just a few examples of what you might be working on:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Building the services that power&nbsp;<a href="http://maps.fatmap.com/" rel="nofollow">http://maps.fatmap.com/</a>&nbsp;and our mobile apps</li><br /><li>Utilising our 3d map platform to build brand new adventure products</li><br /><li>Integrating with 3rd party APIs to import/share adventure data</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Check out some of our products&nbsp;here:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Web maps:&nbsp;<a href="http://maps.fatmap.com/" rel="nofollow">http://maps.fatmap.com/</a></li><br /><li>Our apps:&nbsp;<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/fatmap-3d-backcountry-skiing-resort-trail-map/id934760071?mt=8" rel="nofollow">iOS</a> /&nbsp;<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.terrascope.fatmapski&amp;hl=en" rel="nofollow">Android</a></li><br /></ul>','FATMAP');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('680','Senior Frontend Software Engineer with HTML, CSS, Javascript background (m/f) at WeltN24 GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><em>Our goal is to become the leading multimedia news corporation for high quality journalism in Germany and an essential part of achieving this goal is to work with the best developers. Are you a passionate frontend&nbsp;developer that can think outside of the box? Are you interested in working in an agile environment? If the answer is yes, then we are looking for you to strengthen our international cross-functional teams.</em> <br><br><strong>Us</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>We build and operate welt.de &ndash; one of the fastest full-responsive news portals in the world</li><br /><li>We are a cross-functional team creating the products that show off and monetise the journalistic content to its maximum potential</li><br /><li>We develop using modern web development techniques like progressive enhancement and continuous deployment, modern technologies such as ES2016, SCSS, React, Angular and Scala</li><br /><li>We believe in the benefits of a service oriented architecture, full automation of our infrastructure and the fast pace of independent teams</li><br /><li>We design, manage and support our own stack running on AWS</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>You</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You are a talented, creative developer, proficient with CSS, Javascript, HTML and modern web development technologies</li><br /><li>You have experience initiating or jumping into complex projects and following them though to success</li><br /><li>You have delivered several projects, engaging non-technical stakeholders in the process of delivering working software and have learned from difficult and challenging projects</li><br /><li>You have mentored junior developers and helped them move forward. You have supported your peers in developing their own technical leadership</li><br /><li>You are not afraid to engage people you disagree with</li><br /><li>You create positive, constructive conversations using objective statements and data, and people value your contributions to a debate</li><br /><li>You are a passionate, intelligent person who is a techie at heart, making a difference is what drives you</li><br /><li>You feel at-home working in a fast-moving team</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>What we offer<br></strong><br>You will be given the opportunity to apply your current strengths and plenty of room for professional growth. You will join a highly-qualified team working with agile methodologies using the newest media technologies in a modern office in the heart of Berlin. A variety of seminars and workshops provide you the opportunity to develop your specialized skill-set and your knowledge of comprehensive issues. Besides that, various conferences and TechTalks as well as our regular exchange with subsidiaries of Axel Springer (e.g. Zanox, idealo, KaufDa and Immonet) provide an opportunity to build a valuable network.<br><br></p><br /><p><strong>Contact<br></strong><br>Questions regarding this position (reference number 015700085) will be answered gladly by: Stefanie Neckel; stefanie.neckel@weltn24.de</p><br /><p>WELTN24 emphasizes equal opportunities. We welcome the applications of people with disabilities, whose integration is an important matter to us.<br><br><br><strong>To all recruitment agencies:</strong></p><br /><p>We, and our employees, do not accept unsolicited agency candidate profiles for this position. We will not be responsible for any applications related to unsolicited candidate profiles.<br><br><br></p>','WeltN24 GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('681','Senior Java / Scala Developer at Webtrekk GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>As part of our cross functional agile team, you will program, test and complete user stories along with the rest of our developers, but your background will make you the ''go to guy'' when it comes to concepts and technologies like Event Sourcing, Queuing, Microservice Architectures, Continuous Delivery, Configuration Management, Virtualisation, Containerisation, for example.</p><br /><p>You will ensure the successful delivery of high quality software products, be involved in the functional and technical conceptuation and delivery of new releases and components. You drive the design and development of new innovative products and services from the technical side.</p>','Webtrekk GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('682','Senior DevOps Engineer (m/f) at Wayfair GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>At Wayfair, we are looking to grow our Site Reliability Engineering team by bringing on board a talented Senior DevOps Engineer (m/f)&nbsp;to help manage the large scale physical and virtual server environment that underpins our global e-commerce platform.<br><br> Though the focus of this team is Linux, due to the nature of our platforms you will be involved with and exposed to a wide variety of systems. This team owns a large portion of our customer facing systems and services, and as such are heavily involved in the architecture, growth, and improvement of our various platforms.<br><br> Ever wondered what it would like to work at &lsquo;internet scale&rsquo;? At Wayfair we are dealing with internet scale challenges on a daily basis. With our traffic doubling year over year consistently we are faced with some pretty exciting and interesting challenges!</p><br /><p><br><br><strong>Some projects the team is currently working on in 2017:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Create and improve tools to aid in monitoring and control of our systems</li><br /><li>Enhance our infrastructure to support a variety of different disaster recovery options</li><br /><li>Expansion of current physical data centers</li><br /><li>Migrating targeted applications, sites, systems to cloud platforms</li><br /><li>Improving automation of systems, processes, and services</li><br /><li>Looking to the future - containers? Mesos?</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><br><strong>Responsibilities include:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Taking POC Systems and preparing them for production use by applying our standards to them and making them immutable</li><br /><li>Provide the highest level of technical escalation within the organization of our critical production platforms</li><br /><li>Improve security and performance of infrastructure</li><br /><li>Automate, Automate, Automate</li><br /><li>Provide Architecture &amp; Design feedback for all production platforms, as well as for other teams with in the organization</li><br /><li>Proactively monitor systems to anticipate business needs before they become critical path</li><br /><li>Thinking of what is the next big infrastructure thing</li><br /></ul>','Wayfair GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('683','Work at Zenjob in Berlin as React Frontend Developer at Zenjob (Berlin, Germany)','<p>For this position we are looking for someone who is passionate about frontend development with&nbsp;React. You will work on complex problems with cutting-edge technologies, in a tech-driven company.</p><br /><p>You will develop responsive, fun-to-use web applications for&nbsp;our B2B and B2C users.</p>','Zenjob');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('684','(Senior) Frontend Developer (m/w)  Internet of Things, Software Solutions Berli at Testo SE & Co. KGaA (Berlin, Deutschland)','<ul><br /><li>Entwurf, Entwicklung und Pflege von cloud-basierten Software-L&ouml;sungen unter Einbindung mobiler und station&auml;rer IoT-Hardware aus dem Messbereich als Teil des Scrum-Teams</li><br /><li>Umsetzung moderner Web-Bedienoberfl&auml;chen f&uuml;r unterschiedliche Devices (Responsive Design)</li><br /><li>Unterst&uuml;tzung in allen Projektphasen (Design, Umsetzung, Testing, Integration und Betrieb)</li><br /><li>Ein moderner Techstack (stackshare.io/testo/developer)</li><br /></ul>','Testo SE & Co. KGaA');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('685','Frontend Developer (m/w) at CINTEO GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Our development teams in Berlin and Stuttgart&nbsp;are looking for support &ndash; become a frontend developer at CINTEO and co-design our future!</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Your profile</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You are skilled in handling frontend web technologies like HTML5, CSS, JavaScript and Frameworks like Bootstrap, Foundation or Angular JS and you realize innovative, dynamic E-Commerce and marketing solutions.</li><br /><li>With your Know-How in responsive web design, content management systems, web services and web standards you develop frontends with state-of-the-art interface technologies for desktop and mobile devices.</li><br /><li>Ideally, you can use your existing knowledge in professional software development, SEO, User Experience and automatization to realize our frontend projects.</li><br /><li>Quality controls as well as ensured cross-browser compatibility reflect your conscientious and structured way of working.</li><br /><li>Your proficiency in English helps you to communicate smoothly with your future colleagues in our qualified and interdisciplinary teams.</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>We offer you</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>State of the art software development</li><br /><li>We &lt;3 open source</li><br /><li>Start-up atmosphere with grown-up background</li><br /><li>No top-down hierarchy. We trust in your self-organization</li><br /><li>Flexible working hours and home office friendly</li><br /><li>Modern offices&nbsp;in Berlin and Stuttgart</li><br /></ul>','CINTEO GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('686','Senior-Backend-Developer (in Start-Up) (m/w) at Patientus GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Was Dich bei uns erwartet:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Du pflegst unsere aktuelle Plattform</li><br /><li>Von Anfang an dabei: Du entwickelst unsere neuen Releases (Version 2.0/Gr&uuml;ne Wiese)</li><br /><li>Bei uns findest Du den Freiraum, Deine eigenen Ideen einzubringen und neue Technologien und IT System-Architektur umzusetzen</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Unser Angebot an Dich</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Regelm&auml;&szlig;ige, individuelle Coachings und klare Zielsetzungen</li><br /><li>Workshops und Teamevents</li><br /><li>Flache Hierarchien und kurze Entscheidungswege</li><br /><li>Ein starkes und motiviertes Team, das sich auf neue Kollegen freut</li><br /><li>Einmaliger Start-Up Spirit mit solider Finanzierung</li><br /><li>Wir sorgen immer f&uuml;r gen&uuml;gend Getr&auml;nke, Nervennahrung und Obst</li><br /><li>Top-Netzwerk (zu Burda geh&ouml;ren Unternehmen wie XING, CLIQZ (Mozilla), HolidayCheck etc.)</li><br /></ul>','Patientus GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('687','Fullstack JavaScript Team Manager at Webtrekk GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>In this role, you will be leading a cross functional team of around 8 to 10 software engineers (Frontend-, Backend- and QA Engineers) which is mainly responsible for our Marketing Automation platform and further important products like mobile SDK&rsquo;s, website beacons and tag management.</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Manage and support your team to find best solutions for complex problems</li><br /><li>Ensure a close connection to Product Owner/stakeholders throughout the development process and guarantee an aligned strategy across all agile teams</li><br /><li>Lead discussions with the team and management to define best practices and approaches</li><br /><li>Set goals, objectives and priorities. Mentor team members, providing guidance and carrying out regular performance reviews</li><br /></ul>','Webtrekk GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('688','Senior Frontend Developer (m/f) at movingimage (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>movingimage is in a process of fast growth and therefore looking for qualified senior software engineers for its newly formed teams. We are hiring talented engineers with a broad and deep understanding of technology, visionary, yet very pragmatic developers, who can envision and implement next generation software innovations.</p><br /><p>You will be working with our multinational team on designing and implementing enterprise software solutions. And there''s a lot more to learn about us, for example from our video:</p><br /><p><a href="https://e.video-cdn.net/video?video-id=A5ZJB3cguCu-duGx3Hy3Q4&amp;player-id=EKGFrtKUDHbdBELNij71Hk&amp;width=800" rel="nofollow">https://e.video-cdn.net/video?video-id=A5ZJB3cguCu-duGx3Hy3Q4&amp;player-id=EKGFrtKUDHbdBELNij71Hk&amp;width=800</a></p><br /><p><strong>Interested?</strong></p><br /><p>Then you''re in the right place, because we are currently looking for an experienced:</p><br /><p><strong>Senior Frontend Developer (m/f)</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Would you like to&hellip;</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>play an important role in our multinational agile software development team?</li><br /><li>use new technologies and solve thrilling development tasks?</li><br /><li>implement high-quality and scalable video asset management and video streaming solutions for enterprise customers?</li><br /><li>write clean and reusable code with page performance in mind?</li><br /><li>deliver a rich, engaging and unmatched user experience?</li><br /><li>continuously update and expand the existing product?</li><br /><li>experience how the principles of the Agile Methodology are implemented and lived within the whole organization?</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Are you able to&hellip; </strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>present relevant work experience as Frontend Developer of at least 3 years?</li><br /><li>prove your vast experience with JavaScript and and Typescript?</li><br /><li>demonstrate your skills with frameworks like AngularJS and Bootstrap?</li><br /><li>show very good programming skills in CSS3 and HTML5</li><br /><li>demonstrate that you are familiar with LESS or SASS?</li><br /><li>show your extensive experience with Webpack?</li><br /><li>prove that you are familiar with unit testing tools like Karma or Jasmine?</li><br /><li>show proven experience in implementing RESTful APIs for responsive web applications?</li><br /><li>communicate in English in all relevant courses of business?</li><br /><li>be open and a team player who is able to carry out goal-oriented analysis and solve problems</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Ideally you also possess</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>advanced skills in Node.js - experience with MEAN - a good feeling for customers UX/UI needs</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Do you feel addressed? We should get to know each other!</strong></p><br /><p><strong>We offer&hellip;</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>an exciting perspective, a wide range of tasks, constantly new challenges and a desire for thinking out-of-the-box as part of our corporate culture</li><br /><li>an open working environment that is characterized by teamwork and cross-functional cooperation and in which heart and humor are key figures</li><br /><li>freedom to introduce your own ideas and to take responsibility</li><br /><li>a modern selection of hardware devices</li><br /><li>a professional collaboration with Scrum Masters</li><br /><li>high-quality and scalable video asset management and video streaming solutions for enterprise customers</li><br /><li>free German and English courses</li><br /><li>a weekly breakfast</li><br /><li>Flexible work time with 30 days of holiday</li><br /><li>stable working environment</li><br /><li>Hack days twice a year</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Even more interested?</p><br /><p>Apply now!</p><br /><p>Submit your meaningful application documents noting your earliest available starting date through our online portal at the following link:</p><br /><p><a href="https://movingimage24gmbh.softgarden.io/apply-choice?0&amp;jobDbId=795181&amp;sgClickId=21429680&amp;l=en" rel="nofollow">https://movingimage24gmbh.softgarden.io/apply-choice?0&amp;jobDbId=795181&amp;sgClickId=21429680&amp;l=en</a></p><br /><p><strong>Your contact:</strong></p><br /><p>Mutabazi Nzirubusa | HR Recruiter</p><br /><p>MovingIMAGE24 GmbH</p><br /><p>Stralauer Allee 7 | 10245 Berlin</p><br /><p>You will find more about us on our website: <a href="http://www.movingimage.com" rel="nofollow">www.movingimage.com</a></p>','movingimage');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('689','SENIOR FRONT-END DEVELOPER (M/F) REQUIRED at Department One GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Are you looking for a position with an international dimension, with great clients and exciting projects in the world&rsquo;s most beautiful city? We offer you flexible development opportunities and a dynamic service provider with excellent technical competence.</p><br /><p>Our company has been providing innovative technical solutions for strong brands and partners since 2006. We have developed an efficient and effective backend that has been essential to our success. We are constantly developing, adapting, and expanding our backend to meet the latest technical demands. Our company offers an agile working environment that cultivates collaboration and creativity.</p><br /><br /><p><strong>REQUIRED FOR IMMEDIATE START:</strong></p><br /><p><strong>SENIOR FRONT-END DEVELOPER </strong><strong>TO JOIN OUR BERLIN-BASED TEAM</strong></p><br /><p><br /><p>You will specialise in the development of new and existing websites and web-based applications, as well as in the use of content management systems to create mobile-optimised web pages, including the connection to our technical back-end operation. You will be responsible for front-end development and the design of user-interface solutions. You will work in cooperation with our creative design team in developing website concepts (wireframes and customer journey mapping) and innovative web applications using PHP, HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript.</p><br /><br /><p>Sound attractive?</p>','Department One GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('690','Big Data Engineer (f/m) at The ADEX GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<ul><br /><li>Designing and implementing new features of the Big Data DMP (new automated analyses, data aggregation or summarizing)</li><br /><li>Optimizing our processes and working on Apache Spark to solve real Big Data problems</li><br /><li>Converting new business requirements into data processes</li><br /><li>Supervising and maintain our Big Data systems</li><br /></ul>','The ADEX GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('691','Java Developer CMS (m/f) at Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Java Developer CMS (m/f)</strong><br><strong>Location: Berlin</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Exciting IT challenges at an academic publisher?</strong><br><strong>Where else but here: at Springer Nature!</strong></p><br /><p><br>Springer Nature is a world leading research, education and professional publisher. You may not be so familiar with our company name, but Springer Nature is home to trusted brands including Springer, Nature Research, BioMed Central, Palgrave Macmillan and Scientific American, as well as a family of respected and specialist imprints.</p><br /><p><br><strong>What&rsquo;s it actually like to work with us?</strong><br>In the context of our digital strategies, in Berlin we develop new software and optimize our global platforms (e. g. springernature.com, nature.com, springermedizin.de, palgrave.com). Together with colleagues in London, Pune and New York we work to ensure that our customers enjoy access to individual content &ndash; every day and from anywhere in the world. We strive to make the digital division a place where people and ideas thrive.</p><br /><p><br><strong>The Team</strong><br>We are the team behind the &bdquo;Global CMS&ldquo; platform project at Springer Nature. We work closely together with our users, analysing the requirements and business needs to jointly find the optimal solution. Besides continuous development of the products we also care about overall system stability, performance and maintainability.<br>A good CMS developer in Springer Nature is modest and humble, open to learn from anyone regardless of age, gender, race, role or experience, values social interactions and is able to self-reflect. They are self-conscious and smart, but never smart-ass. They favour building relationships over building systems. Continuously looking for improvement, but not chasing perfection and accepting failure. They have a strong preference of working together and sharing knowledge as opposed to quickly getting this done alone.</p>','Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('692','Ruby on Rails Developer (f/m) at homify (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Implementing upcoming features along our full stack, with special focus on either the UI or the backend:</p><br /><p><em>Frontend:</em></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Maintaining and revamping the UI/UX of existing features</li><br /><li>Have an active contribution in re-designing and future-proofing our website</li><br /></ul><br /><p><em>Backend:</em></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Maintaining, improving, revamping and expanding our existing features and business model</li><br /><li>Supporting the backend and services API team</li><br /><li>Being a key player in re-designing and future-proofing the homify brand products</li><br /></ul>','homify');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('693','Senior Java Developer (m/f) at Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Senior Java Developer (m/f)</strong><br><strong>Location: Berlin</strong></p><br /><p><br>Join an exciting and fast-paced team as we develop and build global tools utilized globally within Springer Nature. We are currently seeing a mid-to-senior level Java Developer to join our growing team to work on a variety of core company applications.<br>In particular the role will focus on development of Liferay and related tools.</p><br /><p><strong>About the role:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Participate in global projects of varying sizes and provide input to the plan</li><br /><li>Participate and support communication between various applications such as SAP, Concur travel, Google and Jive</li><br /><li>Responsible for providing estimates to design and build timelines</li><br /><li>Become an expert with development surrounding front-end/back-end technologies</li><br /><li>Work closely with both IT and related business teams located globally</li><br /><li>Regularly meet with other developers and the user community</li><br /><li>Accountable for all applications developed and &ldquo;pushed&rdquo; in the production environment. Will be responsible for applications developed by others</li><br /><li>Take direction from department senior management and works on current projects</li><br /><li>Meet or exceed all task deadlines assigned</li><br /><li>Develop and document programming specifications from business requirements in coordination with development team</li><br /><li>Responsible for reviewing and resolving problems in a timely fashion</li><br /><li>Follow the predefined development cycle for all applications</li><br /><li>Perform and manage tasks independently or as part of an international or local development team</li><br /><li>Perform related duties as required</li><br /></ul>','Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('694','Java Engineer (m/f)  Web Development at Visual Meta GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>We are Visual Meta, a successful and steadily growing web company, founded in 2009 and acquired by the Axel Springer Group in 2011. Operating from a great office in central Berlin, we run 14 online shopping portals worldwide under the brands <strong>LadenZeile</strong>, <strong>ShopAlike</strong> and <strong>UmS&oacute;Lugar</strong>. We offer the professionalism of a big player and the company culture of a startup. Our vision? To become THE global service for comparison shopping. &nbsp;</p><br /><p>How are we trying to achieve that? During the last years, we have been building a strong, international team. We deal with modern web technologies, large databases, millions of images, data mining and analysis, search technologies and machine learning. We code stuff that matters and reaches millions of people. We believe in lean and agile software engineering. Our technology stack is plain Java, MySQL, Hadoop, HBase, Spring, Eclipse, Elasticsearch and Tomcat.</p><br /><p>Your mission at Visual Meta? As &ldquo;<a href="http://app.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Careers.aspx?nl=1&amp;k=Job&amp;j=orDq4fwi&amp;s=stackoverflow" rel="nofollow">Java Engineer (m/f) &ndash; Web Development</a>&ldquo; you will be mainly working on the user site of our product. If you have an analytical, detail oriented as well as agile mindset and would like to work in a highly international tech company, then this might be the right opportunity for you.</p><br /><p><strong>Your challenge:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You are in charge of implementing new features in cooperation with our product management and graphics team</li><br /><li>You proactively look for ways to improve our platform and products</li><br /><li>You set up A/B-Tests to assure effectiveness and user acceptance of new functionalities</li><br /><li>You rapidly fix bugs and solve problems</li><br /><li>You actively take part in product improvement decisions and process optimizations</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Our offer:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>We code stuff that matters- Be part of our agile environment (Scrum), work with the latest technology and participate in regular tech-events (e.g. Hackathons, TechTalks)</li><br /><li>We love diversity- Our team contains over 50 nationalities</li><br /><li>We see your development as our priority- Profit from a structured onboarding process, internal and external training possibilities as well as room for further professional development</li><br /><li>We take responsibility- With us you have the option to become socially involved (e.g. charity lunch)</li><br /><li>We care for you- Benefit from a company pension plan, flexible working hours, 27 vacation days, healthy snacks and sport activities (yoga, soccer, volleyball)</li><br /><li>We enjoy spending time together- Join in for Friday beers, movie nights, team events, table football and ping-pong</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Is this the job you are looking for?</strong></p><br /><p>Go ahead and submit your application in English including CV, cover letter, salary expectations and your availability by using the following link: https://app.jobvite.com/j?cj=orDq4fwi&amp;s=stackoverflow. As your responsible recruiter,&nbsp;<strong>Nikolina Dosen&nbsp;</strong>will be your point of contact.&nbsp;</p>','Visual Meta GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('695','Frontend Entwickler (m/w) Standort Berlin at REWE Digital GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland) (allows remote)','<p><strong><strong>Das gibt es bei uns zu tun:</strong></strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Entwicklung von qualitativ hochwertigen E-Commerce Anwendungen</li><br /><li>Enge Zusammenarbeit in interdisziplin&auml;ren agilen Teams</li><br /><li>Eigenverantwortliches Arbeiten</li><br /><li>Mitwirkung bei der Gestaltung von Softwarearchitekturen und der Auswahl von Technologien</li><br /><li>Intensiver Wissensaustausch mit erfahrenen Kolleginnen und Kollegen</li><br /><li>Weiterentwicklung der pers&ouml;nlichen methodischen und technischen Exzellenz</li><br /></ul>','REWE Digital GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('696','Senior Software Developer at Coresystems AG (Berlin, Germany)','<p>THE ROLE</p><br /><p>We are looking for talented and motivated engineers to join our team here at Coresystems who can hit the ground running and take our product to the next level, as we scale up and develop our business in our target markets. The engineers who are building our Core Platform work across the stack, always willing to go the extra mile to deliver the highest quality in enterprise software. As a Developer for Coresystems you are building the tools today that will redefine tomorrow''s Field Service.</p><br /><p>CURIOUS ABOUT THE DAY-TO-DAY?</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Lead the technical design and architecture of our Core Platform (Backend &amp; Frontend) and take ownership over the Platform Roadmap</li><br /><li>Define the future of APIs, Integrations with 3rd party Systems like ERPs, Exstensibility, Modularity,&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Lead the design of the Cloud Data Architecture</li><br /><li>Understand and stay informed about the new Technologies and the benefits they could provide to our Platform</li><br /><li>Contribute in coding/reviewing both on the backend and the frontend side</li><br /><li>Work with the Product Team to ensure the Platform fits with the Product Vision</li><br /></ul>','Coresystems AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('697','Java Software Architect at Webtrekk GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Your responsibilities</strong>:</p><br /><p>In this position, you will strengthen one of our agile development teams and design and develop a high-performance delivery platform supporting several products to handle a huge number of requests:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Get involved in all phases of the product lifecycle: requirements analysis, design process, implementation, testing and deployment</li><br /><li>You will develop new and optimise existing components always with an eye on scalability, performance and maintenance.</li><br /><li>Create proof of concepts and MVP&rsquo;s</li><br /><li>Lead your teams technical vision</li><br /></ul>','Webtrekk GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('698','Senior Full Stack JavaScript Engineer at SatoshiPay Germany UG (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>TL;DR</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Node, React, Mongo/Postgres, Bitcoin, Docker</li><br /><li>Full-time preferred</li><br /><li>Immediately</li><br /><li>Berlin, Germany</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What you will be doing</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Design and develop highly scalable microservices with Node and Docker</li><br /><li>Deploy and scale microservices in a fully distributed environment</li><br /><li>Securely interact with different blockchains</li><br /><li>Create and operate scalable APIs for clients and front-end developers</li><br /><li>Make design decisions as one of the two key engineers of our team</li><br /><li>Support front-end developers with an easy build and bundling setup</li><br /></ul>','SatoshiPay Germany UG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('699','Web-Developer (m/f) / Frontend for whistleblowing system at Business Keeper AG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Configuring accounts and making a valuable contribution at the same time?<br>Then we are the right company for you.</p><br /><p>At Business Keeper AG you get the chance to do what you love &ndash; the Frontend-Development &ndash; while providing a valuable contribution to society. With our electronic whistleblowing system the company has been making an important progress towards an economic culture based on values and integrity.</p><br /><p>As Web-Developer/Frontend-Developer (m/f) you are responsible for creating and updating customer accounts as well as continuous optimization of our Java-based web application in cooperation with our dedicated and international team.</p><br /><p>Become a part of an innovative, sustainably growing company located in the heart of Berlin. We are offering an independent working environment, diverse projects, fast decision-making processes, flexible working hours and interesting benefits.</p><br /><p><strong><br>Our Benefits</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>regular team meetings</li><br /><li>personalised training measures</li><br /><li>flexible working hours</li><br /><li>benefit packages including gym membership discount, a company pension plan or restaurant vouchers</li><br /><li>we promote team spirit with regular company-internal events</li><br /><li>Business Keeper AG is located in the centre of Berlin &ndash; right across from Berlin''s most famous shopping centre, KADEWE. This means our employees can get to work quickly and conveniently.</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong><br>Responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Creating and updating customer accounts</li><br /><li>Continuous optimization of our application in HTML/CSS and JavaScript</li><br /><li>Common implementation of design requirements and technical concepts</li><br /><li>Interface role and close cooperation with Software Development and Account Management</li><br /></ul>','Business Keeper AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('700','PHP Full Stack Developer (m/w) at A&O Holding GmbH & Co. KG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>BE UNCONVENTIONAL</strong><br><strong>BE A PART OF OUR COMMUNITY!</strong></p><br /><br /><p>Gepr&auml;gt durch flache Hierarchien, st&auml;ndiges Wachstum, Innovation und hohe Dynamik bietet A&amp;O auch f&uuml;r Quereinsteiger eine tolle Karriereplattform. Wir legen gro&szlig;en Wert auf einen fairen, sozialen und verantwortungsvollen Umgang miteinander. Denn gemeinsam macht nicht nur die Arbeit viel mehr Spa&szlig; &ndash; sondern auch der Erfolg.</p><br /><p>F&uuml;r unsere Bereiche Software und Webentwicklung suchen wir am Standort Berlin Mitte ab sofort eine</p><br /><p><strong>PHP Full Stack Developer (m/w)</strong><br>in Vollzeit</p><br /><p>Unser Ziel ist es, dem Kunden eine funktionale Website mit bestm&ouml;glicher Buchungstechnologie zur Verf&uuml;gung zu stellen &ndash; dabei schaffen wir kontinuierlich Barrieren aus dem Weg und passen uns neuen Trends an.</p><br /><p>Aktuell arbeitet ein kleines Team von kreativen und sympathischen K&ouml;pfen im Frontend- und Backend-Bereich daran, unsere Buchungstechnologie stetig anhand konkreter Kundennutzen weiterzuentwickeln und jeden Tag aufs Neue zu verbessern.</p>','A&O Holding GmbH & Co. KG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('701','JS Frontend Engineer at Europes most popular home&living shopping platform at Home24 AG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Do you feel like the work you do makes a difference and moves the business in a meaningful way? Are you interested in building software used by millions of customers? Do you like writing performant, high quality code at a rapid pace? If you answered yes to these questions, you could be just the person we&rsquo;re looking for to join our team at Home24.</p><br /><p>We are looking for a great Senior Frontend Engineer who is passionate about developing customer-facing front end solutions that will deliver a great user experience - whether you&rsquo;re on your smartphone, tablet or home computer. In joining our team you will get the opportunity to work on some of the most interesting and challenging problems we can offer. This position is full-time and based in our cool office in Berlin.</p><br /><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Build beautiful, fast,efficient and reusable frontend solutions</li><br /><li>Build prototypes and proof of concepts to demonstrate emerging technologies</li><br /><li>Working with product managers and UX designers to implement the next generation of the Home24 e-commerce experience</li><br /><li>Use RESTful APIs for communication with our backend services</li><br /><li>Work in a small agile team collaborating with designers and other engineers taking features from concept to production</li><br /><li>Identify and adopt best practices for software and front-end engineering</li><br /><li>Make demos for the whole company to share achievements</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What we can offer you</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Opportunity to use state of the art front end development tools</li><br /><li>Become a part of a highly motivated world class team of technology professionals</li><br /><li>An open culture to learn, share new ideas, solve hard problems and opportunity to demonstrate your creativity to make a real difference</li><br /><li>Opportunities for advancement, independence and the autonomy to take on responsibility</li><br /><li>Benefits including relocation support, employee discount, team events, free fruit, drinks and much more</li><br /></ul>','Home24 AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('702','JavaScript Developer (m/f) to create beautiful & scalable interfaces at plista GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>As a JavaScript developer (m/f), you are part of our team, "Platform Architecture". You are responsible for the development of user-friendly, scalable and high-performing interfaces by mainly using Angular. These interfaces are used by custumers across the world, and our main goal is to provide one web application that fits all the different needs from the markets that plista is operates on. You will work in a crossfunctional SCRUM Squad in close cooperation with our product management team.</strong></p><br /><p><br /><p><strong>Your responsibilities:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Joint responsibility for the consistent "look and feel" of our internal Angular platform</li><br /><li>Development software by mainly using AngularJS and Angular</li><br /><li>Development and maintenance of user-friendly web based interfaces</li><br /><li>Optimizing interfaces for fluent workflow</li><br /><li>Development of GUI concepts in cooperation with the product management</li><br /><li>Planning of REST APIs in cooperation with the backend development team</li><br /><li>Take care of the processes as a team (plannings, retrospectives, etc.)</li><br /></ul>','plista GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('703','Softwareentwickler (m/w) Java at IT4IPM GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Werden Sie Teil unseres erfolgreichen Teams am Standort Berlin und unterst&uuml;tzen Sie uns zum n&auml;chstm&ouml;glichen Termin als</p><br /><p><strong>Softwareentwickler (m/w) Java</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Ihre Aufgaben:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Beratung der Fachabteilungen der GEMA zu technischen L&ouml;sungsm&ouml;glichkeiten, bei der Erstellung von Fachkonzepten und zum effektiven Einsatz vorhandener Software&shy;systeme auf Basis der Gesch&auml;ftsprozesse</li><br /><li>Technische Federf&uuml;hrung bei Anforderungsbewertung und L&ouml;sungsfindung</li><br /><li>Konzeption und Entwicklung von IT-L&ouml;sungen in der Wartung und Weiterentwicklung und in Projekten</li><br /><li>Erarbeitung von technischen Design-Dokumenten und Teilnahme an Design Reviews</li><br /><li>Softwaretechnische Umsetzung im Bereich Java und PL / SQL</li><br /><li>Unterst&uuml;tzung bei Produktionsproblemen und bei der Herausgabe von neuen Produkt&shy;releases (von Entwicklungsseite)</li><br /><li>Integration der individuellen System&shy;land&shy;schaften &uuml;ber ESB, insbesondere service&shy;orientierte Architekturen und webbasierte L&ouml;sungen</li><br /><li>Ber&uuml;cksichtigung vorgegebener Methoden, Standards und Qualit&auml;ts&shy;sicherungs&shy;vorschriften</li><br /><li>Beobachtung von Markt- und Technologie-Trends und Ableitung notwendiger Einf&uuml;hrung solcher</li><br /></ul>','IT4IPM GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('704','DevOps / Platform Engineer / Back End - Cloud Foundry, BOSH, Ruby at Avarteq (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Your core tasks</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Construction and operation of highly automated Platform as a Service solutions</li><br /><li>Working with Open Source Software</li><br /><li>Implementation and maintenance of system automation</li><br /><li>Support for existing PaaS applications</li><br /><li>Customer consulting regarding best practices in Cloud environments</li><br /></ul>','Avarteq');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('705','Fullstack-Java-Entwickler (m/w) at Tembit Software GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Ihre Aufgaben:</strong></p><br /><p>Sie arbeiten bei uns als Fullstack-Java-Entwickler (m/w) in einem Team erfahrener Softwareentwickler/-innen und be&shy;rei&shy;chern unsere testgetriebene Produktentwicklung.</p><br /><p>Ihre Programmiersprache ist Java und Sie nehmen die Herausforderung an, eine bew&auml;hrte Banking-Software permanent wei&shy;ter&shy;zuentwickeln, an neue Architekturen anzupassen und durch gezieltes Refactoring die Zukunftsf&auml;higkeit sowie Si&shy;cher&shy;heit der Webl&ouml;sung zu gew&auml;hrleisten. Die Software ist bei Banken und gro&szlig;en Firmen in der Cloud und &bdquo;on premise&ldquo; im praktischen Einsatz.</p><br /><p><strong>Das erwartet Sie:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>abwechslungsreiche und anspruchsvolle Aufgaben in einem kreativen, innovativen Arbeitsumfeld am Standort Berlin</li><br /><li>ein sehr kollegiales und menschliches Miteinander in kleinen und best&auml;ndigen Teams</li><br /><li>flexible Arbeitszeiten, attraktive Verg&uuml;tung, betriebliche Altersvorsorge, Jobrad, kostenfreie Getr&auml;nke und Obst, Chill-Out-Lounge mit Kickertisch, Team-Events, Englischkurse</li><br /><li>modernes B&uuml;ro- und Gesch&auml;ftsgeb&auml;ude (inkl. Einkaufsm&ouml;glichkeiten) im Norden Berlins</li><br /><li>ergonomisch ausgestattete Arbeitspl&auml;tze und freie Rechnerwahl (Mac/Linux/Windows)</li><br /></ul>','Tembit Software GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('706','Cloud Engineer- API Developer at Kenkou GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Overview:</strong></p><br /><br /><br /><br /><p>The <strong>Cloud Engineer- API Developer</strong>&nbsp;will be responsible for building and scaling a reliable state of the art cloud-services platform. In this role, the position will be responsible for development and support of multi-tiered systems that captures data 24 hours a day supporting millions of devices, makes data accessible at scale via APIs and front-end web systems, and leverage established tools to automate the operation and maintenance of such systems with high levels of performance and availability.</p><br /><br /><br /><br /><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><br /><br /><br /><br /><ul><br /><li><br />Development and support of our cloud-based services to provide reliability and scalability for applications to both individual consumer and health industry customers.<br /></li><br /><li><br />Work closely with product, engineering, QA, DevOps and support teams to define and refine our cloud platform to achieve company objectives.<br /></li><br /><li><br />Ensure high availability and provide application support to enable 24x7 monitoring<br /></li><br /><li><br />Continually improve operational processes and procedures<br /></li><br /><li><br />Collaborate with other technology teams and to define protocols, API''s, to operate and acquire data from large numbers of Internet-connected devices&nbsp;<br /></li><br /><li><br />Develop and support all aspects of our cloud presence on Amazon Web Services<br /></li><br /></ul>','Kenkou GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('707','Site Reliability Engineer at Minodes (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>From a technology perspective, we have thousands of sensors with our own firmware installed in our customers&rsquo; retail stores around the world. We process terabytes of data via machine learning algorithms and provide a self-service platform for our analytics solutions. We offer a great opportunity for personal and professional growth in a multicultural environment. We work, learn and develop while having lots of fun on the way.<br><br>Join our team as a&nbsp;<strong>Site Reliability Engineer/ Systems Engineer</strong>.<br><br><strong>What we do all day:</strong><br>We create a beautiful self-service platform for our analytics solutions using modern tools and libaries. We process, query and analyze terabytes of sensor and geospatial advertising data. We work in cross-functional teams in order to create a premium experience for our customers. If you are passionate like us, you love to learn, work and share knowledge with your team, you will be a good fit.</p>','Minodes');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('708','Full Stack Engineer (JavaScript) (m/f) Change the way people eat forever at HelloFresh (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Who we&rsquo;re looking for</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have 2+ years of solid development experience</li><br /><li>You ideally have experience in&nbsp;React/JavaScript/Ansible/Node.js</li><br /><li>You have a lot of experience with building different kinds of front-end web applications</li><br /><li>You have experience with DevOps topics, like deploying and monitoring your applications</li><br /><li>You can work in fast-paced teams</li><br /><li>You know how to take responsibility</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What we offer</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Have a fast growing, dynamic and diverse IT team</li><br /><li>The possibility to experiment with any new technology</li><br /><li>A homegrown state of the art micro-service architecture (yes for the front-end as well)</li><br /><li>A great open source mindset</li><br /><li>Choose your own hardware to work on</li><br /><li>The opportunity to work with the newest and hottest technologies</li><br /><li>Bright minds for you to measure yourself with and learn from</li><br /><li>Give you the possibility to grow</li><br /><li>Work in an office in the coolest city in the world, Berlin</li><br /><li>A competitive salary for the startup job market</li><br /><li>Relocation service to help anyone moving to Berlin from abroad</li><br /></ul><br /><p>You can get a taste of what we''ve been working on by checking out our <strong><a title="HelloTech Engineering Blog" href="https://engineering.hellofresh.com/" rel="nofollow">engineering blog</a></strong>.&nbsp;</p>','HelloFresh');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('709','Senior Software Engineer (Scala) at LiveIntent (Berlin, Germany)','<p>As a <strong>Senior Software Engineer</strong>, you&rsquo;ll work in an agile environment with talented, cross-functional teams to design, implement, and iterate on products that satisfy customer needs and drive company growth. Our tech stack runs on a Linux foundation and includes Scala, Akka, Node.js, DynamoDB and PostgreSQL. As a senior engineer you will help promulgate good design and coding practices, leading by example while at the same time gaining valuable experience. You will be responsible for the design, implementation, and delivery of products that fuel every part of the business.</p><br /><p><strong>What </strong><strong>we offer:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Private office in a shared working environment at WeWork</li><br /><li>Located very central location at Potsdamer Platz next to Tiergarten</li><br /><li>Talented group of people to work with</li><br /><li>Playstation for after work fun</li><br /><li>A friendly international team</li><br /><li>Subsidized gym membership</li><br /><li>Free beer tap</li><br /></ul>','LiveIntent');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('710','QA Analyst (m/f) at Project A (Berlin, Deutschland)','<ul><br /><li>Implementation and continous improvement of the QA processes to ensure high quality standards</li><br /><li>Documentation of bugs on basis of significant bug reports or direct agreements</li><br /><li>Preparation and evaluation of test documentations</li><br /><li>Maintenance of existing test-cases and test-scripts as well as reporting the results to your responsible colleagues</li><br /></ul>','Project A');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('711','Rails Web Developer (de/en) at Giant Monkey Software Engineering GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Your job will be developing the leading visitor management software for museums.</p><br /><p>We want to build the most technologically advanced web-based software for museums. With <strong>GraphQL, Angular, Ruby on Rails</strong> and <strong>Docker</strong>.</p><br /><p><span>We need you to support us with backend programming with <strong>ROR</strong>, including orchestrating controller actions and backend services.</span></p><br /><p>Together with your team, consisting of young, highly motivated software engineers, we want to push the world of museums forward. Allowing better and easier access to culture. Taking advantage of digital media in order to reach younger generations.</p><br /><p>We offer you an <strong>attractive working place in Berlin Mitte</strong>, next to Rosenthaler Platz. In an office full of <strong>natural light</strong>, situated in a <strong>traditional old-style building</strong>, with a view out to Weinbergspark and a fair salary. You will work with exciting colleagues on cutting edge development.</p><br /><p>You will take on the following duties:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Programming backend software</li><br /><li>Writing tests and documentation</li><br /><li>Designing and architecting new features</li><br /><li>Running necessary infrastructure</li><br /><li>Working together with colleagues and management as a team.</li><br /></ul><br /><p>You will be the 9th full time member of our team so expect to take on responsibility.</p>','Giant Monkey Software Engineering GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('712','Senior Software Engineer, Search & Browse (Scala & Solr/ElasticSearch) at Zalando SE (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>THE OPPORTUNITY</strong><br><br>As a software engineer in the area of "Search &amp; Browse" you will focus on developing Zalando''s in-house search engine service providing highly relevant personalized search results helping millions of people find their favorite fashion items. You will be working with state-of-the-art technology to build a SAAS component which can be fully leveraged within our Zalando platform. <br>Your main challenges will include working with large amounts of data, deliver high-quality search results and also provide a high-performance, stable and auto-scaling production system. You will be part of a small, autonomous, and highly ambitious team consisting of experienced Scala developers and expert data scientists pushing "Fashion Search" one step further every day.<br><br><strong>WHAT WE''RE LOOKING FOR</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have 3+ years of experience, working as a Scala Developer (or with any other functional programming language). A technical degree is a plus.</li><br /><li>You are experienced with lucene-based technologies like Solr/ElasticSearch</li><br /><li>You are keen on collaborating closely with Data Scientists &amp; Data Analysts</li><br /><li>A keen interest in applied Machine Learning, Natural Language Processing and Data Mining is essential, work experience in these topics a plus</li><br /><li>You write well-structured and tested code in the spirit of Effective Java and Clean Code that easily scales to Enterprise level</li><br /><li>You love to optimize processes &amp; code and to use new technologies</li><br /><li>You are experienced in building, evaluating, maintaining and improving large-scale, data-driven products</li><br /><li>You have worked with current Big Data technology (e.g. Hadoop/MapReduce, Amazon EMR)</li><br /><li>Knowing near-realtime stream processing and/or message-driven architectures (e.g. Spark, Storm, Aerospike, Kafka) is a plus</li><br /><li>Experience with Cloud Computing platforms such as&nbsp;AWS is a plus</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You will be part of an agile and very experienced team that will further develop our search pipeline in short release cycles</li><br /><li>You will implement highly-scalable solutions with state-of-the-art-technologies together with your team</li><br /><li>You are ready to tweak and optimize our search for various markets all across Europe with more than a dozen different languages</li><br /><li>You will transfer algorithmic prototypes to enterprise level, highly-scalable and fault-tolerant solutions using the right technology for the job</li><br /><li>You are collaborating with our data scientists to improve and extend our search engine and other analytical customer experience solutions</li><br /><li>You will be part of a multi-cultural team with different native languages, skills and backgrounds</li><br /><li>Design, develop, deploy, operate &amp; improve software solutions that impact millions of Zalando customers</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>WHAT YOU CAN EXPECT FROM US</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Community</strong>. Tech culture of trust and empowerment, <a href="https://github.com/zalando" rel="nofollow">open source commitment</a>, meetups, game nights, +100 internal technical and fun guilds, tech talks, product demos, Coderdojos, parties and events.</p><br /><p><strong>Perks.</strong> Competitive salary, 40% Zalando shopping discount, discounts from external partners, public transport discounts, relocation assistance for internationals, free drinks and fruits, hardware of your choice.</p><br /><p><strong>Development.</strong> Tour of Mastery, extensive onboarding, personal branding support, opportunity to attend and speak at conferences and meetups, and encouragement to publish work.</p><br /><p><strong>Work Environment.</strong> Self-organized, &nbsp;autonomous teams and flexible working hours.</p><br /><p><strong>Scale. Unparalleled levels of data and opportunities.</strong></p><br /><p><br><br><strong>WANT TO JOIN US? THEN GO AHEAD AND APPLY!</strong></p>','Zalando SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('713','Javascript Developer at BILD GmbH & Co. KG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Deine Herausforderung</strong></p><br /><p>"Ich m&ouml;chte in einem Fu&szlig;ballstadion stehen und mit meinem Telefon einen Artikel schreiben und publizieren k&ouml;nnen." -<em>Julian Reichelt, Vorsitzender der BILD Chefredaktionen</em></p><br /><p>Unterst&uuml;tze uns dabei, f&uuml;r eines der gr&ouml;&szlig;ten Medienportale Europas, ein schlankes und einfach zu bedienendes Content Management System von Grund auf neu zu entwerfen.</p><br /><p>Dazu setzen wir auf neueste Technologien wie React.js/Redux, Draft.js und Material Design. Im Backend verwenden wir Java 8 mit Spring-Boot und MongoDB Enterprise. Das Ganze lassen wir verdockert in einem Kubernetes Cluster laufen.</p><br /><p><strong>Unser Angebot</strong></p><br /><p>Wir geben unseren Entwicklern den Freiraum, selbstverantwortlich an der Weiterentwicklung unserer Produkte mit zu arbeiten und so Produktentscheidungen aktiv beeinflussen zu k&ouml;nnen.</p><br /><p>Wir investieren in unsere Mitarbeiter mit Schulungen und Trainings und profitieren dabei von unseren Partnerschaften mit Microsoft, Amazon und Apple. Dar&uuml;ber hinaus entsenden wir Kollegen gerne zu internationalen Konferenzen, um verschiedenste Themen und Fachbereiche intern abdecken zu k&ouml;nnen. (Google I/O, AWS Summits, Apple WWDC, etc.)</p><br /><p>Ein reiches Seminarangebot im Bereich der Softskills, spannende Konzernaktivit&auml;ten, betriebliche Altersvorsorge und Unterst&uuml;tzung f&uuml;r Familien stehen den Mitarbeitern parallel zur Verf&uuml;gung.</p><br /><p>Wir bieten unseren Mitarbeitern eine angemessene Bezahlung, ein j&auml;hrliches Bonussystem und ein attraktives Aktienbeteiligungsprogramm. Dazu erhalten die Angestellten neben Getr&auml;nken und Obst, freie Mittagskost in einer der besten Kantinen der Stadt.</p><br /><p>Die Arbeitspl&auml;tze sind hochmodern und werden mit hochwertiger Apple Hardware ausgestattet.</p><br /><p>Wer Lust auf ein spannendes Projekt, mit der Sicherheit eines Gro&szlig;konzernes im R&uuml;cken, anst&auml;ndiger Bezahlung und guten Fortbildungsm&ouml;glichkeiten im Herzen von Berlin hat, ist herzlich eingeladen sich zu bewerben.</p>','BILD GmbH & Co. KG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('714','Producer ( M/F )( Berlin, Helsinki, Dortmund ) at Zalando SE (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>The Opportunity</strong></p><br /><p>As a producer you will be instrumental in supporting the development team in achieving excellence in terms of delivering software. You will help facilitate the lean development process, track progress against Key Performance Indicators and will help organize and support planning and other daily activities as the team requires. You will be expected to showcase your excellent organisational, problem solving and analytic skills.</p><br /><p><strong>What we are looking for</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have 4-5 years of Software Project Management or Software Product Management experience, ideally in an e-commerce company</li><br /><li>You have sound knowledge and experience of managing and supporting software development using industry standard agile project management methodologies</li><br /><li>You have effectively managed features and requirements documents, project management documents and team roadmaps. &nbsp;You are able to bring a team together to craft a joined up plan, you understand risk mitigation and dependency management.</li><br /><li>Activities such as Backlog grooming, Task Prioritization, Roadmap Management, Daily Standups, User stories, Jira, Product/Feature Mockups and Processes diagrams are in your DNA</li><br /><li>You have strong communication skills and actively drive projects, breaking down complex problems into manageable, structured work packages. You effectively manage stakeholders and third party expectations and undertake periodic, appropriate reporting</li><br /><li>You have drive and are you motivativated to get things done. &nbsp;You lead by example, you talk data, you facilitate, you resolve, you negotiate and get things done</li><br /><li>You thrive in an international environment and are fluent in verbal and written English&nbsp;</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Your Responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You will be the organizational engine of your team, responsible for managing product releases and executing the end-to-end integration plan</li><br /><li>Your main focus will be on non-core-engineering tasks to enable successful end-to-end delivery and operation. &nbsp;You will be expected to manage your team&rsquo;s external project dependencies, external deliverables and roadmaps</li><br /><li>You will refine requirements from Business KPIs, features and user stories</li><br /><li>Your special focus will be on ensuring all end-to-end delivery tasks are completed for a successful product release</li><br /><li>You will be part of an engineering team and you will play &nbsp;key role in facilitating the team to take them forward. On a day-to-day basis, you will work very closely with the team and will facilitate taking decisions as a unit</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What you can expect from us</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Autonomy and trust to deliver using agile techniques in an entrepreneurial environment</li><br /><li>A career development path developed jointly with you with potential for developing breadth and depth in skill set</li><br /><li>A unique corporate culture where results are what matters, all within a relaxed office environment</li><br /><li>A highly motivated international team of colleagues who will both inspire and support you</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Want to join us? Then go ahead and apply!</strong></p><br /><p>If you need guidance or have any questions about our recruiting and hiring processes, please contact recruiter Manjuri Sinha at manjuri.sinha@zalando.de</p>','Zalando SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('715','Senior Software Developer (Java Backend) - High Performance Import at idealo internet GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<ul><br /><li>You develop in an agile team spring-based, high-parallelized, distributed applications for the controlling and monitoring of the high-load offer data import of the idealo platform</li><br /><li>You evaluate current trends, technologies and frameworks in the area of big data and streaming</li><br /><li>You keep track of the technical and functional coherences of the idealo platform even beyond your team and recognize dependencies</li><br /><li>You gather a variety of metrics and monitor the running systems on the base of KPI&rsquo;s</li><br /><li>The team benefits from your extensive knowledge of the relevant technologies and to the software developing process</li><br /></ul>','idealo internet GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('716','Kotlin Developer (f/m) at techdev Solutions GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>techdev Solutions is an independent partner for sophisticated IT projects. For our customers we develop individually tailored software solutions, implement them and refine existing systems.</p><br /><p>This vacancy is based in <strong>Berlin</strong></p><br /><p>As part of our team, you will work on improving all aspects of the development lifcycle. <strong>Here''s what you can expect:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>a hell of a lot of fun</li><br /><li>a dynamic, entrepreneurial and friendly working environment with a team that will coach you and bolster you up in every situations</li><br /><li>flexible structure and flat hierarchies</li><br /><li>independent work and development of your competencies from day one with an exceptionally steep learning curve</li><br /><li>fascinating projects across various industries</li><br /><li>cutting edge technologies, latest and greatest tools and space to&nbsp;tinker with both</li><br /></ul>','techdev Solutions GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('717','Senior Frontend Engineer (f/m) - Marketplace platform at DaWanda GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<strong><em>How we work</em></strong><br /><br />Our Product Engineering department is composed of passionate Software and QA Engineers, Product Managers, UX/UI Designers, Data Analysts and BI Experts structured in full stack vertical teams. We believe in the empowerment of individuals and we use Agile methodologies to let the team set quarterly objectives, in accordance with the company vision.&nbsp;We manage our own fleet of servers, deploying our services inside Docker containers. Besides, we develop our features in small incremental steps, with a workflow based on GitHub pull requests. We want our code to be well tested and we continuously integrate with Travis CI.&nbsp;The scale of our operations is a sweet spot between the freedom and the agility of a startup and the challenges of a big company.<br /><br /><strong><em>What we are looking for</em></strong><br /><br />Our marketplace platform was built over the years by dozens of skilled&nbsp;engineers and we are looking for experienced Frontend Engineers (f/m) who have&nbsp;worked on large web platforms to keep evolving it.<br />You will be working with one of our teams, collaborating with UX/UI&nbsp;Designers and Backend Engineers in the development of new features on&nbsp;our marketplace.<br /><br />Do you want to help us in migrating our clientside architecture to new&nbsp;technologies like React to make our platform faster and easier to&nbsp;develop, test and extend?&nbsp;We are looking for passionate and skilled people to join our engineering team and&nbsp;are glad to have you on board&nbsp;as a <strong>Frontend Engineer</strong><strong>&nbsp;(f/m)!</strong><br /><br /><br /><br /><p><strong>Your Responsibilities:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Work in a flat hierarchy international team (our office language is English)</li><br /><li>Write elegant and performant code that is easy to maintain</li><br /><li>Develop your code well-tested and improve tests and code continuously</li><br /><li>You deploy to our production cluster with over 100 million monthly page impressions on a daily basis</li><br /><li>Agile development and modern project management following the Scrum approach</li><br /><li>Ensure, restructure and maintain code for scalability</li><br /></ul>','DaWanda GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('718','FRONTEND/UX DEVELOPER (M/F) IN BERLIN at tridion digital solutions GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>tridion digital solutions</strong> is a provider of HR software. Our unique, constantly growing network and our strong brand give us access to interesting and dynamic startups in Germany.<br><strong>tridion digital solutions</strong> is an HR operations and BPOutsourcer with a long history and strong market position. To support us in changing the world, thinking crazy thoughts and developing the next generation of HR software we are looking for:</p><br /><p><strong>FRONTEND/UX DEVELOPER (M/F) IN BERLIN</strong></p><br /><p><strong>YOUR CHALLENG</strong>E</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Professional work experience in IT development and project management</li><br /><li>Be part of an amazing cloudbased HRSolution and a great team of technical experts</li><br /><li>Flat hierachies with space for your own ideas in a dynamic, dedicated and motivating environment</li><br /><li>A fun workplace right in the heart of Berlin</li><br /><li>Challenges which let you grow day by day</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>YOUR SKILLS</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have 3 years work experience in JavaScript</li><br /><li>You worked with backbone.js or angular.js and know the architecture</li><br /><li>You have very good skill in HTML 5</li><br /><li>(Optional) You understanding Chai, Mocha, TDD and BDD and have strong attitude to testing</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>YOUR TASKS</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You are responsible for developing innovative HR solutions on Backbone.js</li><br /><li>You improve the frontend with HTML 5</li><br /><li>You de ine and run javascript unit tests (QUnit)</li><br /><li>You research and are happy to learn new technologies that will improve our product and development flow</li><br /></ul><br /><p>You want to move things, be part of a professional and passionate team?<br>You hate bureaucracy and like to do things your way? Perfect!<br>Then send your CV to notjustajob@hrlab.de</p>','tridion digital solutions GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('719','Senior Java Backend - Engineer with AWS experience (m/f) at WeltN24 GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><em>Our goal is to become the leading multimedia news corporation for high quality journalism in Germany and an essential part of achieving this goal is to work with the best developers. Are you a passionate backend developer that can think outside of the box? Are you interested in working in an agile environment? If the answer is yes then we are looking for you to strengthen our international cross-functional teams.&nbsp;</em><strong><br><br><br>Your challenge</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Help us to establish the future of digital journalism at the WELT</li><br /><li>Continuous delivery of highly available services and API&acute;s for our mobile App</li><br /><li>Help us to stay ahead of the market by evaluating and using the latest technologies</li><br /><li>Identifying new services for our mobile applications</li><br /><li>Continuous review and improvement of our strategy as well as your skills</li><br /><li>Development of high quality, low maintenance software</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>Your profile</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>A skilled Java backend developer with DevOps experience and a minimum of three years experience</li><br /><li>Test-driven development of server components</li><br /><li>Excellent knowledge of OO &amp; functional programming</li><br /><li>Familiarity with Java, Spring, AWS, Docker, Gradle, Git, Jenkins and automation, you use TDD and BDD by heart</li><br /><li>Experience with Scala, Go, Terraform and different database systems is an advantage</li><br /><li>Besides your focus as a backend developer you would like to extend your Android knowledge with Kotlin and RxAndroid</li><br /><li>A self-starter willing to take the initiative and proactively remove impediments</li><br /><li>You appreciate sharing your knowledge in backend development with other team members</li><br /><li>The ability to think analytically and communicate well with non technical people</li><br /><li>Results oriented with the ability to work both independently and within a team</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What we offer<br></strong><br>You will be given the opportunity to deploy your current strengths and gain additional ones. In an agile and highly qualified team, you will work on the newest media technologies in a modern office in the heart of Berlin. A variety of seminars and workshops give you the opportunity to develop your specialized skill-set and your knowledge of comprehensive issues. Besides that, various conferences and Tech Talks as well as our regular exchange with subsidiaries of Axel Springer (e.g. Zanox, idealo, KaufDa and Immonet) provide an opportunity to build a valuable network.</p><br /><p>Moreover: You will have flexible working hours and above average number of vacation days, and a generous subsidy in our four on-site restaurants every day. Furthermore, a MacBook Pro with Apple Cinema Display, which can also be used privately, will be placed at your disposal.<br><br><br></p><br /><p><strong>Contact<br></strong><br>Questions regarding this position (reference number 015700059) will be answered gladly by:Stefanie Neckel; stefanie.neckel@weltn24.de</p><br /><p><strong>To all recruitment agencies:</strong></p><br /><p>We, and our employees, do not accept unsolicited agency candidate profiles for this position. We will not be responsible for any applications related to unsolicited candidate profiles.<br><br><br>WELTN24 emphasizes equal opportunities. We welcome the applications of people with disabilities, whose integration is an important matter to us.</p>','WeltN24 GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('720','Administrator Vertriebssysteme (m/w) at Berlin-Chemie AG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Administrator Vertriebssysteme (m/w)</strong></p><br /><br /><p>Die BERLIN-CHEMIE AG ist ein international expandierendes, forschendes Pharmaunternehmen der italienischen MENARINI-GRUPPE. Hochwirksame innovative Pr&auml;parate, ein professionelles Marketing und die intensive Zusammenarbeit mit &Auml;rzten und Patienten sind die Grundlage unseres Erfolges. M&ouml;chten Sie durch Ihre Leistung mit uns gemeinsam auf Erfolgskurs gehen?</p><br /><p><strong>Fachbereich</strong> Sales Controlling<br><strong>Karriere-Level</strong> Berufserfahrene<br><strong>Befristung</strong> unbefristet<br><strong>Standort</strong> Berlin<br>Einstieg ab sofort<br>Arbeitszeit Vollzeit</p><br /><br /><p><strong>Ihre Aufgaben</strong></p><br /><p>Als Administrator Vertriebssysteme(m/w) sind Sie ma&szlig;geblich f&uuml;r folgende Aufgabenbereiche verantwortlich:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Sicherstellung der Qualit&auml;t und Optimierung der Kundendatenbank und der zur Au&szlig;endienststeuerung eingesetzten IT-Systeme</li><br /><li>Programmierung, Administration und Organisation des CRM/ ETMS, von relationalen Datenbanken sowie des kontinuierlichen Kundenstammdatenabgleichs f&uuml;r regelm&auml;&szlig;ige und ad hoc Analysen</li><br /><li>Reporting von Au&szlig;endienstaktivit&auml;ten sowie diesbez&uuml;gliche Analysen</li><br /><li>Koordination komplexer, au&szlig;endienstbezogener IT-Vorg&auml;nge mit internen und externen Dienstleistern</li><br /><li>Selektion, Abgleich und Bereitstellung von Arztadressen f&uuml;r Mailings, Musterversand und Marktforschungsstudien</li><br /><li>Kontrolle der Musteranfragen und -bereitstellung innerhalb der Kundendatenbank</li><br /><li>Definition nationaler Anforderungen an das CRM/ETMS und enger Austausch mit Corporate Marketing und IT sowie Leitung, Begleitung und Beratung bei bereichs&uuml;bergreifenden Projekten im Themenkreis CRM/ETMS</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Sie arbeiten dabei unter anderem eng mit unserem Au&szlig;endienst-Team, den Abteilungen Marketing und Marktforschung sowie externen Ansprechpartnern zusammen.</p>','Berlin-Chemie AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('721','Software Engineer Ruby (f/m) - Marketplace platform at DaWanda GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong><em>How we work</em></strong> Our Product Engineering department is composed of passionate Software and QA Engineers, Product Managers, UX/UI Designers, Data Analysts and BI Experts structured in full stack vertical teams. We believe in the empowerment of individuals and we use Agile methodologies to let the team set quarterly objectives, in accordance with the company vision.&nbsp;We manage our own fleet of servers, deploying our services inside Docker containers. Besides, we develop our features in small incremental steps, with a workflow based on GitHub pull requests. We want our code to be well tested and we continuously integrate with Travis CI.&nbsp;The scale of our operations is a sweet spot between the freedom and the agility of a startup and the challenges of a big company.</p><br /><p>We are looking for passionate and skilled people to join our engineering team and&nbsp;are glad to have you on board&nbsp;as a<strong>&nbsp;Software Engineer Ruby</strong> (f/m)<strong>!</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Your Responsibilities:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Work in a flat hierarchy international team (our office language is English)</li><br /><li>Write elegant and performant code that is easy to maintain</li><br /><li>Develop your code well-tested and improve tests and code continuously</li><br /><li>You deploy to our production cluster with over 100 million monthly page impressions on a daily basis</li><br /><li>Agile development and modern project management following the Scrum approach</li><br /><li>Ensure, restructure and maintain code for scalability</li><br /></ul>','DaWanda GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('722','Software Entwickler Verifikation (m/w) at BIOTRONIK SE & Co. KG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Der Bereich Entwicklung Software entwickelt Software als Medizinprodukt f&uuml;r Serversysteme und f&uuml;r Ger&auml;te zur Implantation und Nachsorge aktiver Implantate sowie Softwaretools zur Unterst&uuml;tzung qualit&auml;tsrelevanter Prozesse.</p><br /><p>Ihre Aufgaben:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Entwicklung von Strategien und Frameworks f&uuml;r die Testautomatisierung sowie deren Integrations- und Performancetests</li><br /><li>&Uuml;berpr&uuml;fung von Anforderungsspezifikationen</li><br /><li>Erstellung, Automatisierung und Ausf&uuml;hrung von Performancetests f&uuml;r verteilte Systeme und mobile Anwendungen</li><br /><li>Analyse von Performance-Problemen sowie Durchf&uuml;hrung von Optimierungsma&szlig;nahmen</li><br /></ul>','BIOTRONIK SE & Co. KG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('723','Linux System Administrator (m/w) at NATIVE INSTRUMENTS GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>DEINE ROLLE</strong><br> Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung unseres Systems &amp; IT-Teams am Standort Berlin suchen wir zum n&auml;chstm&ouml;glichen Zeitpunkt einen Linux System Administrator (w/m). In dieser Position bist du f&uuml;r die Administration verschiedenster geographisch getrennter Netzwerk- und Serverstrukturen zust&auml;ndig. Die Administration der verschiedenen Systeme findet zentral vom Headquarter in Berlin aus statt.</p><br /><br /><p>DEINE Aufgaben</p><br /><br /><ul><br /><li>Betreuung und Pflege unserer Netzwerk- und Serverinfrastruktur im Regelbetrieb</li><br /><li>Stetige Optimierung bereits bestehender Strukturen und kritisches Hinterfragen, ob diese noch zeitgem&auml;&szlig; sind</li><br /><li>Monitoring bestehender Systeme, Identifikation und L&ouml;sung von Problemen und Risiken mit Kollegen aus dem 2nd und 3rd Level Support</li><br /><li>Sicherstellung der zuverl&auml;ssigen Sicherung und Archivierung von Daten</li><br /><li>Dokumentation der internen und externen IT Best Practices sowie von standardisierten Arbeitsabfolgen</li><br /></ul>','NATIVE INSTRUMENTS GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('724','Senior Software Engineer (f/m) at eBay (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Looking for a company that inspires passion, courage and inventiveness, where you will be part of the team shaping the future of global commerce? Want to shape how millions of people buy, sell, connect, and share globally? If you&rsquo;re interested in joining a purpose driven community that is dedicated to creating a daring and inclusive workplace, join eBay &ndash; a company you can be proud to be a part of.<br> <br> We are a fast growing, fast paced group that is constantly changing and innovating. Today we are building out our platform to become the premier content engineering solution within eBay.<br> <br> In order to achieve these lofty goals, we need a senior developer to lead the definition and coding of our platform&rsquo;s CI, CD, and clustering tools. The person who fills this role will work with quality assurance team on automating testing processes. Important requirements for this position include strong team collaboration, creativity, and contribution to the platform&rsquo;s full-stack codebase.</p><br /><p>&nbsp; To strengthen our team at the gates of Berlin we are hiring a <strong>Senior Software Engineer (f/m)</strong><br> <strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Ownership of the platform&rsquo;s automation and QA components.</li><br /><li>Push regular improvements to the platform''s full-stack codebase.</li><br /><li>Work with architects, engineers, and QA and operations teams to design and develop strategic and tactical solutions</li><br /><li>Design, develop, and test features and functions delivered via applications and services</li><br /><li>Collaborate with peers and seniors both within your team and across the organization</li><br /><li>Apply automated testing and other engineering methodologies on all the code you deliver</li><br /><li>Constantly improve quality: refactoring code, proposing new solutions and updating processes.</li><br /><li>Pair with team members and collaborate with remote teams to share knowledge and exchange constant feedback</li><br /><li>Work across our entire stack and infrastructure, including APIs, enterprise distributed systems, services and tools</li><br /><li>Tune, support and monitor applications</li><br /><li>Promote the best Agile practices, supporting and mentoring other teams in improving their technical skills and processes.</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br> <strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>5+ years of strong software development experience, preferably in high volume online organization.</li><br /><li>Strong interest in building out code-based solutions for scaling distributed multi-server systems. Experience with Kubernetes is a big plus.</li><br /><li>Experience with automated testing. It&rsquo;s an added bonus if you''ve built CI/CD workflows in the past.</li><br /><li>Experience with with Java, Ruby, Python, or any other OO language.</li><br /><li>Hands-on experience with SQL and No-SQL databases</li><br /><li>Flexible, adaptable, and able to autonomously handle multiple tasks in an international, dynamic, fast-paced, iterative development environment with short turnaround times.</li><br /><li>Self-motivated, passionate for technology, and strong driver for results and continual improvement.</li><br /><li>Great teammate - work well independently and in multi-group cross-discipline environment</li><br /><li>BS/MS CS degree or equivalent</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br> <strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Sysadmin - You have experience scaling applications, using open source tools for automating builds, testing deployments, and orchestration of services.</li><br /><li>Polyglot - You are confident working on a range of languages and can quickly adapt to new ones. You like contributing to quickly changing platforms in addition to well established technology stacks. You&rsquo;re eager to learn new tools and technologies and bring the same to the team.</li><br /><li>Architect - You choose the right tool for the job at hand. You know when the easiest solution is best and when it&rsquo;s time to rethink the existing approach. You have strong working experience building out PaaS and SaaS solutions.</li><br /><li>Agile - You&rsquo;ll help us inspect and adapt our processes &ndash; taking the best bits of XP, Lean, Scrum and Kanban. You will contribute to the agile transformation of eBay leading by example, offering workshops, and contributing to internal open source projects.</li><br /><li>Communicator - Very good English language skills. Some German would be a plus!</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br> <strong>What do we offer?</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Rewarding technical challenges - Building solutions for advertising and marketing teams requires solving difficult technical problems: scaling to deliver content globally, handling complex datasets and workflows, enabling non-technical users with self-service access to their content, and iterating quickly while providing the best customer experience. This isn&rsquo;t just another CMS-based project, our team is creating a platform to scale within the eBay ecosystem.</li><br /><li>Wonderful, bright offices - A great campus just outside of Berlin with fitness center, table soccer, beach volleyball, basketball, bike rental, coffee-bar, excellent canteen and shuttle-service. Work in a global environment with numerous career development opportunities.</li><br /><li>Great company culture - We have a culture of mutual respect and high expectations of others, dynamic team, passion for e-commerce, professionalism and a good sense of humor.</li><br /><li>Flexible working environment - Flexible working hours and generous holiday.</li><br /><li>Competitive salary and generous benefits.</li><br /></ul>','eBay');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('725','Salesforce Architect - Senior Developer (f/m) at Delivery Hero AG (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Delivery Hero</strong>&nbsp;is building the next generation global online food ordering platform. Our awesome international team already operates in over 40&nbsp;countries worldwide. We feature an environment with feedback exchange throughout the company from people who are genuine, ambitious and fun. We are looking for passionate and smart people to join us on our mission. Our ideal candidate will be enthusiastic, innovative, and good at &ldquo;getting things done&ldquo;.&nbsp;Play an active role in our future. An exciting job opportunity in the heart of Berlin is waiting for you.</p><br /><p><strong>Your Mission:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Design, develop Salesforce components using apex code, visual force pages, SFDC APIs</li><br /><li>Work cross-functionally with other engineering teams, such as product development and Interface development</li><br /><li>Conduct code reviews and establish code best practices to ensure that code quality is at the highest level possible</li><br /><li>Ensure team skills development and help with recruiting new team members</li><br /><li>People management experience a plus</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Your Heroic Skills:</strong></p><br /><p>We need someone with sound technical and functional knowledge of Salesforce.com technologies and architecture: Visualforce, SOAP/REST based web services, Salesforce.com Mobile, Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, Standard/Custom Objects, Workflows, Approvals, Email Templates, Validation Rules, Reports, Dashboards, Apex Classes and Controllers, Apex Triggers</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Clear and up to date knowledge of code-based and configurative possibilities in Salesforce, at least across Sales and Service Cloud</li><br /><li>Deep understanding of key Salesforce architectural concepts (e.g. pros and cons of object models, API concepts, concurrent actions and governor limits) and how they influence design</li><br /><li>Security models and techniques within the salesforce.com environment</li><br /><li>Experience in Database modeling, jquery, JSON, JSP, XML, HTML, JavaScript</li><br /><li>Utilizing Change sets, Github, etc. for migrating objects/metadata from one (development/sandbox) organization to another (Sandbox or production)</li><br /><li>Using ANT scripts and creating packages</li><br /><li>Experience in importing and exporting data in Salesforce.com</li><br /><li>3-5 years&rsquo; work experience in Salesforce development projects and deep familiarity with Salesforce platform</li><br /><li>Good knowledge of Apex, VisualForce, Javascript, OOP concepts</li><br /><li>SFDC certification is highly desired (DEV 401, ADM 201)</li><br /><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, MIS or relevant subject</li><br /><li>Ability to code and unit test programs / objects</li><br /><li>Experience working in a multi-team environment a plus</li><br /><li>Prior people management experience in the services industry a plus</li><br /><li>Experience working with agile development methodologies</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>We offer you:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Challenges</li><br /><li>International working atmosphere and cross-cultural teams</li><br /><li>Goal oriented environment&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Flexible working hours</li><br /><li>Great career opportunities</li><br /><li>Safety of a large company: pension scheme and stability</li><br /><li>Nice work environment and English as working language&nbsp;</li><br /><li>For applicants from abroad: relocation package and German lessons</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Have we caught your attention?</strong>&nbsp;Then please send us your application including cover letter, CV, salary expectations and earliest starting date. We&rsquo;re looking forward to your application!&nbsp;</p>','Delivery Hero AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('726','Datenbankpezialist/-in PostgreSQL at foo - financial engineering (Berlin, Germany)','<ul><br /><li>Wartung, Monitoring und Optimierung der gesamten PostgreSQL-Landschaft</li><br /><li>Review von SQL und Liquibase Changesets</li><br /><li>Optimierung komplexer SQL-Anfragen (auch im Team)</li><br /><li>Erstellung von Bash- und PHP-Skipten</li><br /><li>Datenbanktests mit pgTap</li><br /><li>Datenbankdeployment mit liquibase</li><br /></ul>','foo - financial engineering');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('727','Full Stack Engineer - PHP and System Engineer at Ocono (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Full Stack Engineer Software Architecture is about balance: The balance between perfect and functional, between technological needs and business requirements, between efforts and returns. We are searching for a very experience Full Stack Engineer to join our newly established Architecture Team to keep that balance in our high traffic environment. We understand a Full Stack Engineer as somebody who is an extremely experienced software engineer combined with several years of professional experience in system administration. We&rsquo;re looking for an enthusiastic go-getter who is just as comfortable designing high level applications as digging into the details of our infrastructure. Does that sound like you?<br><br>These will be your environment and tasks in our team:<br><br></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You will work in an high traffic environment (&gt; 3 million requests / hour)&nbsp;</li><br /><li>You dedicate yourself to building scalable architecture as well as hands-on coding&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Create redundancy in our systems with clustering, sharding or replication strategies and being responsible for its availability</li><br /><li>You will develop RESTful backend services and build stable and elegant web applications</li><br /><li>You will be a part of a very agile, short cycle development with continuous integration, in a dynamic start-up environment, where it is always interesting. &nbsp;</li><br /><li>You will elaborate technical concepts and integrate your own ideas and visions into the product</li><br /><li>You would work in an international team and feel comfortable working in English or German</li><br /></ul>','Ocono');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('728','Lead Frontend Developer (React Native) at Inkitt (Berlin, Germany)','<p>We have developed an algorithm that can predict best sellers, making the dreams of thousands of aspiring authors come true who haven&rsquo;t had the chance before. Join Us for building the future of publishing!</p><br /><p><strong>We:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Are building the future of publishing</li><br /><li>Have developed an algorithm that can predict best sellers, making the publication dreams of thousands of aspiring authors come true</li><br /><li>Love data and numbers</li><br /><li>Are based in the center of the beautiful capital Berlin</li><br /><li>Do everything to make our users happy</li><br /><li>Work long, hard, and smart</li><br /><li>Work from Mon-Sat (Saturdays on our own ideas/projects)</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Role:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You will mostly build features for our React Native iOS and Android App, which are featured by Apple and Google internationally</li><br /><li>You will mostly work with React Native, Redux, Realm</li><br /><li>You will also maintain our website, which is build with React, AngularJS, and Webpack</li><br /><li>Spend Saturdays on ideas/projects you come up with yourself</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Do you want to build the next successful global product?</p><br /><p>Please send us an application with your updated Resume, Cover Letter, and Preferred Start Date with the subject line "Stack Overflow: Lead Frontend Developer" at hiring@inkitt.com to get in touch.</p>','Inkitt');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('729','Site Reliability Engineer at LiveIntent (Berlin, Germany)','<p>As a <strong>Site Reliability Engineer</strong>, you&rsquo;ll work in an agile environment with talented, cross-functional teams to design, deploy and operate products that satisfy customer needs and drive company growth. Our technology stack runs on a Linux foundation and includesScala Play, NodeJS, Ruby on Rails, kinesis, lambda, DynamoDB and PostgreSQL on AWS. You will help promote good system design and operations practices and gain valuable experience simultaneously. Furthermore you will be responsible for the providing a rock solid infrastructure setup while working closely with the developers.</p><br /><p>The role will involve a mix of Linux system administration and security. Nominal IT duties may arise on an ad hoc basis.&nbsp;</p><br /><p><strong>What </strong><strong>we offer:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Private office in a shared working environment at WeWork</li><br /><li>Located very central location at Potsdamer Platz next to Tiergarten</li><br /><li>Talented group of people to work with</li><br /><li>Playstation for after work fun</li><br /><li>A friendly international team</li><br /><li>Subsidized gym membership</li><br /><li>Free beer tap</li><br /></ul>','LiveIntent');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('730','Senior-Frontend-Developer (in Start-Up) (m/w) at Patientus GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Was Dich bei uns erwartet:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Du pflegst unsere aktuellen Plattformen</li><br /><li>Von Anfang an dabei: Du entwickelst unsere neuen Releases (Version 2.0/Gr&uuml;ne Wiese)</li><br /><li>Bei uns findest Du den Freiraum, Deine eigenen Ideen und neue Technologien umzusetzen</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Unser Angebot an Dich</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Regelm&auml;&szlig;ige, individuelle Coachings und klare Zielsetzungen</li><br /><li>Workshops und Teamevents</li><br /><li>Flache Hierarchien und kurze Entscheidungswege</li><br /><li>Ein starkes und motiviertes Team, das sich auf neue Kollegen freut</li><br /><li>Einmaliger Start-Up Spirit mit solider Finanzierung</li><br /><li>Wir sorgen immer f&uuml;r gen&uuml;gend Getr&auml;nke, Nervennahrung und Obst</li><br /><li>Top-Netzwerk (zu Burda geh&ouml;ren Unternehmen wie XING, CLIQZ (Mozilla), HolidayCheck etc.)</li><br /></ul>','Patientus GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('731','R&D Engineer (Virtual Reality, AR, 3D vector math, C++) at Zalando SE (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>The Opportunity</strong></p><br /><p>Zalando&rsquo;s mission is to become the world&rsquo;s leading platform for connecting fashion with people. This goal requires a massive expansion of our business functions. We will serve a wider range of customers in different ways, build new technologies to support our platform architecture and continue to innovate as we expand.</p><br /><p>Zalando&rsquo;s Innovation R&amp;D Team focuses on strategic technical research supporting Zalando&rsquo;s product vision. Research areas include 3D scanning, soft body physics simulation, and computer graphics (AR and VR). The small team consists of multi-focused computer scientists and researchers.&nbsp;<br><br><strong>What We''re Looking For </strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Ph.D./M.S. in Computer Science, Mathematics or related engineering field</li><br /><li>4+ years of relevant industry or academic experience</li><br /><li>Mastery of C++ and one garbage collected language</li><br /><li>Familiarity with 3D vector math (matrix and quaternion algebra, calculating intersections of geometric primitives, etc.)</li><br /><li>You can quickly prototype an application and have sufficient knowledge about front-end frameworks, databases, and mobile platforms</li><br /><li>Strong Research &amp; Development experience</li><br /><li>Team player with the ability to work in a collaborative environment</li><br /><li>Creative, resourceful, and innovative problem solver</li><br /><li>Strong written and verbal communication skills in English</li><br /><li>Experience with Linux and Amazon Web Services (desired)</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Your Responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Driving and contributing to projects around various technological challenges (e.g. 3D scanning, soft body physics simulation, and computer graphics (AR, and VR))</li><br /><li>Give vital impulses to the R&amp;D team&rsquo;s decision making process</li><br /><li>Solve some of the most challenging technological challenges of our time while working in a team towards achieving a common goal as efficiently as possible</li><br /><li>Identify and share your knowledge of state-of-the-art technologies, related scientific research, as well as related developments in the startup and open source scene</li><br /><li>Contribute to &nbsp;the architecture and coding best practices for the R&amp;D team&rsquo;s systems</li><br /><li>Represent Zalando at conferences and meetups, give technical talks and help to recruit great technical talent</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>What You Can Expect From Us</strong><br><br><strong>Community</strong>. Tech culture of trust and empowerment, open source commitment, meetups, game nights, +100 internal technical and fun guilds, tech talks, product demos, Coderdojos, parties and events.<br><br><strong>Perks.</strong> Competitive salary, 40% Zalando shopping discount, discounts from external partners, public transport discounts, relocation assistance for internationals, free drinks and fruits, hardware of your choice.<br><br><strong>Development.</strong> Tour of Mastery, extensive onboarding, personal branding support, opportunity to attend and speak at conferences and meetups, and encouragement to publish work.<br><br><strong>Work Environment.</strong> Self-organized, autonomous teams and flexible working hours.<br><br><strong>Scale. Unparalleled levels of data and opportunities.</strong><br><br> <br><br><strong>About Zalando</strong><br><br>Zalando is Europe''s leading online fashion platform, doing business in 15 markets. Delivering first-class shopping experiences to our +15 million customers requires moving fast - with microservices, Agile processes &amp; autonomous teams - and using cutting edge, open source technologies. We are passionate about what we do and have fun while doing it. And we are willing to experiment and make mistakes: It''s how we grow.<br><br>Want to join us? Then go ahead and apply!</p>','Zalando SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('732','Lead Engineer (Java/Scala) - connect houses, cars and people. at Scout24 (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Scout24 operates leading digital classifieds platforms in Germany and other selected European countries. The main operations under the umbrella brand Scout24 are the digital marketplaces ImmobilienScout24 and AutoScout24. ImmobilienScout24 is the leading digital real estate classifieds platform in Germany, based on consumer traffic and time spent as well as customer numbers and listings. AutoScout24 is a leading automotive digital classifieds platform in Europe, in terms of unique monthly visitors and listings. Scout24&rsquo;s digital marketplaces are empowering people to realize their property and car-owning dreams simply, efficiently and stress-free. For more information, please visit: <a href="http://www.scout24.com" rel="nofollow">www.scout24.com</a>.</p><br /><p><strong>Lead Engineer (f/m)</strong></p><br /><p>Berlin, Full Time</p><br /><p>Are you passionate about sharing your knowledge? Do you like guiding people and people follow your lead?</p><br /><p>We are looking for someone who is passionate about bringing her knowledge of good reactive microservice architecture into the team. As a full member of the team you are working with cutting-edge technologies and lead one of the most influential and impactful engineering projects in Germany.</p><br /><p><strong>What we need from you:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Lead the technical journey of the team</li><br /><li>Be the expert for the architecture of our existing and future microservices</li><br /><li>Build applications in the AWS cloud</li><br /><li>Understand the business and product and help the team to find good technical answers to our product strategy</li><br /><li>&ldquo;You build it, you run it&rdquo; &ndash; DevOps mentality, take over responsibility for your team&rsquo;s applications</li><br /><li>Connect with the rest of the company to influence the platform architecture</li><br /><li>Practice Extreme Programming (pair programming, TDD, CleanCode)</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>What we need you to bring:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>More than 5 years experience or equivalent in the relevant fields</li><br /><li>Excellent knowledge of JVM based microservices in a cloud environment</li><br /><li>Sound knowledge in Java and the Spring eco system</li><br /><li>Knowledge of Scala and Play</li><br /><li>Knowledge of JavaScript frameworks like Angular JS or React.js/Redux</li><br /><li>Experience with relational and non-relational databases</li><br /></ul>','Scout24');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('733','Team Manager - Test Automation / QA at Webtrekk GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Your Responsibilities:</strong></p><br /><p>In this role, you will be leading a cross functional agile team of around 8 to 10 software engineers (Frontend-, Backend- and QA Engineers) which is mainly responsible for our Analytics platform.</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Manage and support your team to find best solutions for complex problems</li><br /><li>Ensure a close connection to Product Managers/stakeholders throughout the development process and guarantee an aligned strategy across all agile teams</li><br /><li>Lead discussions with the team and management to define best practices and approaches</li><br /><li>Set goals, objectives and priorities. Mentor team members, providing guidance and carrying out regular performance reviews</li><br /></ul>','Webtrekk GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('734','Scala Developer helping people find their dream homes at Scout24 (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>What we need from you:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Together with the team you will build great software solutions for our core customers, the real estate agents, based on proven and new technologies and integrate these solutions into our ecosystem.</li><br /><li>We work in a cross-functional team of developers, product owners, designers, business analysts and other stakeholders on product discovery</li><br /><li>We take responsibility for the whole stack: Build, test, deploy and operate all the necessary software, front-to-back</li><br /><li>We are living Agile: Frequent development cycles, Pair Programming, Continuous Delivery and DevOps</li><br /><li>We make time to learn about the newest technologies and apply them accordingly</li><br /><li>We celebrate our successes and learn from our failures</li><br /></ul>','Scout24');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('735','Java Full-Stack Engineer at TomTom (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Our team <strong>achieves more</strong> every day. So can you.</p><br /><p>We have been making navigation devices since 2002 and have been the market leader ever since.<br>And, we are not slowing down.<br><br>At TomTom you are able to develop Java from the UI down to the NoSQL data layer to deploy TomTom&rsquo;s Traffic and Navigation Services to the cloud. In addition you can improve the Testing and Integration strategies; essentially improving the DevOps capabilities of TomTom.<br><br><strong>Sound interesting?<br></strong>How about - <strong>Want to code the future?<br><br></strong><strong>Here&rsquo;s a little taste of your challenge</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Provide TomTom users with relevant and complex information at a glance by creating comprehensive algorithms</li><br /><li>Improve the user experience by generating new software components to deliver even more complete information</li><br /><li>Create highly scalable and high performing solutions, able to be running on all sorts of hardware</li><br /><li>Designing, implementing, testing and maintaining strategic feature development in J2EE projects.</li><br /><li>Improving the non-functional system characteristics of our backends and frontends, focusing on response times and uptime.</li><br /><li>Finding solutions to decrease time-to-market in tight collaboration with our DevOps team.</li><br /><li>Continuously improving our testing and integration strategies.</li><br /></ul>','TomTom');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('736','Software Engineer QA (m/w) Standort Berlin at REWE Digital GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong><strong>Das gibt es bei uns zu tun:</strong></strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Entwicklung von qualitativ hochwertigen E-Commerce Anwendungen</li><br /><li>Enge Zusammenarbeit in interdisziplin&auml;ren agilen Teams</li><br /><li>Eigenverantwortliches Arbeiten</li><br /><li>Etablierung von automatisierten Testverfahren</li><br /><li>Mitwirkung bei der Auswahl von Technologien</li><br /><li>Intensiver Wissensaustausch mit erfahrenen Kolleginnen und Kollegen</li><br /><li>Weiterentwicklung der pers&ouml;nlichen methodischen und technischen Exzellenz</li><br /></ul>','REWE Digital GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('737','Senior JavaScript Frontend Developer (m/f) - FinTech Application at smava GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Our Engineering department conceptualizes and realizes web services to guarantee a well performing smava ecosystem of financial products. We continuously develop our online loan comparison platform and implement new product features.</p><br /><p><strong>What we would like you to do:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Design &amp; development of reusable React.js based libraries/components for building various Product and Marketing frontends which can be A-B-tested and perform well under heavy load</li><br /><li>Follow a server-side rendering approach using node.js</li><br /><li>Work closely together with our Web Design and UI Team</li><br /><li>Create an amazing user experience</li><br /><li>Implement JavaScript based web tracking technologies and work also closely together with Analytics Team</li><br /><li>Agile Development</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>A current project:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Development of a state of the art landing page management system made of reusable components and based on React and Redux&nbsp;</li><br /></ul>','smava GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('738','Senior Backend Engineer at FreightHub GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>At FreightHub we are building the backbone of global trade and as part of the engineering team you are working on the core of that mission every day. Based on a cutting edge stack, consisting of MongoDB, NodeJs, TypeScript, React and Docker, our goal is to digitise&nbsp;this industry - one step more with every release.</p><br /><p>We define ourselves as a customer-centric team that enjoys working in a fast-paced environment. Daily releases, a high degree of test automation and constant application monitoring is our standard. We strive to optimize our workflows, architecture and infrastructure every month because we know that there is always room to improve.</p><br /><p>As backend engineer your tasks include:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>implementing and improving our multi modal routing algorithms that analyze millions of data points every day</li><br /><li>working with a multitude of different API&rsquo;s from our suppliers and ocean carriers to build solutions like automated freight booking or track and trace for ships, trucks and terminals;</li><br /><li>building the&nbsp;backend for a state of the art shipment and supply chain management solution</li><br /></ul>','FreightHub GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('739','Java Developer (m/f) at Project A (Berlin, Deutschland)','<ul><br /><li>Professional architecture and implementation of scalable platforms in an agile and motivated team</li><br /><li>Selection of appropriate technologies and architecture discussions within our team</li><br /><li>Programming clean, testable code</li><br /><li>Quality assurance through testing and code reviews</li><br /><li>Sharing of knowledge and willingness to learn</li><br /><li>Personal and professional development&nbsp;</li><br /></ul>','Project A');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('740','Professional Quality Engineer (w/m) at Deutsche Post E-POST Development GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><em><strong>Du willst besser werden, um Bester zu bleiben? Wir haben die Spielr&auml;ume f&uuml;r Vorw&auml;rtsdenker.</strong></em></p><br /><p>Die E-POST Development GmbH setzt die digitalen Produkte der Deutschen Post DHL Group in die Realit&auml;t um. Dazu wird in Berlin jeden Tag intensiv und in enger Zusammenarbeit mit dem Produktmanagement und dem UX-Team gecoded, released und gewartet. In der Friedrichshainer Oberbaum City arbeiten mutige, selbstorganisierte Teams, die neugierig auf neue Technologien sind und die an agile Entwicklungsmethoden und DevOps glauben.</p><br /><p><strong>Deine Kernaufgaben:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Qualit&auml;tssicherung der Anforderungen</li><br /><li>Umsetzung von Anforderungen in Akzeptanzkriterien und Tests</li><br /><li>entwicklungsbegleitendes Testdesign</li><br /><li>explorativem Testen</li><br /><li>Monitoring der Systeme in der Produktivumgebung.&nbsp;</li><br /></ul>','Deutsche Post E-POST Development GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('741','Senior Ruby On Rails Developer (f/m) in Berlin/Germany at MODOMOTO (Curated Shopping GmbH) (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Your&nbsp;Role:</strong></p><br /><p>As MODOMOTO expands internationally,&nbsp;your work will have immediate impact on our customers and the many departments of MODOMOTO that are serving them.&nbsp;You will be&nbsp;continuously&nbsp;developing and optimizing our system&nbsp;with the goal of making it&nbsp;more reliable, scalable, and performant as we grow.</p><br /><p>Therefore,&nbsp;we are looking for an experienced, passionate, and self-motivated engineer who will contribute to and influence the direction of this vision.</p><br /><p>To be successful in this role, you must be a quick learner and have excellent software development skills. You must also be a great communicator and excel at working in a highly collaborative and cross-functional environment. There is no shortage of opportunities to shape the future of our product.</p>','MODOMOTO (Curated Shopping GmbH)');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('742','C++ Engineers for plotting the quickest route at TomTom (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Our team <strong>achieves more </strong>every day. So can you.</p><br /><p>We have been making navigation products since 2004 and we are not slowing down.</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Would you like to bring the navigation experience to life for millions of TomTom users?</li><br /><li>Do you want to work on a solution which operates on all sorts of devices and platforms?</li><br /><li>Does clean and maintainable code make you smile more than a good coffee?</li><br /></ul><br /><p>In the TomTom office in Berlin we are working on the NavKit solution. This is the complex C++-coded algorithm used to plot the quickest route to any destination, on any device. As we are ushering into the (highly) automated driving, the TomTom NavKit is not only improving human-machine interaction, but also machine-to-machine instruction. Please see <a href="http://https//www.youtube.com/watch?v=FNW7DCEHwWo" rel="nofollow">this video</a> for more information. As a C++ Engineer you are involved in improving the routing, the guidance or the visualization of the Navigation solution.</p><br /><p><strong><strong>Here&rsquo;s a little taste of your challenge</strong></strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Produce great code<br>One minute you are discussing race conditions in multi-threaded code on a review, next you are in a whiteboard session with your colleagues drawing up the design of the next feature:&nbsp; you love what we refer to as &ldquo;perfect code&rdquo; that is recognized by your peers as being elegant and simple.</li><br /></ul><br /><ul><br /><li>Constantly develop yourself<br>Languages evolve, platforms change and so you learn. You grab the chances we offer to develop yourself because you are curious and like to work with the latest tools and techniques in an ever changing technological landscape.<br>&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Apply and expand knowledge with either:<br>&nbsp;- complex algorithms (most probable path)<br>&nbsp;- Digital Signal processing (GPS, Lidar)<br>&nbsp;- DevOps / Continuous Integration</li><br /></ul>','TomTom');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('743','Big Data Engineer (m/f) at mbr targeting GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>We are looking for a <strong>Big Data Engineer (m/f).</strong></p><br /><p><strong>YOU will &hellip;</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>work on extending our <strong>Hadoop</strong>-based Big Data infrastructure into the Petabyte region.</li><br /><li>extend our <strong>real-time stream-processing</strong> capabilities as new data comes in.</li><br /><li>help make the enormous amounts of data accessible to our machine learning team for <strong>ad-hoc queries</strong>.</li><br /><li>implement <strong>batch jobs</strong> from scratch and optimize existing ones.</li><br /><li>always adopt the latest technologies from the Hadoop ecosystem.</li><br /></ul>','mbr targeting GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('744','Senior DevOps Engineer in a fast growing ecommerce startup at Oberlo (Berlin, Germany)','<p>We are looking for a DevOps Engineer (m/f) who maintains, grows, and optimizes our development infrastructure. In this role, you work closely with our development team and enable them to ship faster and more securely.</p><br /><p><strong>Your responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Plan, build, maintain and evolve our AWS infrastructure</li><br /><li>Further develop the monitoring for all our services</li><br /><li>Scale our infrastructure with high availability in mind</li><br /><li>Work on the migration from our current PaaS to pure AWS solution</li><br /><li>Share your experience about building a reliable and immutable infrastructure by documenting processes and consulting your colleagues</li><br /></ul>','Oberlo');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('745','(Senior) Backend Developer (f/m) at eBay (Berlin, Germany)','eBay Kleinanzeigen is flexible and fast like a start-up yet we part of the global eBay Family. Our 70-people sized company includes all functions to run our business and do fast decision making. Members of our team value the entrepreneurial spirit, the &ldquo;can-do&rdquo; attitude and their mutual respect for each other&rsquo;s talent and contribution.<br><br /><br><br />We are one of the most-visited sites in Germany and growing at an amazing speed. Currently, we have about 20 million active ads and more than 15 million monthly unique users - more than half on mobile devices. All this traffic is powered by a set of Java 8/Spring applications and MySQL/Cassandra/Solr servers that serve tens of thousands request every second. We use Kanban for development and have up to 7 releases a day, thanks to our fully automated continuous delivery pipeline.<br><br /><br><br />Our development team is small yet excellent. Just over 20 highly motivated people build and maintain virtually all software components eBayK is made of - from backend to mobile apps. The current strategical focus of our efforts is the transformation of our platform into a polyglot Apache Kafka based microservice architecture - which means that now is the time to get creative, introduce new technologies, and leave your mark!<br><br /><br><br />To beef up our team we are hiring a Senior Backend Developer (f/m).<br><br /><br><br />Tasks and Responsibilities<br><br />Create the technology future of online classifieds in a scalable, clean way<br><br />Improve our applications and APIs to become better each day<br><br />Ensure code quality and maintainability by improving build and test systems<br><br />Be an interface between Product Management, Design, Business and Customers<br><br />Drive your own ideas for code and process improvement and achieve the next level together with the team<br><br />Be involved in the whole development lifecycle from planning through architecture to QA and deployment<br><br /><br><br />Requirements<br><br />Bachelor degree in computer science or equivalent education<br><br />Excellent programming skills in Java and the Spring Framework<br><br />Ideally knowledge of one or more other programming languages.<br><br />Strong know-how in object-oriented and/or functional design<br><br />Experience with Continuous Delivery, Jenkins-based build pipelines, Git and Maven<br><br />Experience with RDBMS and/or NoSQL (e.g. Cassandra, MongoDB, MySQL)<br><br />Ideally experience in the field of personalization.<br><br />Ideally knowledge of messagebroker systems (Kafka, RabbitMQ, ...)<br><br />Curiosity to learn new technologies (MySQL, Riak, MongoDB, Solr, ElasticSearch, Spring, Hadoop, Kafka, Cassandra, etc...)<br><br />Passion for beautiful, test-driven code and an eye for simplicity and pragmatism<br><br />Get up to speed with new systems and concepts easily<br><br />Believer in team work and a DevOps mindset<br><br /><br><br />What do we offer?An excellent working environment, flat hierarchies and challenging work with a diverse, highly skilled and humorous team<br><br />Competitive salary and great benefits e.g. conference &amp; education budget, company pension scheme, employee stock plans, mobile phone for business and personal use, latest Mac Book Pro, Notebook, PC you name it, home office possibilities etc.<br><br />International career opportunities throughout eBay Inc.<br><br />A great campus with free fitness center, basketball and beachvolleyball courts, table soccer, bike rental, coffee-bar, canteen and shuttle-service<br><br />Free coffee, tea, drinks, snacks, fruit throughout the day','eBay');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('746','Software Engineer Java (m/w) mit dem Blick für das Wesentliche at adesso AG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Wir suchen f&uuml;r die Standorte: Aachen, Berlin, Dortmund, Essen, Frankfurt/Main, Hamburg, Hannover, Istanbul, Jena, Karlsruhe, K&ouml;ln, M&uuml;nchen, N&uuml;rnberg, Stralsund, Stuttgart</p><br /><p><strong>IHRE ROLLE &ndash; DAS WARTET AUF SIE</strong><br>&gt;&gt;Sie &uuml;bernehmen mit Ihren Kollegen abwechslungsreiche T&auml;tigkeiten in technisch anspruchsvollen<br>Softwareprojekten aus dem gesamten Engineering-Prozess:<br>&bull; Anforderungsanalyse<br>&bull; fachlicher und technischer Systementwurf<br>&bull; Programmierung und Implementierung<br>&bull; Qualit&auml;tssicherung, Inbetriebnahme und Projektmanagement<br>&gt;&gt;Je nach Projektkontext nutzen Sie daf&uuml;r zeitgem&auml;&szlig;e Vorgehensweisen (bspw. Scrum, Kanban,<br>V-Modell oder Wasserfall) und zukunftsweisende Java/JavaScript-basierte Client/Server-Architekturen,<br>Microservices, Webanwendungen und Cloud-Technologien<br>&gt;&gt;Wir wissen - diese Aufgaben lassen sich nur mit offenem Erfahrungsaustausch, gegenseitiger<br>Unterst&uuml;tzung, kontinuierlicher Weiterbildung und gut ausgestattet erf&uuml;llen. Rund 650 Software<br>Engineers Java bei adesso und &uuml;ber 120 Schulungen &ndash; bspw. in Angular2 oder Spring Boot &ndash; sowie<br>Laptop und Smartphone ab Tag 1 warten auf Sie!</p>','adesso AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('747','Working Student, Internship or Thesis in Berlin - Java, Groovy, Grails at Zenjob (Berlin, Germany)','<p>For this position we are looking for someone who is passionate about backend&nbsp;development with Java/Groovy based on the Grails Framework. You will work on complex problems with cutting-edge technologies, in a tech-driven company.</p><br /><p><strong>If you join us, you&rsquo;ll:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>learn to develop scalable, restful applications for&nbsp;our B2B and B2C app</li><br /><li>learn to handle complex data and integrate with external business services</li><br /><li>have the option to write your thesis at Zenjob</li><br /><li>have the option to get a full-time contract when you graduate</li><br /><li>get a competitive salary</li><br /></ul>','Zenjob');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('748','Work at Zenjob in Berlin as a Groovy Backend Developer at Zenjob (Berlin, Germany)','<p>For this position we are looking for someone who is passionate about backend&nbsp;development with Java/Groovy based on the Grails Framework. You will work on complex problems with cutting-edge technologies, in a tech-driven company.</p><br /><p><strong>If you join us, you&rsquo;ll:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>develop scalable, restful applications for&nbsp;our B2B and B2C app</li><br /><li>handle complex data and integrate with external business services</li><br /><li>not only develop but also work out solutions to complex problems</li><br /></ul>','Zenjob');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('749','Senior QA Engineer (m/w) at Friendsurance (Alecto GmbH) (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>We are looking for an experienced <strong>QA Engineer</strong> to join an existing, cross functional team.&nbsp; In this role you will not only test code and features, but also guide the team in testing based on your test plans and approaches.&nbsp; This is a full time job with significant responsibility, working as part of a strong and growing team of software technologists on site in Berlin.</p><br /><br /><p><strong>Our Current Technologies, Tools, and Processes</strong></p><br /><br /><br /><ul><br /><li>Testing: Selenium, JUnit, Mockito</li><br /><li>Front End: react.js, TypeScript, Bulma, Redux</li><br /><li>Back End: Java, Spring, Hibernate, PostgreSQL</li><br /><li>Build and Deploy: Jenkins, Maven</li><br /><li>Infrastructure: AWS, Apache, Tomcat</li><br /><li>Process: Kanban, Retrospectives, JIRA, Confluence</li><br /></ul>','Friendsurance (Alecto GmbH)');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('750','Senior Data Scientist at Careem (Berlin, Germany)','<p>At Careem, our mission is to simplify the lives of people, initially through solutions that make transportation reliable, and over time, through disruptions in payments and logistics. In the process, we want to build an organization that inspires and become a world-class institution.<br><br>Careem is an innovative transportation service operational in 50+ cities. With 30% monthly growth, we are one of the fastest growing companies. Our recipe for success has been a team that thrives on challenges and is passionate about solving problems. We have attracted strong investors and are positioned on the cusp of significant scale.</p><br /><p><strong>ABOUT THE ROLE</strong></p><br /><p>As a Senior/Lead Data Scientist at Careem, you''ll be part of a team that''s leading the next wave of disruption at a whole new scale. You will be developing descriptive and predictive models as well as running extensive data analysis on million of customer transactions supported by a cutting edge data platform to unlock the big opportunities that simplify the lives of people through reliable transportation</p><br /><p>In the process, you will:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Answer complex analytic questions from big data sets to help Careem shape its products and services in a better way.</li><br /><li>Implement strong data pipelines for Machine Learning algorithms that will be used in production</li><br /><li>Implement large scale machine learning algorithm.</li><br /><li>Exploratory Data Analysis experience.</li><br /><li>Design, implement and support ETLs/ELTs to process terabytes of data each week.</li><br /><li>Embark on exploratory data analysis projects to achieve better understanding of phenomena as well as to discover untapped areas of growth and optimization.</li><br /><li>Help define and track the approperiate key metrics for specific projects.</li><br /><li>Design and run randomized controlled experiments, analyze the resulting data and communicate results with other teams,</li><br /><li>You will always challenge the status quo and continually investigate new data processing technologies and seek to ensure that we follow the industry best practices.</li><br /></ul><br /><p>The ideal candidate will have a passionate commitment to improving the lives of people, an insane focus on excellence and customer service, and a strong alignment with our core values: being bold, focused, agile and collaborative. &nbsp;</p>','Careem');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('751','Linux Server Administrator (m/f) at Visual Meta GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>As a &ldquo;Linux Server Administrator (m/f)&rdquo;, you will be working in an international team ensuring that our infrastructure and systems are working correctly and efficiently. Your main responsibilities will be configuring and monitoring our servers, implementing new technologies and solutions for our developers, resolving problems if they occur as well as performing day-to-day maintenance task. You&rsquo;ll need to be an autonomous, accountable, proactive, and solution-oriented person.</p>','Visual Meta GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('752','Lead Frontend Software Developer at 99chairs GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Do you love coding?&nbsp;Are you looking for the next step in your career?</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Then join our team of talented entrepreneurs right in the heart of the startup capital Berlin!</strong></p><br /><p>We believe in bringing happiness to people through interior designs that turn their homes and offices into places they love.</p><br /><p>In our pursuit to innovate living, we deliver exceptional &amp; affordable interior design solutions. Whether our clients are looking for design inspiration or want us to bring the ideas to life ourselves, we strive to make their experience as convenient &amp; inspirational as humanly possible &ndash; and, by the way, that&rsquo;s only where we start!</p><br /><p>We pride ourselves in the service we deliver. And, we value the people that turn our mission into a reality. Our dream is to create a work environment that connects great talent, gives them the freedom to do great stuff and continuously supports opportunities for learning and growth. At 99chairs, colleagues turn into friends and goals are accomplished as a team.</p>','99chairs GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('753','Senior Softwareentwickler Java (m/w) at BIOTRONIK SE & Co. KG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Der Bereich Entwicklung Software entwickelt Software als Medizinprodukt f&uuml;r Serversysteme und f&uuml;r Ger&auml;te zur Implantation und Nachsorge aktiver Implantate sowie Softwaretools zur Unterst&uuml;tzung qualit&auml;tsrelevanter Prozesse.</p><br /><p><strong>Ihre Aufgaben</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Entwicklung von medizinischer Software im Bereich mobiler Applikationen</li><br /><li>Konzeption und Umsetzung von State-of-the-Art Cloud L&ouml;sungen im medizinischen Umfeld</li><br /><li>Weiterentwicklung der BIOTRONIK Home Monitoring Plattform</li><br /></ul>','BIOTRONIK SE & Co. KG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('754','Senior Rails Developer at Funding Circle CE GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Funding Circle &nbsp;uses Ruby on Rails&nbsp;for many parts of the&nbsp;platform, and we are revamping the architecture to include Apache Kafka, Elasticsearch, Clojure and architectural style of&nbsp;stream processing, event sourcing and CQRS. The system includes Salesforce and Big Data technologies like Hadoop / Hive.</p><br /><p>We are a test driven team where English is the common language, but you''ll hear Russian, Spanish, French, Arabic, Romanian and Dutch in our Berlin office every day as well.</p><br /><p>This is a hands-on position, where you will design, test and implement core features of the platform, using Rails and other languages and frameworks in close cooperation with stakeholders, product management, and users of the system.</p><br /><p>We are part of the global Funding Circle team, so you''ll have colleagues in London and San Francisco, that are living at the cutting (and sometimes bleeding) edge with Clojure, Mesos, Docker and more.</p><br /><p>Responsibilities</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Develop new features for all stakeholders in a test driven manner.</li><br /><li>Improve usability and performance to scale to a large global deployment.</li><br /><li>Constantly improve the quality of code and processes.</li><br /><li>Mentor and lead other developers.</li><br /><li>Own core functionality of the platform across all systems.</li><br /></ul>','Funding Circle CE GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('755','Java Full-Stack Entwickler (m/w) at European IT Consultancy EITCO GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Du arbeitest in agilen Prozessen und interdisziplin&auml;ren Projektteams, bestehend aus 3 - 7 Personen von Anfang bis Ende an unseren Projekten. Hierbei liegt der Fokus auf der Neu- und Weiterentwicklung unserer Java Applikationen und Projekte und vor allem auf unserer Mission, die digitale Transformation des Public Sector voranzubringen.</p><br /><p>Hierbei triffst du auf folgende Technologien:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Java-SE und Java-Frameworks (z.B. Spring, Spring Boot)</li><br /><li>RESTful Web-Services mit JAX-RS (z.B. Jersey)</li><br /><li>ORM-Frameworks (z.B. JPA / Hibernate)</li><br /><li>Relationale DBMS</li><br /><li>Web-Frameworks (z.B. Vaadin, Angular, Smart GWT)</li><br /></ul>','European IT Consultancy EITCO GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('756','Lead Backend Developer at Tungsten Labs (Berlin, Germany)','<p>About Tungsten (tungstenapp.com)</p><p>We believe that everyone has the right to private and anonymous communication. With Tungsten we set out to build a secure messaging app for people who require advanced privacy and anonymity, while providing the ease of use of the apps that were used to use everyday.</p>As Lead Backend Developer you will be working with our cross-functional engineering team of 15+ people on the technical architecture and development of Tungsten, a high security messaging application. You will work with the product owner, designers and others on the team to map out and implement features, fix critical bugs, and continually improve the security, stability and usability of Tungsten.<p><br></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p> <ul> <li>Building and refining high-performance, scalable and secure systems  this means youll be essential in laying down the groundwork, building out infrastructure and developing product from start to finish.</li> <li>Designing and development elegant solutions to complex problems.</li> <li>Presenting your technical solutions to the rest of the team through design reviews, pair programming, tech talks and code reviews.</li> <li>Recognize architectural problem areas and determine ways to effectively resolve them.</li> </ul><br><p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><br><ul> <li>Very interesting work solving hard technology problems </li> <li>Use bleeding edge technologies</li> <li>Flat hierarchy, no middle management</li> <li>Above market compensation for high performers</li> <li>Training &amp; Development</li> <li>Performance Bonus</li> </ul>','Tungsten Labs');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('757','Senior Backend Developer (m/f) at reBuy reCommerce GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Support our shop team at creating a brilliant customer experience.</p><br /><p>Check out our tech website&nbsp;<a href="https://tech.rebuy.com/" rel="nofollow">tech.rebuy.com</a></p><br /><p><strong>Your quest:</strong></p><br /><p>At reBuy we are always trying to push our platform to the next iteration and you will be part of that daily routine. You will be working with the team to develop a new generation of our PHP7 powered webshop, while keeping complexity at a minimum. Improving the website responsiveness and keeping the server load to a low with the help of New Relic, Nagios and Graphite is an ongoing task. Nothing stops you at consuming our REST APIs, instead we encourage you to roll up your sleeves to improve the current APIs and share your knowledge to the team. Hunting mythical creatures called "bugs" in our high traffic application will give you a certain satisfaction.</p>','reBuy reCommerce GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('758','Softwareentwickler (w/m) für Embedded / Telefonie at AVM GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Dein Herz schl&auml;gt f&uuml;r Innovationen?</strong></p><br /><p>Perfekt, denn unser 11-k&ouml;pfiges Team sucht jemanden, der ebenso Spa&szlig; daran hat wie wir. Du sprudelst vor Ideen, programmierst hardwarenah und greifst beim Entwickeln auch gern mal zum L&ouml;tkolben? Hier hast Du die M&ouml;glichkeit, selbstst&auml;ndig und im Team an der Weiterentwicklung von marktf&uuml;hrenden Produkten zu arbeiten. Eine Reihe von Debugtools, von denen Du vielleicht selbst eines entwickeln wirst, unterst&uuml;tzen Dich bei der Arbeit. Und das ist Dein Aufgabenpaket:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Hardwarenahe Softwareentwicklung im Bereich von&nbsp;Telekommunikationsger&auml;ten&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Konzeption und Implementierung neuer Kommunikationsmodelle f&uuml;r den&nbsp;Bereich Telefonie&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Umsetzung von Entwicklungsaufgaben sowie Pflege und Erweiterung&nbsp;bestehender Softwaremodule im Bereich DECT/ULE&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Inbetriebnahme und Qualit&auml;tssicherung bei der Entwicklung neuer Hardware&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Entwicklungsbegleitende Dokumentation und enge Zusammenarbeit mit den&nbsp;Fachabteilungen</li><br /></ul>','AVM GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('759','Infrastructure & Cloud Engineer (m/f) at Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Overview:</strong></p><br /><p>In this position, you will be driving changes to culture, technology and championing the adoption of modern infrastructure software engineering practices that will challenge your skill and tap into your experiences. This includes demonstrating a path away from traditional infrastructure delivery model and towards an agile delivery model, through test driven development, configuration management and cloud adoption. The scope and purpose will include global, internal &amp; external cloud offered services for all regions. It also includes active participation in the direction and implementation of cloud platform services to deliver long-term strategies for business areas.</p><br /><p><strong>As a Infrastructure &amp; Cloud Engineer you will be responsible for working across multiple facets of the Springer Nature cloud platform. This role will span design, test and build of services for our customers.</strong></p><br /><p><strong>You will:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Be involved in the build and extend of our cloud services that span IAAS across the global datacenters as well as public cloud providers</li><br /><li>Interface with business units, architects, project managers and subject matter experts to understand and evaluate/translate business requirements into technical solutions</li><br /><li>Be challenged and expected to act as a change agent in our DevOps culture, principles and practices, using the creation &amp; maintenance of our repos and documentation</li><br /><li>Be a technical expert to help internal customers &amp; teams to consume standard cloud services, and be a core member of the ICE team and key contributor and subject matter expert</li><br /><li>Participate and assist in setting the long-term direction, roadmaps and standards for technical solutions, ensuring they align to the overall enterprise architecture</li><br /><li>Proactively appraise and modify current architecture to identify issues, research alternatives and determine improvements</li><br /></ul><br /><p>The patterns you&rsquo;ll work on to deliver will be tied back to business areas looking to use cloud capabilities to innovate, incubate, or graduate ideas into business value. This can include custom built solutions, &ldquo;--- as a service&rdquo; components.</p><br /><p>You will be responsible for participating in team and effort activities as needed, including pair programming, sprint planning, demos, and providing feedback on overall platform improvements.</p><br /><p>This includes working with the product owner, the team, and the internal community of engineers/developers. The demos will be focused on cloud technology updates to stakeholders and the team.</p><br /><p><strong>Training/Tools:</strong> You will be called on at times to assist our internal customers during their cloud adoption journey. This will be in part as a matrixed that will help identify, define and (in some cases) provide hands-on training for cloud service delivery as it pertains to software. You will also be expected to provide input for which toolset will best support our operating needs.</p>','Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('760','Senior Backend Java Developer E-Post (m/w) at Deutsche Post E-POST Development GmbH, Berlin (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><em><strong>Du willst besser werden, um Bester zu bleiben? Wir haben die Spielr&auml;ume f&uuml;r Vorw&auml;rtsdenker.</strong></em></p><br /><p>Die E-POST Development GmbH setzt die digitalen Produkte der Deutschen Post DHL Group in die Realit&auml;t um. Dazu wird in Berlin jeden Tag intensiv und in enger Zusammenarbeit mit dem Produktmanagement und dem UX-Team gecoded, released und gewartet. In der Friedrichshainer Oberbaum City arbeiten mutige, selbstorganisierte Teams, die neugierig auf neue Technologien sind und die an agile Entwicklungsmethoden und DevOps glauben.</p><br /><p><strong>Deine Kernaufgaben:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Weiterentwicklung und Wartung einer Vielzahl von Services mit unterschiedlichen Technologien und Architekturstilen</li><br /><li>Betrieb der eigenen und &uuml;bernommenen Applikationen in modernen Cloud-Umgebungen</li><br /><li>Unterst&uuml;tzung und Anleitung von Teamkollegen</li><br /></ul>','Deutsche Post E-POST Development GmbH, Berlin');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('761','Senior Frontend Engineer (m/f) at SumUp (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>About SumUp</strong></p><br /><p>The people of SumUp have brought the best way to accept card payments to 15 countries so far, but we won&rsquo;t stop there. Headquartered in London, SumUp''s major offices are in Berlin, Sofia and S&atilde;o Paulo. The Berlin office alone comprises more than 100 people from 24 countries. We recently launched a brand new contactless device, which makes paying by card easier than ever before.</p><br /><p><strong>Why work with us?</strong></p><br /><p>SumUp could be interesting for you as an engineer in part because we cover so many platforms: we have physical hardware (made right here in Berlin), our own proprietary payment processing platform, mobile apps on iOS and Android, SDKs and APIs supporting third-party integration, and of course (the main star, in this team''s humble opinion) a merchant-facing web app.</p><br /><p><strong>What we''re looking for</strong></p><br /><p>A web developer with Javascript expertise, who will be able to contribute to and benefit from our team''s ambition to improve our app, our code, and our technical abilities every day.</p><br /><p>To us, fullstack means you are comfortable working with the machine on all the levels most meaningful for web today: you''re familiar with Node, you''re comfortable with Unix as it relates to your work, you''re familiar with developing frontend apps in JavaScript, as well as making them look decent with HTML/(S)CSS based on specs provided by designers.</p><br /><p>This position is frontend heavy in its day-to-day responsibilities, but requires a thorough knowledge of the full stack to operate efficiently.</p><br /><p><strong>You''ll fit in perfectly to our team if:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You not only love coding, but also take the time to reflect on the benefits and drawbacks of your tools, be they frameworks, languages, or processes.</li><br /><li>You strive for clean code, but also know how to make your "shortcuts" easy to delete in a crunch.</li><br /><li>You know what to test, why to test it, and how to write flexible tests that won''t break with minor changes.</li><br /><li>You''re comfortable with Linux and know how to get things done on the command line, including on remote servers.</li><br /><li>You have experience with or interest in Functional Programming techniques.</li><br /><li>You''re not afraid to use Google or ask for help when something is beyond your grasp.</li><br /><li>You care about user interaction, usability, and of course &ndash; making the interface beautiful.</li><br /><li>In general, technology excites you and you strive to learn something on a daily basis!</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Our tech stack and projects</strong></p><br /><p><em>Dashboard:</em> A modern Angular 1.5 application helping merchants keep track of their revenue and manage their accounts. Our core features include sales analytics, a transaction overview, and account management. Right now we''re working on integrating AWS to power document upload and re-thinking our shop. Our Angular codebase uses a modern component approach and pure services supported by Jasmine unit tests. Apart from that, we heavily use JavaScript libraries like Lodash, Moment.js, and d3 and rely on Gulp and Webpack for our build and deployment tasks. Naturally, our codebase is in ES6.</p><br /><p><em>Website</em>: Our website uses Jekyll and is served by a Node server (using Koa, the spiritual successor to Express) that''s largely powered by a headless CMS (which we don''t maintain, win!). The Javascript is microscopic, organized into components, bundled with webpack, and uses jQuery and Lodash for convenience. We''re keen on SEO and optimizing the merchant''s very first impressions of our product.</p><br /><p><em>On our roadmap:</em> We''re always looking at what''s happening in the ever-changing web development space. We''re currently investigating React as an alternative to Angular, moving to Webpack 2, and adding a type system like Flow or TypeScript.</p><br /><p>The backend that powers SumUp is a constellation of microservices, mostly written in Ruby but with an increasing number powered by Node. If you''re interested in the nitty gritty of the complex domain of card payments, there''s space for you to expand your responsibilities to the backend.</p><br /><p><strong>Your impact at SumUp</strong></p><br /><p>You''ll shape some of the core experiences of our merchants: from their first impression on our website, to the web-based features that make them loyal to our platform.</p><br /><p>In the first few weeks, you''ll dive into the code and learn how to create clean, composable components in our codebase. You''ll use this knowledge to start developing and refining features. You''ll learn how we write tests, how we manage application state, and how we keep performance tip-top. You''ll also pitch in on our Jekyll site to enable sales and marketing to reach hundreds of thousands of visitors every month.</p><br /><p>In the first three months, you''ll develop major features that impact our merchant base. You''ll work closely with product and design departments to build features that are maintainable, usable, and beautiful. You''ll help us re-think problems we''ve solved before in a different way as requirements evolve. You''ll also leave your mark on the SumUp web experience by conducting A/B tests on the Jeykll site as well as during onboarding in the web app.</p><br /><p>In one year, you''ll have a wealth of knowledge about our complex problem domain, as well as its implications in the interface and in the backend &ndash; and how to manage it in a clean way. You''ll have launched numerous features on the Dashboard, as well as contributed to side projects and initiatives that gave you an opportunity to diversify your skills and learn something new.</p>','SumUp');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('762','DevOps Engineer (m/f) at reBuy reCommerce GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Be part of our team and shape reBuy''s platform.&nbsp;We are constantly looking for mind-alikes to take our platform&nbsp;where no man or robot has gone before. We have to confess there are no aliens, robots or rocket science involved in our day-to-day work. In the end it''s still work and unfortunately not a ball pit.</p><br /><p><strong>But:</strong> We do our best to create an enjoyable, focused and stress-free environment. We believe work should not be a burden but a cozy place to hang out. With regular cake breaks, fun, endeavour and challenges we enjoy tackling. An environment full of possibilities, exhausting them is your responsibility.</p><br /><p>Check out our tech website&nbsp;<a href="https://tech.rebuy.com/" rel="nofollow">tech.rebuy.com</a></p>','reBuy reCommerce GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('763','DevOps Engineer (m/f) at movingimage (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Would you like to&hellip; </strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>take a leading role in the planning, installation, integration, operation, optimization and continuous development of our IT-infrastructure?</li><br /><li>be a competent point of contact for the implementation of individual video management solutions for our customers?</li><br /><li>administer Linux- or BSD-based system landscapes?</li><br /><li>ensure the secure operation of our software development process by operating and improving the underlying infrastructure?</li><br /><li>contribute new creative ideas for the further development and enhancement of our network operation system?</li><br /><li>manage complex networks, and uphold and implement the highest safety requirements?</li><br /><li>prove your team skills as a member of an agile SCRUM-Team?</li><br /><li>experience how the principles of the Agile Methodology are implemented and lived within the whole organization?</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Are you able to&hellip;</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>show us that you have a fundamental understanding of network technologies and topologies?</li><br /><li>handle firewalls, load balancers, DNS, Web caches, monitoring systems, scripting?</li><br /><li>demonstrate us your experience with Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery?</li><br /><li>exhibit practical experience and/or theoretical knowledge in the following technologies: virtualization systems (VMware, Docker, LXC), Linux Systems, Nginx, Apache, MySQL, MongoDB, and CDN?</li><br /><li>demonstrate orchestration with systems such as Saltstack?</li><br /><li>bring experience with automated build-systems such as Jenkins, Bamboo, or TeamCity?</li><br /><li>demonstrate experience with cloud services such as Microsoft Azure, AWS, IBM or Heroku?</li><br /><li>show a strong understanding of Software as a Service?</li><br /><li>demonstrate experience in object oriented programming and languages such as Bash, Java, PHP, nodeJS or similar?</li><br /><li>be a team player who is able to carry out goal-oriented analysis and solve problems?</li><br /><li>communicate in German and English in a professional way?</li><br /><li>present at least a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in computer sciences (or some other significant degree) and relevant work experience of minimum three years?</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Do you feel addressed? We should get to know each other!</strong></p><br /><p><strong>We offer&hellip;</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>an exciting perspective, a wide range of tasks, constantly new challenges and a desire for thinking out-of-the-box as part of our corporate culture</li><br /><li>an open working environment that is characterized by teamwork and cross-functional cooperation and in which heart and humor are key figures</li><br /><li>freedom to introduce your own ideas and to take responsibility</li><br /><li>a modern selection of hardware devices</li><br /><li>a professional collaboration with Scrum Masters</li><br /><li>high-quality and scalable video asset management and video streaming solutions for enterprise customers</li><br /><li>free German and English courses</li><br /><li>a weekly breakfast</li><br /><li>Flexible work time with 30 days of holiday</li><br /><li>stable working environment</li><br /><li>Hack days twice a year</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Even more interested?</strong></p><br /><p>Submit your meaningful application documents noting your earliest available starting date through our online portal.</p><br /><p><a href="https://movingimage24gmbh.softgarden.io/applications/881007c3-f8dd-438f-9a79-8667de1ad46f?1&amp;isEditMode=false&amp;l=en" rel="nofollow">https://movingimage24gmbh.softgarden.io/applications/881007c3-f8dd-438f-9a79-8667de1ad46f?1&amp;isEditMode=false&amp;l=en</a></p><br /><p><strong>Your contact:</strong></p><br /><p>Mutabazi Nzirubusa| HR Recruiter</p><br /><p>MovingIMAGE24 GmbH</p><br /><p>Stralauer Allee 7 | 10245 Berlin</p><br /><p>You will find more about us on our website: <a href="http://www.movingimage.com" rel="nofollow"><strong>http://www.movingimage.com</strong></a></p>','movingimage');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('764','Network Engineer at Scout24 (Berlin, Germany)','<p>This is a key role within our Data Center Infrastructure team, with full technical responsibility and participation in technical projects. It is ideal for someone with good network skills who is technically strong and up to date and who wants to move in a position that allows decision making in technical areas. You will be involved in working with cutting-edge technologies and supporting some of the most influential and impactful engineering topics in Germany.</p><br /><p><strong>What we need from you:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Setup and operation of network components (switches, load balancers, firewalls, routers)</li><br /><li>Troubleshooting in the network environment</li><br /><li>Technical responsibility for availability of the network, consisting of switches, firewall and router, VPN gateway and load balancers</li><br /><li>Technical lead in projects, e.g. migration, moves, adds and changes</li><br /><li>Working on incident tickets in our incident management system</li><br /><li>Documentation of system information in a knowledge management tool</li><br /><li>Creation and implementation of viable network and security concepts</li><br /><li>Monitoring of network components and traffic</li><br /><li>Be the point of interaction with other parts of the support organization</li><br /><li>Participation in on-call duty</li><br /></ul>','Scout24');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('765','Senior Java Backend Developer (m/f) - FinTech Application at smava GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Our IT-Team takes care of the concept and realization of our platform of web services that consists of smava ecosystem of financial products. We continuously develop our online loan marketplace and implement new product features. Currently we are looking for a Java engineer who has strong experience in designing and building scalable high-performing applications.</p><br /><p><strong>Our backend tech stack:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Java 8</li><br /><li>Spring framework&nbsp; (DI, Security, Scheduling, Tx, Spring REST, Spring WS)</li><br /><li>Spring Cloud</li><br /><li>Messaging JMS / AMQP</li><br /><li>Maven</li><br /><li>PostgreSQL</li><br /></ul>','smava GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('766','Softwareentwickler Web (m/w) at CID GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Wir suchen Sie als <strong>Softwareentwickler Web (m/w)</strong>&nbsp;zum n&auml;chstm&ouml;glichen Zeitpunkt in Festanstellung an unseren Standorten in Freigericht, Biebergem&uuml;nd, Leipzig und Berlin.</p><br /><p><strong>Ihre Aufgaben</strong></p><br /><p>Als Softwareentwickler &uuml;bernehmen Sie Verantwortung f&uuml;r den komplexen Lebenszyklus unserer Softwareprodukte. Sie begleiten den gesamten Prozess von der Anforderungsanalyse und Konzepterstellung, &uuml;ber die Erstellung des Software-Designs, die Implementierung und Dokumentation sowie die Durchf&uuml;hrung von Softwaretests bis hin zur Inbetriebnahme der Systeme.</p>','CID GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('767','Java Developer (m/f) at reBuy reCommerce GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Payment-Provider &amp; Flow of Money... is there anything cooler?&nbsp;</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Integrate payment provider and connect third party software into our custom ERP system</li><br /><li>Build a flawless customer experience for all payment related processes</li><br /><li>Object oriented and test driven development using Java</li><br /><li>Maintain our existing software with the help of design patterns, complexity analysis and fault tolerance</li><br /><li>Develop solid unit and integration tests according to organizational standards</li><br /></ul>','reBuy reCommerce GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('768','Mobile Engineer (m/f) at Commerce 42 GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>&nbsp;<strong>YOUR ROLE</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You build new features and improve existing ones of our iOS and Android app</li><br /><li>You are an early part of our team and help shape our technical landscape and company culture right from the beginning</li><br /><li>You collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features</li><br /><li>You will work closely with our CTO, product manager, backend engineers and business development team</li><br /><li>You create unit test codes for robustness,&nbsp;usability, and general reliability</li><br /><li>You continuously discover, evaluate and implement new technologies to maximize development efficiency</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>YOUR PROFILE</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have experience in at least iOS (Swift/ Objective-C) or Android (Jave) development, preferably on both platforms</li><br /><li>You&nbsp;have published an app before or worked as part of a team that published one</li><br /><li>You have experience with third-party libraries and REST APIs</li><br /><li>Working knowledge of the general mobile landscape, architectures, trends, and emerging technologies</li><br /><li>You have&nbsp;an understanding of basic Security and Encryption principles</li><br /><li>Any other development experience is highly valued&nbsp;</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>WHAT WE OFFER</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>We value results not time, so no vacation policy</li><br /><li>Flat hierarchies with space for your own ideas and working directly with the CTO</li><br /><li>A crucial role in a highly motivated, talented team</li><br /><li>A stack of the most modern technologies</li><br /><li>Participation in hack days, technology brown-bags, hackathons</li><br /><li>Visa and relocation support</li><br /><li>A competitive remuneration, drinks, and snacks for free</li><br /><li>Office in the heart of Berlin''s trendy district Prenzlauer Berg; home office possible</li><br /><li>Potential for promotion to senior engineer</li><br /></ul><br /><p>What are you waiting for? Join us, grow with us and shape our company in the early stage. We look forward to receiving your online application!</p>','Commerce 42 GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('769','Data Engineer (m/f) at crealytics GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>To strengthen our international team in Berlin, we are offering a full-time position as</p><br /><p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data Engineer (m/f)</strong></p><br /><p>We enable leading international e-commerce companies drive performance in product advertising and paid search in more than 20 languages globally. In 2016, we generated over &euro;3 Billion in client revenue and are proud to count some of the Top 500 Worldwide Internet Retailers such as Footlocker, ASOS, and Harrods as clients. To support our clients from all over the world, we have offices in Berlin, London, Passau, and New York.</p><br /><p><strong>// Your responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>As Data Engineer, you will be responsible for fast, accurate, robust and scalable data-processing in our company</li><br /><li>You develop and deploy new features in an agile, test-driven environment in tandem with our team of data engineers, data scientists, software developers, and operations managers</li><br /><li>You build fault tolerant, self-healing, adaptive, and highly accurate data computational pipelines</li><br /><li>You optimize data transfer processes at the code, memory and architecture level</li><br /><li>You develop in an environment of micro-services and event-based architecture</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>// Your profile</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have either a bachelor''s degree&nbsp;with&nbsp;3+ years of work experience&nbsp;or a master&rsquo;s degree and 2+ year of work experience</li><br /><li>You have prior experience with a high level programming language like Ruby, Scala or Go</li><br /><li>You have the ability to quickly understand business requirements and transform them into data models</li><br /><li>You are experienced with Big Data related technologies like HDFS, Hive, Pig and Spark</li><br /><li>You have an aptitude to independently learn new technologies and you are passionate about data</li><br /><li>Prior experience with online marketing is a plus, e.g. Google AdWords, BingAds, Social Media Advertising or Universal Analytics</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>// What we offer</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Contribute to a unique software product that continues to excite us and our customers daily</li><br /><li>We offer challenges and encourage your personal development, offering individual external and internal training, conference visits, and regular appraisals</li><br /><li>You will take responsibility from day one and work in a great, agile team of diverse, smart, and passionate people from more than 20 nationalities</li><br /><li>We regularly provide you with deep insights into our business strategy and offer the chance to shape crealytics with your input and ideas</li><br /><li>You will benefit from our flexible working hours, our great relocation support, and depending on your tasks, we invite you to work in our Passau office from time to time &ndash; accommodation is provided!</li><br /></ul><br /><p>If you would like to become part of our success story and think you would make a great addition to our team, Ann-Marie Hennemuth will gladly receive your application with the subject line &ldquo;Data Engineer (m/f) SO&rdquo; in English at talents@crealytics.com. Please make sure to include your earliest possible starting date and your salary expectations.</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.crealytics.com" rel="nofollow">www.crealytics.com</a></p>','crealytics GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('770','IT-Architekt (m/w) at Deutsche Telekom AG (Berlin, Deutschland) (allows remote)','<p>Deine Aufgabe:</p><br /><p>Du tr&auml;gst Verantwortung f&uuml;r die Konzeption und das Design von IT-Architekturen f&uuml;r Industrieunternehmen und Beh&ouml;rden.</p><br /><p>Dein Tagesgesch&auml;ft:&nbsp;</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Du &uuml;bernimmst eine f&uuml;hrende Rolle dabei, auf der Basis agiler Modelle wie Design Thinking oder Scrum mit unseren Kunden zusammenzuarbeiten.</li><br /><li>Du nimmst entscheidenden Einfluss auf die Zusammenarbeit mit dem Betrieb, wenn es um die Cloud und moderne Deploymentmethoden wie DevOps geht.</li><br /><li>Du bist verantwortlich f&uuml;r die Analyse, Erstellung und Pr&auml;sentation von IT-Architekturl&ouml;sungen.</li><br /></ul>','Deutsche Telekom AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('771','Senior Mobile Developer (iOS) at FATMAP (Berlin, Germany)','<p>FATMAP is looking for a senior mobile developer based in Berlin&nbsp;</p><br /><p><strong>Technology is at the core of FATMAP.</strong></p><br /><p>FATMAP is&nbsp;building the best 3D mapping platform for outdoor adventure. To do that we believe that you need to have an incredible underlying technology stack, so we are investing in infrastructure that is built to be the best in class, right down to the smallest micro-service. We already have some serious technology powering FATMAP, however there is much more in the pipeline, and that''s where you come in!&nbsp;</p><br /><p><strong>What you''ll be working on</strong></p><br /><p>As a 3D mapping platform built to support outdoor adventure, we have an ever ambitious roadmap for mobile and we need your help to execute it.</p><br /><p>You''ll be building the FATMAP mobile app, and help us become the tool of choice for everyone''s outdoor adventures. This role is for an experienced mobile developer to come forward and lead the direction of the new native app, defining the technology stack, building rich media experiences, 3D integrations and a robust cross-platform framework. Working closely with Product and Design you&rsquo;ll have the opportunity to build new products from scratch across a wide range of projects, and help build the foundation of how the mobile app experiences are delivered. Performance is crucial, both in terms of the technology, but also your own.</p><br /><p>We&rsquo;re looking for awesome native developer who is very strong with iOS but can also define a cross-platform strategy. We work flexible hours and we all do some remote work, but we believe that the best results come from working side-by-side. If you&rsquo;re looking for a new opportunity and you&rsquo;re a skier / boarder / climber / runner / cyclist you&rsquo;ll feel right at home.</p><br /><p><strong>Our products:</strong></p><br /><p>Our apps:&nbsp;<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/fatmap-3d-backcountry-skiing-resort-trail-map/id934760071?mt=8" rel="nofollow">iOS</a>&nbsp;/&nbsp;<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.terrascope.fatmapski&amp;hl=en" rel="nofollow">Android</a></p><br /><p>Web maps:&nbsp;<a href="http://maps.fatmap.com/" rel="nofollow">http://maps.fatmap.com/</a></p>','FATMAP');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('772','Scrum Master (m/w) Standort Berlin at REWE Digital GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong><strong>Das gibt es bei uns zu tun:</strong></strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Laterale F&uuml;hrung und Unterst&uuml;tzung von agilen Produktentwicklungsteams</li><br /><li>Prozessverantwortung f&uuml;r die Anwendung agiler Methoden</li><br /><li>F&ouml;rderung von Teamentwicklung, Selbstorganisation und Verantwortungs&uuml;bernahme</li><br /><li>Gew&auml;hrleistung der kontinuierlichen Leistungsverbesserung des Teams</li><br /><li>Kommunikation mit Entwicklern, Stakeholdern und Vorst&auml;nden</li><br /><li>Herstellen von Transparenz &uuml;ber den Status der Teams</li><br /><li>Leben und Vertreten der agilen Werte in der Organisation</li><br /></ul>','REWE Digital GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('773','Junior Java C++ Software Engineer (m/f) Augmented Reality at MBition GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Reference number: MB003</strong></p><br /><p>MBition GmbH is a 100% subsidiary of Daimler and is located in Berlin. It combines the spirit and the flexibilityof a start-up with the resources and capabilities of a global active premium OEM.</p><br /><p>MBition GmbH concentrates on the series development of navigationsoftware, location-based services and User Experience / User Interface.</p><br /><p><strong>Tasks:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Developing and evaluating algorithms for vehicle positioning</li><br /><li>Developing drivable prototypes</li><br /><li>Deriving and evaluating map requirements</li><br /><li>Coordinating requirements with suppliers</li><br /><li>Integrating algorithms and processes into series products including series development</li><br /><li>Designing a suitable software architecture for use in series vehicles</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Your Qualification</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Education</strong>:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Communication Technology, or a comparable qualification</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Experience:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Software development using agile methods</li><br /><li>Comprehensive practical experience in C++ and/or Java</li><br /><li>Development of navigation systems and/or navigation apps</li><br /><li>Experience in the field of map databases (Here, OpenStreetMap) and map viewers</li><br /><li>Project experience gained in OEM telematics projects</li><br /><li>International/intercultural work experience desirable</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Language skills:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Excellent English proficiency; German proficiency is a plus</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Personal skills:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Excellent analytical skills and an independent, structured, and target-oriented approach to work</li><br /><li>Personal initiative, commitment, and resilience</li><br /><li>Well-developed communication and teamwork skills</li><br /><li>Enjoy working in international teams</li><br /><li>High degree of flexibilit</li><br /><li>Willingness to travel</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Interested?</strong></p><br /><p>We look forward to your application at <strong>mbox-mbition-recruitment@daimler.com</strong> along with following documents and information:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>&nbsp;CV and relevant certificates</li><br /><li>Job title and Reference number</li><br /><li>Salary expectation</li><br /><li>Earliest possible start date</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Got further queries? Reach out to us at <strong>mbox-mbition-recruitment@daimler.com</strong></p>','MBition GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('774','(Senior) Application Manager (m/w) at GfK (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Der Bereich Data &amp; Technology ist f&uuml;r den gesamten Lebenszyklus der globalen Marktforschungsanwendungen verantwortlich. Wir entwickeln die Anwendungen f&uuml;r unsere internen und externen Kunden in der klassischen Marktforschung und im Big Data-Umfeld. Zunehmende Bedeutung erhalten Anwendungen, die unterschiedliche Datenquellen und verschiedene Medien integrieren und dadurch neue Mehrwerte f&uuml;r unsere Kunden generieren.</p><br /><p>Als <strong>(Senior) Application Manager (m/w) </strong>sind Sie f&uuml;r eine der globalen Cross Media Anwendungen t&auml;tig. Sie arbeiten eng mit dem Entwicklungsteam, dem (Data) Operations Bereich sowie der internen IT Abteilung der GfK zusammen.</p><br /><p>Sie etablieren sich als gesuchter Ansprechpartner, der die Anwendungs-Suite und deren Zusammenspiel in der Datenverarbeitungskette durchdringt. Im t&auml;glichen Betrieb und Support k&ouml;nnen sie auch schwierige Problemstellungen l&ouml;sen. Dabei bringen Sie, falls erforderlich die unterschiedlichen Experten zusammen.</p><br /><p>Einfachere und regelm&auml;&szlig;ige T&auml;tigkeiten strukturieren sie und &uuml;bergeben diese an Near- oder Offshore.</p><br /><p>F&uuml;r ihre Aufgabe stehen ihnen moderne Tools und Technologien, sowie ein engagiertes und innovatives Team zur Verf&uuml;gung.</p><br /><p>Ihre Arbeitsinhalte lassen sich wie folgt skizzieren:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Applikationsbetrieb und -support der Application-Suite End2End</li><br /><li>Planen und Umsetzen von &Auml;nderungen an der zugrundliegenden Infrastruktur</li><br /><li>&Uuml;bernahme von Deployments / Optimieren der CI basierten Deploymentprozesse</li><br /><li>Optimieren des Montitoring / Alerting auch auf Applikationsebene</li><br /><li>Schnittstelle zwischen den Entwicklungsteams sowie dem (Data) Operations Bereich / Service Management</li><br /><li>Einarbeitung und Steuerung von Near- oder Offshore Mitarbeitern</li><br /></ul>','GfK');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('775','Application Developer - Logistics (m/f) at MYTOYS GROUP (Berlin, Germany)','<p>As an <strong>Application Developer - Logistics (m/f)</strong> you work autonomously in an international agile team. Within the framework of projects you develop and configure the company processes on our innovative ERP system (Oracle eBusiness Suite). In the course of your work you cooperate intensively with professional users, advise them, meet their requirements in a professional manner and receive direct feedback in a collegial atmosphere. You have a wide range of responsibilities which includes work in all stages of the software development process. You try out new methods, work with the latest Oracle technologies and expand your know-how in dialogue with other IT professionals.</p>','MYTOYS GROUP');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('776','Senior backend engineer for P2P marketplace at Croove GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>As Senior backend engineer you will be responsible for:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Taking operations responsibilities of our systems and services.</li><br /><li>Fostering and refactoring the existing APIs for our front-ends</li><br /><li>Building new systems to securely store sensitive data</li><br /></ul>','Croove GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('777','Senior Java C++ Software Engineer (m/f) 3D Map Rendering at MBition GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Reference number: MB007</strong></p><br /><p>MBition GmbH is a 100% subsidiary of Daimler and is located in Berlin. It combines the spirit and the flexibilityof a start-up with the resources and capabilities of a global active premium OEM.</p><br /><p>MBition GmbH concentrates on the series development of navigationsoftware, location-based services and User Experience / User Interface.</p><br /><p><strong>Tasks:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Concept drafting, series development and validation of current and future navigation products, with a focus on 3D map rendering for displaying state-of-the-art 3D models of cities</li><br /><li>Developing software architectures according to criteria such as relevance, scalability, performance, efficiency, robustness, and security</li><br /><li>Agile software development</li><br /><li>Deriving, evaluating and specifying requirements</li><br /><li>Managing and coordinating with external service providers and suppliers as part of the technical implementation of new product developments</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Your Qualification</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Education:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Degree in Computer Science, IT or Communication Technology or a comparable qualification</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Experience:&nbsp;</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Several years experience in software development using agile methods</li><br /><li>Solid knowledge of C++ and/or Java</li><br /><li>Practical experience in the development of navigation systems and/or navigation apps</li><br /><li>Experience in the field of map databases (Here, OpenStreetMap) and map viewers</li><br /><li>Project experience gained in OEM telematics projects</li><br /><li>International/intercultural work experience desirable</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Language skills:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Excellent proficiency in English; German proficiency is a plus</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Personal skills:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Excellent analytical skills and an independent, structured, and target-oriented approach to work</li><br /><li>Personal initiative, commitment, and resilience</li><br /><li>Well-developed communication and teamwork skills</li><br /><li>Enjoy working in international teams</li><br /><li>High degree of flexibility</li><br /><li>Willingness to travel</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Interested?</strong></p><br /><p>We look forward to your application at <strong>mbox-mbition-recruitment@daimler.com</strong> along with following documents and information:</p><br /><ul><br /><li>&nbsp;CV and relevant certificates</li><br /><li>Job title and Reference number</li><br /><li>Salary expectation</li><br /><li>Earliest possible start date</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Got further queries? Reach out to us at <strong>mbox-mbition-recruitment@daimler.com</strong></p>','MBition GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('778','Artificial Intelligence System & Solution Architect (m/w) at Deutsche Telekom AG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Sie&nbsp;sind Sie im Team mit Product Ownern, Entwicklern und weiteren Spezialisten verantwortlich daf&uuml;r Plattformen, Services und Produkte zu entwickeln, zu implementieren und zu testen, die sich K&uuml;nstliche Intelligenz zunutze machen, um Kundenbindung und Kundenzufriedenheit zu erh&ouml;hen</p><br /><p>Diese Plattformen, Services und Produkte werden l&auml;nder&uuml;bergreifend entwickelt und sollen in allen Produktbereichen eingesetzt werden, vor allem jedoch im Umfeld von Kundenservice, eCommerce/eSales und in der Bedienung und Vernetzung existierender Produkte. Dabei bewerten Sie die technische Realisierbarkeit, den Kundennutzen und gemeinsam mit den entsprechenden Experten die Wirtschaftlichkeit, und entwickeln ferner&nbsp; Ma&szlig;nahmen zur Verbesserungen oder Modifikationen bestehender Plattformen und Produkte.</p><br /><p>Und was noch?</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Erstellung von technischen Solution Designs und deren Abstimmung mit den jeweiligen Experten bezogen auf die Vorgaben einer Ziel-Architektur</li><br /><li>Analysieren, Bewerten und Ausw&auml;hlen von Technologien, L&ouml;sungen und Vendoren</li><br /><li>Zusammenarbeit und Koordination interner und externer Entwickler oder Offshore-Entwicklungsteams zusammen mit den verantwortlichen Product Ownern</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Interesse geweckt?&nbsp;Wir suche auch an den Standorten Bonn und Darmstadt. Hier gibt es weitere Infos:&nbsp;&nbsp;www.welove.ai</p>','Deutsche Telekom AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('779','Senior iOS Developer (m/f) - Berlin, Munich or Regensburg at intive-Kupferwerk GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Unterst&uuml;tze unser Team aus erfahrenen Entwicklern und professionellen Juniors! Wir legen unseren Fokus nicht nur auf "best apps" sondern auf ideale und ganzheitliche L&ouml;sungen. &Uuml;berzeuge dich davon.&nbsp;</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Deine Aufgaben</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Technische Konzeption, Entwicklung, Integration und Test nativer iOS-Apps</li><br /><li>Kommunikation mit den Ansprechpartnern unserer Kunden, z.B. f&uuml;r Anforderungsanalyse, L&ouml;sungs-Design und Problemsuche</li><br /><li>Mitarbeit bei der Konzeption von Angeboten</li><br /><li>Enge Zusammenarbeit mit Kollegen aus den Teams Quality Assurance &amp; Creative</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Was wir bieten</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Einen Job mit Zukunft in einer schnell wachsenden und innovativen Branche</li><br /><li>Begeisternde mobile Produkte f&uuml;r national als auch international f&uuml;hrende Kunden</li><br /><li>Anspruchsvolle Projekte im Bezug auf Usability, Design und Technologie</li><br /><li>Eine verantwortungsvolle Aufgabe mit Gestaltungsspielraum</li><br /><li>Zusammenarbeit mit einem kompetenten und motivierten Team</li><br /><li>Ein eigenes MacBook sowie ein Smartphone inkl. Mobilfunkvertrag werden dir zur beruflichen und privaten Nutzung zur Verf&uuml;gung gestellt</li><br /><li>Individuelle Weiterbildungs- und&nbsp;Entwicklungsm&ouml;glichkeiten</li><br /><li>Eine ausgewogene Work-Life-Balance</li><br /><li>Ein wettbewerbsf&auml;higes Gehalt</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Fakten</strong></p><br /><p>Unterst&uuml;tze unsere Teams ab sofort am Standort Regensburg, M&uuml;nchen oder Berlin. Bei regelm&auml;&szlig;igen Meetings triffst immer wieder auf Kollegen/Innen an beiden Standorten!</p><br /><p>Wir wollen Dich als festes Team-Mitglied und bieten dir daher eine unbefristete Vollzeit-Stelle an.&nbsp;</p>','intive-Kupferwerk GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('780','Senior Software Engineer, Recommendation & Personalization (Java, Big Data) at Zalando SE (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>THE OPPORTUNITY</strong><br><br>As a software engineer in the area of "Recommendation &amp; Personalization" you are working on Zalando state-of-the-art recommendation systems serving millions of customers with highly relevant and personalized content. You will be working with the newest technologies to build a SAAS component which can be fully leveraged within our Zalando platform.</p><br /><p><br>Your main challenges will include working with large amounts of data, deliver high-quality recommendation results and at the same time provide a low-latency, rock solid and auto-scaling production system. You will be part of an autonomous and highly ambitious team consisting of experienced software engineers and expert data scientists working on the cutting-edge every day.<br><br><br><strong>WHAT WE''RE LOOKING FOR</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have 4+ years of experience, working as a (Java or Scala) developer. A technical degree is a plus</li><br /><li>You have in-depth experience of working with data-driven recommendation solutions, including creating, implementing, and tuning recommendation engines</li><br /><li>You have worked with current Big Data technology (e.g. Hadoop/MapReduce)</li><br /><li>You are experienced in building and deploying large-scale, distributed data-driven systems in a cloud environment</li><br /><li>You are keen on collaborating closely with Data Scientists &amp; Data Analysts and have passion to solve algorithmic problems</li><br /><li>You have a keen interest in Data Mining &amp; Processing as well as applied Machine Learning</li><br /><li>You&rsquo;ve worked with NoSQL databases before (e.g. Cassandra, MongoDB) and ideally also have experience in search engines (Solr, Elasticsearch)</li><br /><li>You write well-structured and tested code in the spirit of Effective Java and Clean Code that easily scales to enterprise level</li><br /><li>You love to improve &amp; optimize software and to use new technologies</li><br /><li>Knowledge of near-realtime stream processing and/or message-driven architectures (e.g. Spark, Storm, Aerospike, Kafka) is a plus</li><br /><li>Experience with Cloud Computing platforms such as AWS is a plus</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You will be part of an agile and very experienced team that will further develop our recommender systems in short release cycles</li><br /><li>You will build and operate all services and stream-processed data infrastructure for low-latency personalized recommendations</li><br /><li>You will implement highly-scalable solutions with state-of-the-art-technologies together with your team</li><br /><li>You are ready to tweak and optimize our recommendations for various markets all across Europe for millions of customers</li><br /><li>You will transfer algorithmic prototypes to enterprise level, highly-scalable and fault-tolerant solutions using the right technology for the job</li><br /><li>You are collaborating with our data scientists to improve and extend our recommendation engine and other analytical customer experience solutions</li><br /><li>You will be part of a multi-cultural team with different native languages, skills and backgrounds</li><br /><li>Design, develop, deploy, operate and improve software solutions that impact millions of Zalando customers</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>WHAT YOU CAN EXPECT FROM US</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Community</strong>. Tech culture of trust and empowerment, <a href="https://github.com/zalando" rel="nofollow">open source commitment</a>, meetups, game nights, +100 internal technical and fun guilds, tech talks, product demos, Coderdojos, parties and events.</p><br /><p><strong>Perks.</strong> Competitive salary, 40% Zalando shopping discount, discounts from external partners, public transport discounts, relocation assistance for internationals, free drinks and fruits, hardware of your choice.</p><br /><p><strong>Development.</strong> Tour of Mastery, extensive onboarding, personal branding support, opportunity to attend and speak at conferences and meetups, and encouragement to publish work.</p><br /><p><strong>Work Environment.</strong> Self-organized, &nbsp;autonomous teams and flexible working hours.</p><br /><p><strong>Scale. Unparalleled levels of data and opportunities.</strong></p><br /><p><br><br><strong>WANT TO JOIN US? THEN GO AHEAD AND APPLY!</strong></p>','Zalando SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('781','(Senior) Ruby on Rails Engineer (m/f) for ad2games at ad2games (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Your Role:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You design, implement and deploy new products and features for our web scale applications</li><br /><li>You enjoy the freedom to work on cutting edge technologies and to explore new ones</li><br /><li>You work in an agile team using pairing, pull request based code reviews, automated testing and continuous integration</li><br /><li>You proactively pay attention to the scalability, performance and availability of our systems</li><br /><li>You take responsibility to ensure successful results in a data driven environment</li><br /><li>You work closely with product, business development, design and other stakeholders</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Our Requirements:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You bring 2+ years of working experience in web development and software engineering</li><br /><li>You have a very good understanding of systems engineering, scalability, algorithms and RoR</li><br /><li>You hold a degree in Computer Science or have equivalent working experience</li><br /><li>You are familiar with backend infrastructure technologies such as Linux, AWS, Continuous Integration/Delivery, Docker</li><br /><li>You speak very good English</li><br /><li>You show a disciplined approach when it comes to automated testing and quality assurance</li><br /><li>You have the agile mindset, drive and flexibility that is required in a startup environment</li><br /><li>You are a team player, good communicator and easy to work with</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br><strong>What do we offer?</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You become a part of a unique and fun company culture (<a href="https://vimeo.com/99734712" rel="nofollow"><strong>https://vimeo.com/99734712</strong></a>)</li><br /><li>You are part of our regular Hackdays where you work on what you are passionate about</li><br /><li>You profit from working with serial entrepreneurs who co-founded over 10 successful companies</li><br /><li>You work with a highly motivated and skilled team of top performers</li><br /><li>You get access to a well-established network in Berlin&rsquo;s start-up scene</li><br /><li>You have the opportunity to attend German classes and numerous events</li><br /><li>You enjoy a competitive remuneration package and much more</li><br /><li>You work in the start-up centre of Berlin-Mitte, the European Silicon Valley</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong><br>Interested? Then submit your CV along with links or demos of your work online.</strong></p>','ad2games');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('782','Sr. Software Engineer - Recommendation at eBay (Berlin, Germany)','eBay Kleinanzeigen is flexible and fast like a start-up yet we part of the global eBay Family. Our 70-people sized company includes all functions to run our business and do fast decision making. Members of our team value the entrepreneurial spirit, the &ldquo;can-do&rdquo; attitude and their mutual respect for each other&rsquo;s talent and contribution.<br><br /><br><br />We have one of the most-visited sites in Germany and are growing at an amazing speed. Currently, we have about 20 million active ads and more than 15 million monthly unique users &ndash; far more than half of them on mobile devices. All this traffic is powered by a set of Java 8/Spring applications and MySQL/Kafka/Cassandra/Elasticsearch servers that serve tens of thousands of requests every second. We use Kanban for development and have up to 10 releases a day, thanks to our fully automated continuous delivery pipeline.<br><br /><br><br />Our 25 people-sized development team is small yet excellent. We build and maintain virtually all software components eBay Kleinanzeigen is made of - from backend to mobile apps. Right now we&rsquo;re in the middle of a transformation towards a polyglot Apache Kafka based microservice architecture - which means that now is the time to get creative, introduce new technologies, and leave your mark!<br><br /><br><br />To beef up our team we are hiring a Senior Software Engineer - Recommendation / Personalization (f/m).<br><br /><br><br />Tasks and Responsibilities<br><br />Build scalable low-latency pipelines and components to handle large amounts of data<br><br />Generate high quality personalized content for our users<br><br />Be an interface between Product Management, Design, Business and Customers<br><br />Drive your own ideas for code and process improvement and achieve the next level together with the team<br><br />Be involved in the whole development lifecycle from planning through architecture to QA and deployment<br><br /><br><br />Requirements<br><br />Bachelor degree in computer science or equivalent education<br><br />Passion for beautiful, test-driven code and an eye for simplicity and pragmatism<br><br />Excellent programming skills in Java, knowledge of one or more other programming languages<br><br />Experience with data-driven personalization and recommendation solutions<br><br />Track record of working in high-throughput stream processing or micro-batch environments like Spark, Kafka Streams, Flink, Storm<br><br /><br><br />Beneficial<br><br />Strong know-how in object-oriented and/or functional design<br><br />Believer in teamwork and a DevOps mindset<br><br />Experience with RDBMS and/or NoSQL (e.g. Cassandra, MongoDB, MySQL)<br><br />Ideally knowledge of search engines (Elasticsearch, Solr) and Hadoop / MapReduce<br><br />Curiosity to learn new technologies<br><br /><br><br />What do we offer?<br><br />An excellent working environment, flat hierarchies and challenging work with a diverse, highly skilled and humorous team<br><br />Competitive salary and great benefits e.g. conference &amp; education budget, company pension scheme, employee stock plans, mobile phone for business and personal use, latest Mac Book Pro, Notebook, PC you name it, home office possibilities etc.<br><br />International career opportunities throughout eBay Inc.<br><br />A great campus with free fitness center, basketball and beachvolleyball courts, table soccer, bike rental, coffee-bar, canteen and shuttle-service<br><br />Free coffee, tea, drinks, snacks, fruit throughout the day','eBay');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('783','Java Engineer (m/f) w/ Android Experience in Berlin at SuitePad (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>We shape the hotel room of the future!</strong></p><br /><p>As the European market leader for in-room tablets more than 400 of the most renowned hotel chains worldwide trust us with their digital guest communication.&nbsp;For our office in Berlin, we are now looking for someone to help build out new device capabilities on our custom Android Tablets.</p><br /><p><strong>Our Playground:</strong></p><br /><p>The Android component of this role is not a typical Android engineering position. While we build and support several native Android apps, the meat of this role will focus on systems design and require dealing with ROMs, the Linux system, Android source code and Android private/hidden APIs.</p><br /><ul><br /><li>&nbsp;Work with a fleet of android devices and tablets running our custom ROMs and suite of native and hybrid (Cordova) android apps</li><br /><li>Our stack includes a few Cordova &ldquo;wrapped&rdquo; ember applications, with a backend SOA implemented in mostly Ruby and some Node.js</li><br /><li>While here, you will need to push the limits of our custom android tablets, discovering ways of doing things that aren&rsquo;t publicly documented and no other hardware makers are doing</li><br /><li>Help us explore how to expand our existing infrastructure into the IOT space as we prepare to design and launch new custom hardware</li><br /><li>Please note that day-to-day responsibilities will include various support tickets or tasks (20% of your time)</li><br /><li>No German language skills required</li><br /></ul>','SuitePad');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('784','Software Developer C++ (f/m) at NATIVE INSTRUMENTS GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>YOUR ROLE</strong><br> We are looking for an enthusiastic Software Developer (f/m) with a passion for music and NI products to help us evolve our MASCHINE, KOMPLETE, and TRAKTOR software. As a Software Developer (f/m) in a cross-functional scrum team you will iterate in two-week sprints. Based in Berlin, Kreuzberg, you will join an international, multicultural, and creative environment that supports individual growth and sharing knowledge.</p><br /><p>YOUR TASKS</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Build products that enable music enthusiasts, producers and performers to express themselves</li><br /><li>Write clean and maintainable code that functions on multiple platforms</li><br /><li>Learn from other experienced developers and work in an environment which supports individual growth</li><br /><li>Collaborate with other engineers, designers, and product owners to identify and solve challenging issues</li><br /><li>Demo your team results after each sprint to all other teams</li><br /><li>Hack with colleagues on your ideas in our quarterly hackathon week</li><br /><li>Work from our office in Berlin, Kreuzberg in a multicultural and creative environment</li><br /><li>Bring a high level of motivation and interest to the team</li><br /></ul>','NATIVE INSTRUMENTS GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('785','Professional Backend Java Developer E-Post (m/w) at Deutsche Post E-POST Development GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><em><strong>Du willst besser werden, um Bester zu bleiben? Wir haben die Spielr&auml;ume f&uuml;r Vorw&auml;rtsdenker.</strong></em></p><br /><p>Wir setzen mit der E-POST Development GmbH die digitalen Produkte der Deutschen Post DHL Group in die Realit&auml;t um. Dazu wird in Berlin jeden Tag intensiv und in enger Zusammenarbeit mit dem Produktmanagement und dem UX-Team gecoded, released und gewartet. In der Berliner Oberbaum City arbeiten mutige, selbstorganisierte Teams, die neugierig auf neue Technologien sind und die an agile Entwicklungsmethoden und DevOps glauben.</p><br /><p><strong>Deine Kernaufgaben</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Weiterentwicklung und Wartung einer Vielzahl von Services mit unterschiedlichen Technologien und Architekturstilen</li><br /><li>Betrieb der eigenen und &uuml;bernommenen Applikationen in modernen Cloud-Umgebungen</li><br /></ul>','Deutsche Post E-POST Development GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('786','Devops Engineer (f/m) at Wimdu GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Your Tasks:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Build, automate, and manage key parts of the global Wimdu production environment</li><br /><li>Help define a solid strategy for ensuring future growth of our platform and help with our migration to AWS</li><br /><li>Optimize existing systems and components for performance and stability</li><br /><li>Forge close relationships with development teams, and empower them to take ownership of their own parts of the infrastructure in a SOA environment</li><br /><li>Collaborate with developers and QA engineers on release processes, deployment and scaling</li><br /><li>Build and maintain core infrastructure components like monitoring services and automation recipes that our development teams can use</li><br /><li>Proactively monitor end-to-end system performance (client to database) to identify bottlenecks and potential failures, and help developers improve their code based on your analysis</li><br /><li>Help with maintaining our office infrastructure and lend an occasional hand to colleagues needing IT support</li><br /><li>Assume strong ownership for what you build - including being on-call for it</li><br /></ul>','Wimdu GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('787','Senior Software Engineer / Senior Developer Backend (m/f) at medneo GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Senior Software Engineer / Senior Developer Backend (m/f)</strong></p><br /><p>Experienced software developer for the healthcare sector</p><br /><p><strong>medneo | Radiology as a Service</strong></p><br /><p>medneo revolutionises diagnostic imaging &ndash; as the operator of diagnostic platforms in the inpatient and outpatient area. Instead of today&rsquo;s system of buying expensive medical equipment, customers buy from us clinical images &ndash; as a service. We call this &ldquo;Radiology as a Service&rdquo;. This means that we, as a company, handle all areas of the diagnostic process that are not one of a physician''s core competencies. As a dynamically expanding company &ndash; in Germany and internationally &ndash; we are continuously on the lookout for employees to implement our unique service and quality promise in a range of different roles for our customers and their patients.</p><br /><p><strong>Your tasks</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Personal responsibility from designing and implementing autonomous microservices</li><br /><li>Implementing a cloud-based solution using state of the art technologies in the area of scalable microservices, based on asynchronous messaging</li><br /><li>Joint acceptance of responsibility for architecture, development and operation of the system (you build it, you run it!)</li><br /><li>Proactive communication within and outside of your own development team</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>medneo offers</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>A modern technology environment to support the company&rsquo;s growth</li><br /><li>Opportunity to leave a footprint by building up the IT department together with the team in a young and growing company</li><br /><li>Personal development by growing together with the company</li><br /><li>Flexible working hours</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Employment: permanent full-time position</p><br /><p>Start: immediately</p><br /><p>Location: Berlin City center</p><br /><p><strong>Contact</strong></p><br /><p>We look forward to receiving your application via the &ldquo;Apply Now&rdquo; button.</p><br /><p>Your contact if you have any questions</p><br /><p>Personnel &amp; Academy</p><br /><p>Alessandro Di Dedda</p><br /><p>medneo GmbH | Hausvogteiplatz 12, 10117 Berlin</p><br /><p>Phone +49 (30) 814 501 700</p><br /><p>personnel@medneo.com</p><br /><p>www.medneo.com/en/career</p>','medneo GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('788','Senior Multi Skilled Software Engineer at Oliver Wyman Systems Engineering (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Fantastic opportunities are available in the Oliver Wyman Labs Systems Engineering team in our London and Berlin offices. You&rsquo;ll be working in smaller, more agile teams than usual. Our philosophy is to liberate our developers to do the best job they can with minimal interference. The position combines the roles of architect, lead developer and team lead. You&rsquo;ll be immersed in the business side of the work from the start of each project too, so you can shape it to meet the business requirements.&nbsp; Any success we have had is because of this development model, which we have been refining for almost 20 years, first as LShift, and now as the Systems Engineering team at OW Labs. We work across technologies, platforms, OS&rsquo;s and industries, which means you will be working on a wide range of projects and will gain a correspondingly wide range of experience, both technical and personal, as an engineer, a developer and as a leader.</p>','Oliver Wyman Systems Engineering');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('789','Systems Engineer Cyber Security (m/w) at BIOTRONIK SE & Co. KG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Der Bereich Entwicklung Software entwickelt Software als Medizinprodukt f&uuml;r Serversysteme und f&uuml;r Ger&auml;te zur Implantation und Nachsorge aktiver Implantate sowie Softwaretools zur Unterst&uuml;tzung qualit&auml;tsrelevanter Prozesse.</p><br /><p><strong>Ihre Aufgaben</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Analyse und Spezifikation von Produkten und Services hinsichtlich Cyber Security Anforderungen</li><br /><li>Konzeption und Gestaltung von Cyber Security L&ouml;sungen &uuml;ber den Produktlebenszyklus</li><br /><li>Methodenentwicklung hinsichtlich Cyber Investigation</li><br /><li>Definition und Durchf&uuml;hrung von Attack &amp; Penetration Testing auf Systemebene</li><br /></ul>','BIOTRONIK SE & Co. KG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('790','Senior Java/Scala Developer (m/f) at Springer Nature Germany (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>You may think of publishing as somewhat traditional. At Springer Nature we have ambitious plans and our IT group is what will drive our ambitions. We need talented people in every discipline, from Business Analysts and UX Designers to Software Developers and Platform Engineers to name just a few.</p><br /><p><strong>What&rsquo;s it actually like to work with us?</strong></p><br /><p>We might be a large global organisation with people all around the world, but our IT team operates more like a start-up; working in agile project teams. We strive to make the digital division a place where people and ideas thrive.</p><br /><ul><br /><li>New, diverse and growing international team</li><br /><li>Broad range of technologies</li><br /><li>Leading innovation at Springer Nature</li><br /><li>Small lean cross functional teams</li><br /><li>Choose your own tools (Hardware, OS, IDE, etc.)</li><br /><li>Relaxed and friendly environment</li><br /><li>Supportive organisational culture</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>About you:</strong></p><br /><p>Your are...</p><br /><ul><br /><li>Communicative and open to criticism</li><br /><li>A teamplayer, not a Ninja</li><br /><li>Embracing of change</li><br /><li>Always learning, not afraid to fail</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>So what do we offer?</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>A healthy work/life balance</li><br /><li>Interesting and challenging work</li><br /><li>A relaxed, positive environment</li><br /><li>Enthusiastic, supportive colleagues</li><br /><li>Further development to help you progress your career</li><br /><li>Flexible hours, a 37 hour week and 30 days annual leave</li><br /><li>Book discount of 15-40%</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Terms</strong></p><br /><p>Limitation: Permanent<br>Working Hours: Full-time&nbsp;<br>Company and Location: Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH, Berlin</p><br /><p><strong>Excited by the prospect of joining us? We are looking forward to your online application in English!</strong></p><br /><p>To find out more information about our organization please take a look at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.springer.com/" rel="nofollow">www.springer.com</a>&nbsp;and springernature.com.</p>','Springer Nature Germany');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('791','Comms Platform Developer (Full Stack/Java Development) at Scout24 (Berlin, Deutschland)','<ul><br /><li>Your number one responsibility &ndash; innovate and create.</li><br /><li>At its core, this is an early-stage program of work that essentially builds a communications platform capable of linking millions of people and data intelligently and meaningfully.&nbsp;</li><br /><li>Work across all platforms &ndash; you will be in a constant dialogue with our mobile team to think about solutions holistically.</li><br /><li>Project is backed as a core strategic program of work. Expect visibility and interaction with senior leaders in the company.</li><br /><li>Those who join this team will be deeply integrated across the Scout product family &ndash; this is not just about property. While we have initiated our effort in ImmoScout, our &ldquo;One Scout&rdquo; vision is now moving us into AutoScout.</li><br /><li>In addition to developing domain knowledge across the property and automotive industries, you will be thinking about leveraging B2C and C2C platform. We need people who can really think about solutions in multiple flows.</li><br /></ul>','Scout24');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('792','Senior Java/Scala Developer (f/m) at eBay (Berlin, Germany)','<p>With more than 2,6 million registered Users, MOTOR-TALK.de is the biggest German-speaking online community for automotive enthusiasts. It is part of mobile.de GmbH, which runs additional sites in Italy, Romania, Poland and France, featuring more than 40,000 merchants. With 1.4 million vehicles, mobile.de is the largest online vehicle trade site in Germany. The mobile.de GmbH employs 140 coworkers at Dreilinden just outside of Berlin and is a part of the eBay Group. This is an excellent opportunity to work for one of the most challenging product development organizations in eBay Germany.<br> <br> We''re searching for a professional individual to join our team in Berlin as <strong>Senior Developer (m/f) Java/Scala</strong>.<br> <br> The Dialogue/Advertising team deals with all technical tasks to integrate various premium partners (mostly of the automotive industry) on the pages of MOTOR-TALK.de. Underlying is a separation of the partner themed sites from the core sites. This means that the current MySQL setup will be replaced and the data is pulled via a REST-interface. The Techstack will change with this transition from MySQL, spring, Java8 to a play framework with Scala.<br> <br> <strong>Job responsibilities:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Drive the separation of the dialogue pages from the core platform for MOTOR-TALK.de</li><br /><li>Support managing the Advertising tech infrastructure on motortalk.de/mobile.de</li><br /><li>Own the entire development lifecycle from specification to deployment</li><br /><li>Be an active partner for Product management in order to provide the best value for stakeholders and our customers</li><br /><li>Innovate technology, process and product with your team</li><br /><li>Coaching junior developers</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Job requirements:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>4+ years&rsquo; experience as a Java/Scala developer with a deep understanding of the surrounding technology ecosystem</li><br /><li>Strong architecture and design experience</li><br /><li>You are an absolute pro in Java / MVC / Spring4</li><br /><li>You speak HTTP and REST like your mother tongue</li><br /><li>Solid understanding of up-to-date front-end technologies (Javascript, modern JS frameworks, CSS)</li><br /><li>Knowledge in MySQL / Hibernate / Linux is beneficial.</li><br /><li>You firmly believe in lean and agile development (Kanban / Scrum)</li><br /><li>You get up to speed with new systems and concepts quickly</li><br /><li>You understand that quality is not assured by a QA engineer, but by the team</li><br /><li>Proven excellence in analyzing, designing, implementing, running and maintaining large scale distributed scalable solutions for the Web</li><br /><li>Ability to plan strategically and execute in a result-oriented manner</li><br /><li>Ability to thrive in a cross-functional environment while juggling multiple responsibilities</li><br /><li>Passion for keeping up to date with the latest developments in the industry</li><br /><li>For you &ndash; Advertising/Marketing is a key to success and not a burden.</li><br /><li>Good communication skills, ability to explain technical decisions to colleagues at all levels and from all trades</li><br /><li>Excellent English language skills, German language skills not required, but a plus</li><br /></ul><br /><p><br> <strong>What we offer:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Dynamic, international teams with very skilled personalities, a passion for e-commerce, professionalism and a great sense of humor</li><br /><li>A competitive salary, great benefits and an excellent working environment</li><br /><li>Potential for career advancement in just about any line of business and the opportunities to work almost anywhere in the world within eBay Inc.</li><br /><li>Silicon Valley Amenities (iPhones and MacBooks, Ping-Pong and kicker tables, volleyball and basketball courts, free coffee and juice, tasty subsidized lunches, a nice forest for walking and thinking and a free on-campus gym with trainers)</li><br /></ul>','eBay');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('793','Heart and Soul Developer (m/w) at FinTech Group AG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Wir suchen zur Verst&auml;rkung unseres modernen Fintech-Teams in Berlin, Frankfurt am Main, Willich<br>und D&uuml;sseldorf ab sofort Entwickler, die mit viel Herzblut bei der Sache sind.</p>','FinTech Group AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('794','iOS Team Lead (f/m) at eBay (Berlin, Germany)','<strong>eBay Kleinanzeigen</strong> is the most-visited general classifieds proposition in Germany and growing at an amazing speed. Currently, about 17 million unique customers use our native apps, mobile website and website every month.<br><br /><br><br />We are managed like a start-up yet we are anchored in the global portfolio of eBay. Customer centricity and passion for our products is what helps us to develop great apps. Our agile environment, weekly usability tests, prototyping and cross-functional teams make our product better each day.<br><br />To make our team even more powerful we are hiring a <strong>Team Lead iOS Development (f/m)</strong>. As part of our mobile team you will be building and managing our app for iOS and power our amazing growth.<br><br /><br><br />If you are a believer in customer centric thinking, agile and lean software development, feel responsible for your product, enjoy working in cross functional teams, want to craft quality and not quantity and most importantly want to make an impact then get in touch with us!<br><br /><br><br /><strong>Tasks and Responsibilities</strong><br /><br /><ul><br />	<li>Lead, coach and mentor a team of 4-5 engineers</li><br />	<li>Help to raise the overall skill and quality level through pairing and&nbsp;design/code reviews</li><br />	<li>Support recruiting of new team members (screening candidates, conducting interviews)</li><br />	<li>Support agile development and continuous delivery in the team</li><br />	<li>Collaborate with and provide technical consultation to Product Managers, UX, other Team Leads and engineers</li><br />	<li>Foster continuous knowledge transfer in the team and across teams</li><br />	<li>Ensure code quality and maintainability by improving build and test systems</li><br />	<li>iOS native app development using Swift and Objective C</li><br />	<li>Be a role model for software engineering best practices and agile process best practices</li><br /></ul><br /><strong>Requirements</strong><br /><br /><ul><br />	<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in computer science or equivalent degree</li><br />	<li>At least 5 years relevant experience (iOS development) including</li><br />	<li>previous Team Lead experience of around 2 years</li><br />	<li>Excellent knowledge of Objective-C, Swift and XCode</li><br />	<li>Strong knowledge of design patterns and object oriented programming</li><br />	<li>Comfortable with agile methodologies, Jira, git, and code reviews</li><br />	<li>Experience consuming data from REST APIs (JSON / XML)</li><br />	<li>Experience in KIF, XCTest (Test automation in general)</li><br />	<li>Knowledge of Java is a big plus.</li><br />	<li>Real life reference or open source projects (Github / Bitbucket / Stackoverflow Account) will be beneficial.</li><br />	<li>Outstanding communication skills, ability to explain technical decisions to colleagues at all levels and from all trade</li><br /></ul><br /><strong>What we offer:</strong><br /><br /><ul><br />	<li>Attractive salary and great benefits (Employee Stock Plans, Company Pension Scheme, Commuting allowance, shuttle Bus to S-Bahn Wannsee)</li><br />	<li>Conference &amp; Education Budget</li><br />	<li>Latest Mac Book Pro, Notebook, PC you name it</li><br />	<li>Mobile phone for business and personal use</li><br />	<li>Free Snacks &amp; Drinks, subsidized Lunch in the cafeteria</li><br />	<li>Onsite Gym, Basketball &amp; Volleyball Court, Table Soccer, Ping Pong</li><br />	<li>Most importantly: Greatest people and spirit on the planet</li><br /></ul>','eBay');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('795','Sys-Admin / IT- Assistenz at eligo (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Sie haben Interesse an Softwareverteilung (wir inventarisieren mit OCS) und m&ouml;chten uns bei(m) First-Level-Support, IP-Telefonie, Monitoring, Syslogging und der Konfiguration von Firewalls unterst&uuml;tzen. Dabei ist Ihnen die Relevanz einer sorgf&auml;ltigen Dokumentation der IT-Infrastruktur (nach ISO 27001) bewusst.</p>','eligo');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('796','Ruby on Rails Developer - Possible Team Lead at ARGO Trade Solutions (Berlin, Deutschland) (allows remote)','<p><strong>Ever dreamed of disrupting&nbsp;an entire industry?</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Join ARGO and change the way companies participate in international trade!</strong></p><br /><p>Have you ever wondered how Western companies sell goods to countries such as China or Tanzania for hundred thousands of Euros without fear of never being paid? We help them do it!</p><br /><p>ARGO is building a new way to take the risk of non-payment out of international trade transactions, helping companies paying when its best for them. We make&nbsp;global transactions&nbsp;as easy as PayPal made it for consumers to buy in the dangerous world wide web.</p><br /><p>We have just started on our big vision! We are backed by one of the best European VCs, we have a great complimentary management team and are right in the middle of building our first product.</p><br /><p>But now it''s time for us to get help. We are looking for&nbsp;<strong>experienced Ruby on Rails champions</strong>&nbsp;that share our vision of creating a big disruption and want to build something exciting and fresh from the ground up!</p><br /><p>As a core member of our backend team,&nbsp;<strong>you will help to build...</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>our&nbsp;API-centric Ruby on Rails application</li><br /><li>attached services that help us create the best experience for our customers</li><br /><li>a broad&nbsp;test coverage to ensure availability</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Both in Berlin as well as in a remote position,&nbsp;<strong>we offer you...</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>a small team of super smart and driven people that believe in changing things for the better&nbsp;</li><br /><li>an informal working atmosphere based on direct communication and feedback with no bureaucracy or unnecessary disturbance: we believe in Slack, limited meetings and fast honest talk</li><br /><li>direct influence on anything you build: We know what we want to do, but if you know a better solution, we will go your way!</li><br /><li>an environment to grow: learn from your team, help others around you getting better every day, visit conferences, get and give feedback regularly and understand more than just the technical side of our business</li><br /><li>lots of additional perks such as awesome team events, regular team lunches and dinners, free of choice hardware,...</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>We hope to find in you...</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>experience in Ruby on Rails development&nbsp;proven by contribution to at least one or two projects</li><br /><li>a passionate developer that loves to code</li><br /><li>a team player that can talk code and English</li><br /><li>sufficient Ruby, Ruby on Rails and test-driven development skills&nbsp;</li><br /></ul><br /><p>&nbsp;We are super excited to hear from you!&nbsp;</p>','ARGO Trade Solutions');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('797','Softwareentwickler für verschiedene Plattformen (Linux/Unix oder z/OS) (m/w) at Beta Systems Software AG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Zur Verst&auml;rkung unseres Softwareentwicklungsteams in Berlin suchen wir ab sofort mehrere</p><br /><p><strong>Softwareentwickler f&uuml;r verschiedene Plattformen (Linux/Unix oder z/OS) (m/w)</strong></p><br /><p>Kennziffer PA 12/17</p><br /><p><strong>Aufgaben</strong></p><br /><p>Als Mitglied unseres Entwicklungsteams entwickeln und pflegen Sie z/OS-basierte sowie verteilte Unternehmensanwendungen im Bereich der Output Management Software.</p>','Beta Systems Software AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('798','Java Developer (m/f) / Backend for whistleblowing system at Business Keeper AG (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Writing great code and making a valuable contribution at the same time?<br>Then we are the right company for you.</p><br /><p>At Business Keeper AG you get the chance to do what you love &ndash; the programming &ndash; while providing a valuable contribution to society. With our electronic whistleblowing system the company has been making an important progress towards an economic culture based on values and integrity.</p><br /><p>As Java Developer (m/f) you are responsible for the continuous optimization of our Java-based web application in cooperation with our dedicated and international team.</p><br /><p>Become a part of an innovative, sustainably growing company located in the heart of Berlin. We are offering an independent working environment, diverse projects, fast decision-making processes, flexible working hours and interesting benefits.</p><br /><p><strong><br>Our Benefits</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>regular team meetings</li><br /><li>personalised training measures</li><br /><li>flexible working hours</li><br /><li>benefit packages including gym membership discount, a company pension plan or restaurant vouchers</li><br /><li>we promote team spirit with regular company-internal events</li><br /><li>Business Keeper AG is located in the centre of Berlin &ndash; right across from Berlin''s most famous shopping centre, KADEWE. This means our employees can get to work quickly and conveniently.</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong><br>Responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Continuous optimization of the Java-based web-application</li><br /><li>Transition to new technologies</li><br /><li>Function extension in existing applications</li><br /><li>Development and preparation of new applications and functions</li><br /><li>Implementation of application tests</li><br /></ul>','Business Keeper AG');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('799','Senior/Lead iOS Engineers (Berlin) at Careem (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Our iOS developers have a passion for pushing mobile technologies to the limits. As an iOS Developer, you work with our team of talented engineers to design and build the next generation mobile applications in a scalable manner. <br><br><strong>What would you do:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Design and build advanced, scalable applications for the iOS platform.</li><br /><li>Work with the product and design teams to understand end-user requirements and use cases and translate them pragmatic and effective technical solutions.</li><br /><li>Integrate with our backend services (JSON, XML, etc.) to make sure we are delivering a great mobile user experience that is super-fast for end users.</li><br /><li>Own end-to-end product modules/features from requirement to going live.</li><br /><li>Design and review code, troubleshoot and act as a consultant to team members on technical matters.</li><br /><li>Gather requirements by interacting directly with the end users and advocate delightful user experiences.</li><br /><li>Continuously discover, evaluate, and implement new technologies to maximize development efficiency.</li><br /><li>Unit-test code for robustness, including edge cases, usability, and general reliability.</li><br /><li>Use core animation to create engaging motion effects and intuitive interfaces.</li><br /></ul>','Careem');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('800','Professional Database Administrator E-Post (m/w) at Deutsche Post E-POST Development GmbH, Berlin (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong><em>Du willst besser werden, um Bester zu bleiben? Wir haben die Spielr&auml;ume f&uuml;r Vorw&auml;rtsdenker.</em></strong></p><br /><p>Die E-POST Development GmbH setzt die digitalen Produkte der Deutschen Post DHL Group in die Realit&auml;t um. Dazu wird in Berlin jeden Tag intensiv und in enger Zusammenarbeit mit dem Produktmanagement und dem UX-Team gecoded, released und gewartet. In der Friedrichshainer Oberbaum City arbeiten mutige, selbstorganisierte Teams, die neugierig auf neue Technologien sind und die an agile Entwicklungsmethoden und DevOps glauben.</p><br /><p><strong>Deine Kernaufgaben im ITO Team</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Wir bef&auml;higen unsere Entwicklungsteams schnell und unabh&auml;ngig Ihre Software live zu nehmen und das beste Produkt zu erstellen.</li><br /><li>Wir stehen f&uuml;r die Stabilit&auml;t und die Verf&uuml;gbarkeit unserer Kernplattform. Dabei gestalten wir aktiv die eingesetzten Technologien mit und bringen eigenverantwortlich unsere betriebliche Erfahrung ein.</li><br /><li>Du bist mitverantwortlich f&uuml;r die Datenbanken unserer Systeme von der Entwicklung bis in den produktiven Livebetrieb.</li><br /><li>Dein Team ist der interne Ansprechpartner rund um unsere Datenbanken und Du bist ein wichtiger Teil unseres Teams.</li><br /></ul>','Deutsche Post E-POST Development GmbH, Berlin');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('801','Ruby Developer (m/f) at crealytics GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>To strengthen our international team in Berlin, we are offering a full-time position:</p><br /><p><strong>Ruby Developer (m/f)</strong></p><br /><p>crealytics is a fast-growing technology company whose data-driven platform enables global e-commerce retailers to drive performance in product advertising and paid search. Our innovative products support our clients by automating their workflow and generating valuable intelligence.&nbsp;crealytics is generating &euro; 1.7 billion in annual client revenue for top internet retailers such as Footlocker, ASOS, and Harrods, enabled by 170 employees in our Berlin, London, Passau, and New York City offices.</p><br /><p>We are always looking for people interested in working with industry leading technologies, and are willing to play a big part in small, agile teams.</p>','crealytics GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('802','QA Engineer (f/m) - Marketplace platform at DaWanda GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>DaWanda is<strong><em> the</em></strong> leading German online marketplace for handmade and unique products. Designers and creatives offer their one of a kind and limited-edition products for sale on www.dawanda.com. Going against the grain of mass-production, DaWanda is a haven for those who value individuality and responsible consumption, as much as they like the latest trends. On the website you can find unique fashion, accessories, baby items and home decor. DaWanda is a social commerce platform, where consumers can exchange creative ideas and find inspiration from one another. Many products are created to the individual specifications of the buyer.</p><br /><p><strong><em>How we work</em></strong></p><br /><p>Our Product Engineering department is composed of passionate Software and QA Engineers, Product Managers, UX/UI Designers, Data Analysts and BI Experts structured in full stack vertical teams. We believe in the empowerment of individuals and we use Agile methodologies to let the team set quarterly objectives, in accordance with the company vision.</p><br /><p>As QA Engineers, we closely work with the Full Stack Teams in estimating, planning, and coordinating testing activities. We also ensure that quality issues and defects are appropriately identified, documented, tracked and resolved in our bug tracking tracking system. Besides, we also maintain and develop our existing automation Framework. The scale of our operations is a sweet spot between the freedom and the agility of a startup and the challenges of a big company.</p><br /><p><strong><strong><em>What we are looking for</em></strong></strong></p><br /><p>Our marketplace platform was built over the years by dozens of skilled engineers and we are looking for experienced QA Engineers (f/m) who have worked on large web platforms to keep evolving it.</p><br /><p>You will be working with one of our product teams, collaborating with Product Managers, UX/UI Designers and Software Engineers in ensuring the quality of new features on our marketplace.</p><br /><p>Do you want to help us bring the quality of our platform to the next level and also excited to learn new technologies? We are looking for passionate and skilled people to join our engineering team and are glad to have you on board as a <strong>QA Engineer (f/m)!</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Your Responsibilities:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Work in a flat hierarchy international team (our office language is English)</li><br /><li>Work closely with the Full Stack Teams in estimating, planning, and coordinating testing activities</li><br /><li>Manual testing of our mobile and web applications</li><br /><li>Create, execute and maintain test cases</li><br /><li>Identifying, reporting and tracking bugs</li><br /><li>Develop and maintain the existing automation Framework</li><br /><li>Drive process improvements that will lead to higher quality products</li><br /></ul>','DaWanda GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('803','Android Developer (m/f) at SumUp (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Your impact at SumUp</p><br /><p>You&rsquo;ll shape the core experience of merchants who are using the Android App on a daily basis.</p><br /><p>In the first few weeks, you''ll dive into the code and learn how to create clean, composable components in our codebase. You''ll use this knowledge to start developing and refining features. You''ll learn how we write tests, how we manage Bluetooth communication, and how we keep performance tip-top.</p><br /><p>In the first three months, you''ll develop major features that impact our merchant base. You''ll work closely with product and design departments to build features that are maintainable, usable, and beautiful. You''ll help us re-think problems we''ve solved before in a different way as requirements evolve.</p><br /><p>By the end of your first year, you''ll have a wealth of knowledge about our complex problem domain, as well as its implications in the interface and in the backend &ndash; and how to manage it in a clean way. You''ll have launched numerous features in the Android App as well as in the Android SDK.</p>','SumUp');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('804','Agile Software Developer - Scala (f/m) at eBay (Berlin, Germany)','<p>eBay is hiring! We are looking for a talented <strong>agile practitioner and senior Scala engineer (f/m) </strong>to join our Commerce Experience team in Berlin.<br> <br> <strong>About eBay in Europe</strong><br> eBay is the world&rsquo;s largest online marketplace, connecting people with the things they need and love virtually anytime, anywhere. eBay has 124 million active users globally and more than 500 million live individual and merchant listings at any given time, the majority of which is new and fixed-price merchandise. With mobile apps available in 190 countries, eBay delivers a personalised shopping experience and seamless access to inventory from down the street and around the world. Tailored shopping experiences, including eBay Fashion and eBay Motors, customise buying and selling; and eBay provides variety and choice for sellers by enabling them to offer goods through online, mobile and local channels to consumers globally. For more information, visit www.ebay.com.<br> <br> <strong>What is Product Development like in the eBay Commerce Experience Group?</strong><br> European Product Development (EPD) has teams in London and Berlin; we''re part of a much larger Seller Experience group globally within eBay. We enable commerce at scale, have massive customer impact. Whilst doing all this, we are on a mission to globally improve eBay technology, drive agile adoption and demonstrate customer-centric development.<br> <br> The Seller Experience group is responsible for improving the experience of our 25 million sellers worldwide. To do this, we improve existing experiences and build new products to make the life of eBay sellers better, no matter where in the world they are based.<br> <br> We are continually striving for the highest quality, and work in small focused teams following bits of Scrum, bits of Kanban, with a healthy dose of Extreme Programming (p.s these aren''t buzzwords, we mean it when we say we do this stuff).<br> <br> Our cross-functional teams have Product Management, all aspects of Product Development (including DevOps and Test), and UX all working together every day.<br> <br> Working at eBay is a rewarding, challenging and inspiring experience.<br> <br> <strong>So, what type of developer are we looking for?</strong><br> You will have an expert''s depth and breadth of experience in building high availability, scalable applications and RESTful API in Scala. You will be proficient in teaching and leading by example, and be comfortable mentoring both junior and senior engineers.<br> <br> Most of our applications are written in Java, Scala or Javascript, but as someone who is passionate about development, you&rsquo;ll be open to picking up new languages and frameworks when the situation arises.<br> <br> You care about test-driven, clean code, delightful user experiences and all the lovely stuff that''s involved with automatically tested, continuously deployed applications. You will enjoy pair programming on pretty much everything.<br> <br> You will write your own tests, whilst learning from embedded test engineers who code. You have depth of experience, but are open to being more broad too. For example, our Java developers learn from the Javascript experts, and vice versa. Having a desire to expand and master something new means you''re a good fit for us.<br> <br> We value individual contributors on the team and department level greatly, and have a fantastic culture of recognising self starters.<br> <br> Our developers decide the right tool for the job, so you should be comfortable doing this too. We have a lot fun discussing the merits of different technology and we want you to join and lead these conversations.<br> <br> Because of this culture, we value people who are open, honest and direct.<br> So you''re getting the idea of what we''re looking for; great people, with an opinion, and the ability to back it up.<br> <br> <strong>What we offer:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Dynamic, international teams with very skilled personalities, a passion for e-commerce, professionalism and a good sense of humour.</li><br /><li>The chance to work closely with other teams across eBay; in Europe, the USA and globally.</li><br /><li>A competitive salary, great benefits and an excellent working environment.</li><br /><li>Silicon Valley amenities, such as iPhones and MacBook Pros, crazy high spec dev machines and very nice office facilities.</li><br /><li>An opportunity to build applications which are used by millions of people globally.</li><br /><li>We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, colour, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.</li><br /></ul>','eBay');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('805','Softwareentwickler Backend (m/w) at CID GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Wir suchen Sie als <strong>Softwareentwickler Backend (m/w)</strong>&nbsp;zum n&auml;chstm&ouml;glichen Zeitpunkt in Festanstellung an unseren Standorten in Freigericht, Biebergem&uuml;nd, Leipzig und Berlin.</p><br /><p><strong>Ihre Aufgaben</strong></p><br /><p>Als Softwareentwickler arbeiten Sie in einem erfahrenen Team und pflegen, erweitern, optimieren und testen eine bestehende Backendsoftware sowohl in C/C++ als auch in C#. Selbst&auml;ndig analysieren Sie Anforderungen, erarbeiten L&ouml;sungskonzepte und setzen diese um. Zus&auml;tzlich unterst&uuml;tzen Sie das Team bei der Entwicklung von Tools und bei der Testautomatisierung.</p>','CID GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('806','DB-Administrator (m/w) at Verband der Ersatzkassen e. V. (vdek) (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Zur Verst&auml;rkung unseres Teams in der Abteilung <strong>Informatik </strong>suchen wir zum n&auml;chstm&ouml;glichen Zeitpunkt f&uuml;r das Referat <strong>&bdquo;Systeme / Netze / BK-Service&ldquo; </strong>einen engagierten</p><br /><br /><p><strong>DB-Administrator (m/w)</strong></p><br /><br /><p>(Einsatzort: Berlin)</p><br /><p>in Vollzeit (38,5 Std. / Woche).</p><br /><br />Ihre Aufgaben:<p><br /><br /><ul><br /><li>Betrieb, Wartung und Optimierung der bestehenden Informix- und DB2-Datenbanken</li><br /><li>Performanceanalyse und -optimierung sowie Beratung der Anwendungsentwicklung</li><br /><li>Sicherstellung von Backup und Recovery von Informix- und DB2-Datenbanken</li><br /><li>Analyse und Behebung von St&ouml;rungen</li><br /><li>Mitarbeit in Projekten und bei der Weiterentwicklung bestehender Produkte</li><br /></ul>','Verband der Ersatzkassen e. V. (vdek)');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('807','DMP Software Engineer (Java) (f/m) at mbr targeting GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>We are looking for a <strong>DMP Software Engineer (Java) (f/m).</strong></p><br /><p><strong>YOU will &hellip;</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>be a part of our experienced and inspiring development team.</li><br /><li>build solutions that work at a <strong>scale that is unique in the industry.</strong></li><br /><li>drive your software from design through implementation into operations.</li><br /><li>take responsibility for the <strong>stability and performance</strong> of our platform.</li><br /><li>work together with our Product Managers to abstract business needs into APIs.</li><br /></ul>','mbr targeting GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('808','Senior Android Developer at eHealth Systems Africa (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Please note: </strong>The position involves regular travel to Sierra Leone and potentially other West African countries, depending on project requirements.</p><br /><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><br /><p>Want to help eradicate Polio? Want to mentor, guide and work alongside developers in Africa? Want to put your knowledge and experience to work saving lives?</p><br /><p>As part of our global health informatics team, you will be developing Android applications for use by health workers in Africa. This position is based half in Berlin and half in our Freetown office, giving you the opportunity to work closely with our in-country teams, guiding and mentoring them when necessary, and contextualizing the work you&rsquo;ll be doing.</p><br /><p>In return, we offer a very competitive salary and benefits package, a lovely working atmosphere and a bright office space both in the heart of Berlin and by the beach in Freetown. For the months that you''ll be living and working in Freetown, eHealth Africa covers your air fares and related expenses. We also take care of your working visa and provide you with free serviced company housing, including wifi, air conditioning, and Atlantic sunsets.</p><br /><p><strong>Tasks and responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Defines objectives by analyzing user requirements, envisioning system features and functionality</li><br /><li>Works closely with developers and end users to ensure technical compatibility and user satisfaction</li><br /><li>Collaborates with project manager and other software developers to plan, design, develop, test, and maintain the Android application</li><br /><li>Provides thought-leadership regarding implementation best practices</li><br /><li>Assists in estimation and assessment of feasibility of features</li><br /></ul>','eHealth Systems Africa');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('809','Senior DevOps Engineer at Friendsurance (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>We are looking for an experienced&nbsp;<strong>DevOps Engineer</strong>, who is not only confident and current with their skills, but also someone who is ready, able and eager to research and evaluate emerging technologies and identify those best to adopt. <strong>This is a full time job with significant responsibility, working as part of a strong and growing team of software technologists on site in Berlin.</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Our Offer</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Implementation of a revolutionary idea</li><br /><li>Work with the cutting edge technologies</li><br /><li>Work in a highly qualified team</li><br /><li>The technical challenges of a company in strong growth</li><br /><li>Start up atmosphere, flat hierarchies and the possibility to develop further</li><br /><li>Attractive salary and perspectives</li><br /></ul>','Friendsurance');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('810','Atlassian Consultant at kreuzwerker GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Do you like challenges? At kreuzwerker, we''re not afraid to touch running systems. On the contrary.</p><br /><p>With us you will specialize in applying modern technology and frameworks to create and maintain scalable software solutions that last. For multiple Berlin-based clients from all industries.</p><br /><p>If you value collaboration and flexibility, our team of highly qualified developers, engineers, analysts, consultants and testers will gladly welcome you aboard. We will leave you with maximum degrees of freedom to create, innovate, and participate.</p><br /><p>At the moment we are actively looking for support for our team of experienced Atlassian Experts.</p><br /><p><strong>What you will do:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Support our clients in selecting and installing the right Atlassian products and integrate them with their existing infrastructure.</li><br /><li>Configure and administrate Atlassian based toolchains.</li><br /><li>Identify, recommend and implement solutions based on Atlassian tools.</li><br /><li>Train users, project managers, developers in the use of Atlassian tools.</li><br /><li>Maintain our existing managed hosting infrastructure based on Docker and AWS.</li><br /><li>Develop add-ons.</li><br /></ul>','kreuzwerker GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('811','Senior Mobile Developer (f/m) for iOS at eBay (Berlin, Germany)','eBay Kleinanzeigen is the most-visited general classifieds proposition in Germany and growing at an amazing speed. Currently, about 17 million unique customers use our native apps, mobile website and website every month.<br><br />We are managed like a start-up yet we are anchored in the global portfolio of eBay. Customer centricity and passion for our products is what helps us to develop great apps. Our agile environment, weekly usability tests, prototyping and cross-functional teams make our product better each day.<br><br /><br><br />To make our team even more powerful we are hiring a Senior Mobile Developer (f/m) for iOS.<br><br /><br><br />As part of our mobile team you will be building and managing our app for iOS and power our amazing growth.<br><br /><br><br />If you are a believer in customer centric thinking, agile and lean software development, feel responsible for your product, enjoy working in cross functional teams, want to craft quality and not quantity and most importantly want to make an impact then get in touch with us!<br><br /><br><br />Tasks and Responsibilities<br><br />Help architect, build, iterate and manage our mobile application<br><br />Ensure that code is compliant with latest design standards and best-practices<br><br />Help to raise the overall skill and quality level through pairing, design/code reviews, and mentoring<br><br />Push forward our test-driven development process including unit, integration- and functional testing<br><br />Partner closely with product management to continuously improve our app<br><br />Research and prototype solutions to difficult problems<br><br /><br><br />Requirements<br><br />Enthusiasm for iOS development, beautiful, pragmatic code and an eye for simplicity<br><br />Excellent understanding and strong experience with the iOS SDK (CoreData, UIKit)<br><br />Know how to use Instruments (Leaks, Object Allocations, etc)<br><br />Excellent programming skills in Objective-C<br><br />Programming skills in Swift<br><br />Strong know-how in object-oriented software design and design patterns<br><br />Experience with client/server architectures using HTTP, REST, XML, JSON and SQL<br><br />Effective oral and written English communication skills<br><br /><br><br />Nice to Have<br><br />Experience in creating test driven mobile environments, e.g. experience in KIF, XCTest<br><br />Real life reference or open source projects (Github / Bitbucket / Stackoverflow Account)<br><br /><br><br />Benefits &amp; Perks<br><br />Attractive salary and great benefits (Employee Stock Plans, Company Pension Scheme, Commuting allowance, shuttle Bus to S-Bahn Wannsee)<br><br />Conference &amp; Education Budget<br><br />Latest Mac Book Pro, Notebook, PC you name it<br><br />Mobile phone for business and personal use<br><br />Free Snacks &amp; Drinks, subsidized Lunch in the cafeteria<br><br />Onsite Gym, Basketball &amp; Volleyball Court, Table Soccer, Ping Pong<br><br />Most importantly: Greatest people and spirit on the planet','eBay');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('812','Softwarearchitekt (m/w) at CID GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Wir suchen Sie als <strong>Softwarearchitekt (m/w)</strong> zum n&auml;chstm&ouml;glichen Zeitpunkt in Festanstellung an unseren&nbsp;Standorten in Freigericht, Biebergem&uuml;nd, Leipzig, Kaunas und Berlin.</p><br /><p><strong>Ihre Aufgaben</strong></p><br /><p>Sie erstellen Architekturmodelle unter Anwendung bestehender Methodik &ndash; Leitf&auml;den. Zu Ihren Aufgaben z&auml;hlen die Durchf&uuml;hrung von Anforderungsanalysen und das Erstellen von Softwarespezifikationen. Sie definieren und erstellen Architekturanforderungen/-modelle. Das Design, die Implementierung, die Integration und Verifikation von Software-Modulen gem&auml;&szlig; SW-Entwicklungsprozess sowie die &Uuml;berwachung von Entwicklungsprozessen sind ebenso Teil Ihrer Aufgaben, wie die Erarbeitung und Bewertung von Software-Sicherheitskonzepten. Als Softwarearchitekt sind Sie verantwortlich f&uuml;r die Testkonzeption und das Testmanagement. Sie sind erfahren, zielgenaue, methodisch fundierte Aufwandssch&auml;tzungen f&uuml;r IT-Vorhaben abzugeben. Sie moderieren Workshops mit Kunden und pr&auml;sentieren Entwicklungsst&auml;nde gegen&uuml;ber internen und externen Kunden. Dabei arbeiten Sie eigenverantwortlich und zielorientiert, gestalten in und mit Teams. Sie leiten Projekte oder Teilprojekte unterschiedlicher Gr&ouml;&szlig;e und Komplexit&auml;t. Sie erkennen Projektziele und setzen diese um.</p>','CID GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('813','Senior Programmatic Consultant (m/w) at eBay (Kleinmachnow, Germany)','mobile.de ist der meistbesuchte Fahrzeugmarkt f&uuml;r den An- und Verkauf von Fahrzeugen in Deutschland. Das Angebot richtet sich sowohl an Fahrzeugh&auml;ndler als auch an Privatkunden. Zus&auml;tzliche Dienstleistungen wie Tipps und Hinweise rund um den Autokauf, die Vermittlung von Finanzierungen oder Versicherungen und Online-Werbung runden das Angebot von mobile.de ab. Die mobile.de GmbH betreibt dar&uuml;ber hinaus Fahrzeugm&auml;rkte in Italien, Frankreich, Rum&auml;nien, Niederlande und Polen.<br><br /><br><br />Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung unseres Teams in Dreilinden bei Berlin suchen wir Sie als <strong>(Senior) Programmatic Consultant (m/w).</strong><br><br /><br><br /><strong>Ihre Aufgaben:</strong><br><br /><br><br />Der Programmatic Consultant ist f&uuml;r die Betreuung und Beratung unserer programmatischen Kunden und Kampagnen auf mobile.de und motor-talk.de zust&auml;ndig. Mithilfe unserer technologischen Infrastruktur erm&ouml;glicht der Programmatic Consultant unseren Kunden einen Einkauf auf das Werbeinventar.<br><br />Er/Sie ist f&uuml;r die Kommunikation und Koordinierung von Kunden, Trading Desks und Vermarktungspartner verantwortlich. Dazu geh&ouml;ren alle T&auml;tigkeiten von der Kundenansprache bis hin zur Umsetzung und Auslieferung der Werbekampagnen. Dar&uuml;ber hinaus ist der Programmatic Consultant die interne Schnittstelle zu unserem Agency Sales Team und nimmt in dieser Rolle eine wichtige Beratungsfunktion wahr.<br /><ul><br />	<li>Ausbau der programmatischen Vermarktungsaktivit&auml;ten</li><br />	<li>Beratung des Agency Sales Teams bei allen programmatischen Themen</li><br />	<li>Vertiefung der Gesch&auml;ftsbeziehungen zur Demand Side (Trading Desk)</li><br />	<li>Identifizierung und Akquise von relevanten Demand-Quellen</li><br />	<li>Analyse und Weiterentwicklung strategischer Kooperationen im programmatischen Bereich</li><br />	<li>Entwicklung neuer Vermarktungsprodukte in Zusammenarbeit mit den Teilbereichen</li><br />	<li>Gelegentliche Reiset&auml;tigkeit im Rahmen der Kundenbetreuung</li><br /></ul><br /><br><br /><strong>Ihr Profil:</strong><br /><br /><ul><br />	<li>Mehrj&auml;hrige Berufserfahrung im Online Advertising/Marketing (Vermarkter, Agentur, Network)</li><br />	<li>Erfahrungen mit programmatischen Systemen von Vorteil (SSP, DSP, DMP, Ad Exchange)</li><br />	<li>F&auml;higkeit komplexe technische Sachverhalte zu erfassen/hohe Auffassungsgabe</li><br />	<li>Sehr guter Kommunikationsstil sowie strukturierte und l&ouml;sungsorientierte Arbeitsweise</li><br />	<li>Ausgepr&auml;gte Service- und Kundenorientierung, Teamspirit und Freude an neuen Themen</li><br />	<li>Verhandlungs- und Pr&auml;sentationssicher</li><br />	<li>Sprachen: Deutsch, mind. gutes Englisch</li><br /></ul><br /><br><br /><strong>Was bieten wir Ihnen?</strong><br /><br /><ul><br />	<li>Einen umfassenden Verantwortungsbereich mit viel Gestaltungsspielraum</li><br />	<li>Ein erstklassiges Produkt, das zu den f&uuml;hrenden Internet-Marktpl&auml;tzen geh&ouml;rt</li><br />	<li>Dynamisches Team mit Raum f&uuml;r Individualit&auml;t, Professionalit&auml;t und viel Humor</li><br />	<li>Ein attraktives Verg&uuml;tungsmodell sowie umfangreiche betriebliche Sozialleistungen</li><br /></ul>','eBay');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('814','App Entwickler (Multiplattform) at Kinematics GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>Wir sind ein vielfach ausgezeichnetes Start-up mit Sitz in Berlin. Mit unserem jungen, humorvollen Team entwickeln, produzieren und vermarkten wir voller Begeisterung ein einzigartiges Robotik-Baukastensystem.</p><br /><p><strong>www.tinkerbots.com</strong></p><br /><p>Ab sofort suchen wir nach einem begeisterungsf&auml;higen Softwareentwickler(in) mit Schwerpunkt App-Entwicklung (Multiplattform), die/der unser Team bei der Weiterentwicklung unseres Produktes unterst&uuml;tzt.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><br /><p><strong>Deine Aufgaben:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Unterst&uuml;tzung des App-Teams sowie eigenverantwortliche Umsetzung von Apps zur Fernsteuerung &amp; Programmierung unserer Robotik-Module</li><br /><li>Test und Dokumentation der entwickelten Applikationen</li><br /><li>Breites Aufgabenspektrum innerhalb hoch innovativer und spannender Themen&nbsp;rund um das Thema Robotik</li><br /></ul><br /><p>Wir bieten Dir eine spannende Position in einem jungen Hardware-Unternehmen verbunden mit der M&ouml;glichkeit auf eigenverantwortliche und gestaltende Mitarbeit in einem tollen Team. Abwechslungsreiche Aufgaben, flache Hierarchien, eine offene Kommunikation sowie viel Freiraum zur Entfaltung warten auf Dich. Wir bieten zudem eine attraktive Verg&uuml;tung inkl. Boni und langfristige Perspektiven.</p><br /><p>Haben wir Dein Interesse geweckt? Dann schreibe uns eine Mail (bitte mit kurzem Lebenslauf und wenn m&ouml;glich mit einer kleinen Referenzliste deiner Projekte) an jobs@tinkerbots.com</p>','Kinematics GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('815','Mobile Testing Expert at immmr GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Write, test and maintain code for our test automation (cross platform &ndash; web, iOS, Android)</li><br /><li>Create automated test cases for all apps based on user facing features with the goal of increasing our test coverage</li><br /><li>Testing (manual and automated) across different stages of development (dev, integration, QA)</li><br /></ul>','immmr GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('816','Software Engineer (m/f) SAP Hybris at Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Software Engineer (m/f) SAP Hybris</strong><br><strong>Location: Berlin</strong></p><br /><p>You may think of publishing as somewhat traditional. At Springer Nature we have ambitious plans and our IT group is what will drive our ambitions. We need talented people in every discipline, from Business Analysts and UX Designers to Software Developers and Platform Engineers to name just a few.</p><br /><p><strong>Exciting IT challenges at an academic publisher?</strong><br><strong>Where else but here: at Springer Nature!</strong></p><br /><p>In the context of our digital strategies, in Berlin we develop new software and optimise our global platforms (e. g. springernature.com, nature.com, springermedizin.de, palgrave.com). Together with colleagues in London, Pune and New York we work to ensure that our customers enjoy access to individual content &ndash; every day and from anywhere in the world. Our working philosophy is agile and highly motivated &ndash; with the atmosphere and culture of a start-up, embedded in a vital and dynamic publishing group.</p><br /><p><strong>The two sides of your job: between daily thrills and a healthy work-life balance</strong></p><br /><p>You&rsquo;ll contribute to challenging but successful projects, while keeping the needs and interests of the user at the heart of your considerations. You&rsquo;ll use cutting-edge technology to create applications that simply blow our customers away. And nevertheless, at the end of the day you&rsquo;ll be home in time for dinner!</p><br /><p><strong>These three Key Practices shape our actions:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Agile promise: We roll out high-quality services in brief intervals and constantly work to improve our processes and ourselves</li><br /><li>Collective code ownership: Every team member is welcome to and expected to participate &ndash; and that includes decision-making processes</li><br /><li>For us, DevOps isn&rsquo;t just a buzzword: We actively practice shared responsibility for every link of the tool chain for infrastructure, software quality, delivery and operations. Each of our passionate developers has the opportunity to familiarise themselves with and improve every aspect of our system</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>You could play the lead role in our team and...</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>assume responsibility for the entire lifecycle of the web applications you create</li><br /><li>make the active, ongoing further development of our platforms one of your priorities</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Speaking of technologies &ndash; are you familiar with the following?</strong><br><strong>If you aren&rsquo;t now, you can still get to know:</strong></p><br /><p>Cloud Foundry, OpenStack, Chef, Play, Ansible, Spring Boot, Rabbit MQ, Elastic Search, Solr Cloud, Mongo DB, Python, Ruby, Java, Scala</p><br /><p><strong>So what do we offer?</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>A healthy work/life balance</li><br /><li>Interesting and challenging work</li><br /><li>A relaxed, positive environment</li><br /><li>Enthusiastic, supportive colleagues</li><br /><li>Further development to help you progress your career</li><br /><li>Flexible hours, a 37 hour week and 30 days annual leave</li><br /><li>Book discount of 15-40 %</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Success in three simple steps:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>If your CV looks promising, we&rsquo;ll contact you for a short telephone call &ndash; that will give you a chance to learn more about who we are, and we&rsquo;ll get an impression of your motivation</li><br /><li>We&rsquo;ll then send you a test that you can complete in your own time</li><br /><li>Lastly, there will be an in-person interview on site &ndash; where you&rsquo;ll get to know your future colleagues, the working atmosphere and Springer Nature&rsquo;s projects</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Terms:</strong><br>Permanent contract<br>Working hours: full-time<br>Company and location: Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH, Berlin</p><br /><p>Excited by the prospect of joining us? We are looking forward to your&nbsp;<a href="https://career5.successfactors.eu/career?career_ns=job_listing&amp;company=C0001215517P&amp;career_job_req_id=18661" rel="nofollow">online application</a> in English!</p><br /><p>To find out more information about our organization please take a look at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.springer.com" rel="nofollow">www.springer.com</a> and <a href="http://www.springernature.com" rel="nofollow">www.springernature.com</a>.</p>','Springer Science + Business Media Deutschland GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('817','Senior Site Reliability Engineer - Java/ Scala at Zalando SE (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>THE OPPORTUNITY</strong></p><br /><p>SRE/ Production Engineering is a new approach to scaling up highly available systems, originally introduced by Google and embraced by many successful players running Internet scale systems, like Zalando. PE encompasses several practices aimed at creating and operating scalable, reliable, and efficient architectures, including the definition and measurement of Service Level Indicators and Objectives, assessing and managing risk, forecasting demand and planning compute capacity, etc. If you have not heard about this before, you should definitely look into it, regardless of whether you apply to this position or not.</p><br /><p>Within Zalando Payments, you will work with many ambitious and skilled autonomous teams building and operating our microservices-based platform. We are embedded into the larger context of Zalando Tech and live up to the spirit of what we call Radical Agility &mdash; our culture that focuses on autonomy, mastery, and purpose (again, look it up!).</p><br /><p>At Zalando Payments, we are processing all financial transactions of Zalando&rsquo;s fashion store and other consumer facing apps. Starting with a flawless user experience in the checkout over the processing of the payments to reconciliation in the backend, we cover the entire financial process to boost conversion and deliver a competitive advantage to our customers through smart risk steering.</p>','Zalando SE');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('818','Frontend Web Developer (m/f) at Mimi Hearing Technologies GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>We are looking for a <strong>Frontend Web Develope</strong>r as full-time position in our office in Berlin.</p><br /><br /><p><strong>// This is your workplace:</strong></p><br /><p><span>Mimi Hearing Technologies, founded in 2014 in Berlin, is one of the most promising startups in the</span> <span>mHealth / sound space. We develop tools for people to explore their hearing health and enjoy a unique listening experience - </span><strong>we strive to be the forefront of sound innovation.</strong></p><br /><p><span>Our skills are deeply rooted in </span><strong>science, psychoacoustics and engineering</strong><span>. The Mimi team is a diverse group of innovators with strong expertise in audio- and sound engineering, product, communication and business design. </span></p><br /><ul><br /><li><em><span>Mimi Hearing Test</span></em><span> is the number one hearing test app in the AppStore with </span><strong>over one million tested ears</strong><span> worldwide</span></li><br /><li><em><span>Mimi Music</span></em><span> is revolutionizing the way, how people listen to Music and the </span><span>upcoming Mimi SDK will enable even more use cases for our technology</span></li><br /><li><span>Total number of app downloads: 650K</span></li><br /><li><strong>Two patents filed</strong><span> + two patents in the pipeline</span></li><br /><li><span>Close cooperation with Charit&eacute; Berlin and medical certification of our products</span></li><br /></ul><br /><p><span>Our vision is to set a new standard for the way we listen and become the </span><strong>#1 technology for personalized sound </strong><span>and hearing health.</span></p><br /><br /><p><strong>// Who are we looking for? </strong></p><br /><p>We are committed to create a culture which nourishes personal growth as the base for company growth. We are a learning organisation which means, we love to work with people who start doing things, fail and learn fast in order to keep moving instead of waiting and drafting the perfect solutions.</p><br /><br /><p><strong>As our Frontend Web Developer&nbsp;you will:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li><span>Build responsive web applications with a clear focus on frontend development</span></li><br /><li><span>Work closely with our backend developers to create new user facing products as well as internal company tools</span></li><br /><li><span>Collaborate with our cross-functional team to define, design, and ship new product features</span></li><br /><li><span>Continuously discover, evaluate, and implement new technologies</span></li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>You must have</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li><span>5+ years of working experience in frontend web development</span></li><br /><li><span>Strong knowledge of HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript (including the latest features in ES6)</span></li><br /><li><span>Production experience with modern JS frameworks, specifically React/Redux or Angular </span></li><br /><li><span>Highly motivated in learning, excellent communication and execution skills, and an open mindset</span></li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>It would be great if you have</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li><span>A BS/MS degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related study is a plus</span></li><br /><li><span>Solid knowledge of software design patterns and system architecture</span></li><br /><li><span>Experience with third-party libraries and APIs</span></li><br /><li><span>Experience with REST-API''s</span></li><br /><li><span>Fluent in English, as the company language is English</span></li><br /><li><span>Continuous integration and backend technologies</span></li><br /></ul><br /><br /><p><strong>Sounds like you? </strong><br>Please send an email with your CV and motivational letter <span>(both as PDFs)</span>&nbsp;to jobs@mimi.io</p>','Mimi Hearing Technologies GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('819','(Senior) C/C++ Developer (m/f) at Lautsprecher Teufel GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','Our success story is continuing &ndash; be a part of it! We&rsquo;re currently looking for a highly committed and experienced&nbsp;<span><strong>(Senior) C/C++ Developer (m/f)</strong></span><br /><br /><p><strong>Your tasks:</strong></p><br />As (Senior) C/C++ Developer (m/f) you are responsible for conceptualizing and enhancing new and innovative features for our series of audio streaming products. Based on your expertise and know-how gained in related companies/industries you develop firmware for efficient active speakers and thereby ensure the availability of high-quality streaming solutions at any given time. This involves, in particular, the development of user space software on an upstream Linux kernel. In addition, you have the opportunity to contribute to long-term open-source projects.','Lautsprecher Teufel GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('820','Lead Backend Software Developer at 99chairs GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland) (allows remote)','<p>Do you love coding? Are you looking for the next step in your career? Then join us. <br>We believe in creating the perfect places to enjoy unique moments in life. Everything we do is user friendly and beautifully designed. <br><br>We are a highly motivated and dynamic team of young professionals, hungry for new ideas and striving for the great impact we&rsquo;ll have on everyone&rsquo;s life. Our spirit is to have fun while working together &ndash; our daily routine is not simply to go to work, but to push great ideas together as a group of friends. Being a team is a main core value in our company culture as well as improving constantly through the big number of responsibilities each and everyone of us has. At heart, we are a tech company and simply love what we do. <br><br>Our mission is to transform our customer&rsquo;s homes into places they love. Professional interior designers create individually adjusted design concepts across a portfolio of leading furniture brands. Then our customers conveniently order the items they like online at the regular price which will then be delivered to their homes by our merchants.<br> Receiving a professional interior design service does not cost a fortune anymore &ndash; we make it happen: Together we innovate the industry. Together we shape the future of everyone&rsquo;s lifestyle.</p>','99chairs GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('821','Make growth easy with marketing automation (iOS) at Upsales GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Why should you join our team?</strong></p><br /><p>Upsales is a team of young, talented, and highly driven people striving to always deliver high quality in everything they do in order to reach Upsales&rsquo; ambitious goals. From day one you will have a big responsibility and the opportunity to really make an impact. All your initiatives will rapidly be visible and are highly appreciated. At Upsales you will continuously develop and become better by working with talented and driven colleagues and also through our regular off-site competence development events. Despite the high tempo and endless possibilities of developing both your personal and professional self, we don&rsquo;t forget to have fun. Twice a year we travel to exiting places on kick-off and team building events to enhance company collaboration, develop our selves, and build strong ties together, but most important we have a lot of fun! We also offer a generous benefit package of gym reimbursement, robust vacation policy, lunch coupons, and much more!</p><br /><p><strong>The role of iOS developer at Upsales</strong></p><br /><p>This position offers a broad spectrum of challenging task and problem solving using the newest technologies to cope with the rapidly changing market demands and the increasingly digitized world. As an iOS engineer at Upsales you will have the opportunity to develop the full scope of the application and we encourage you to come up with ideas of how we can improve Upsales in order to become the best Marketing software on the planet. Some of the daily work tasks involve: implementation of new features, creating awesome user interfaces, and improving the applications performance.<strong><br> </strong></p>','Upsales GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('822','Software Developer (f/m)  Energy at Bosch Software Innovations GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Wir bieten Themen, die voller Zukunft stecken. Spannende Softwareprojekte. Und ein Team, das gemeinsam etwas bewegen will. Wir suchen kluge K&ouml;pfe voller Engagement und Begeisterung!</strong></p><br /><p>Wir bei Bosch Software Innovations, dem Software- und Systemhaus der Bosch-Gruppe, konzipieren, entwickeln und betreiben weltweit innovative Software- und Systeml&ouml;sungen. So bringen wir unsere Kunden voran &ndash; sowohl im Internet of Things als auch im klassischen Enterprise-Umfeld.</p><br /><p>Wir suchen zum n&auml;chstm&ouml;glichen Zeitpunkt einen Software Developer (f/m) f&uuml;r den Bereich Energy f&uuml;r unseren Standort in Berlin.</p><br /><p><strong>Ihr Beitrag zu Gro&szlig;em:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Als Mitglied unseres Entwicklungsteams gestalten Sie unter Einsatz agiler Entwicklungsmethoden innovative Produkte f&uuml;r den Energiebereich mit</li><br /><li>Sie analysieren Anforderungen, Sie entwerfen und implementieren L&ouml;sungen im Team und testen und dokumentieren diese selbstst&auml;ndig. Die Integration und Anpassung bestehender Software-Komponenten geh&ouml;rt ebenfalls zu Ihrem Aufgabengebiet</li><br /><li>Sie tragen durch Ihre Professionalit&auml;t ma&szlig;geblich zur hohen Produktreife unserer Software-Systeme bei, zu deren Sicherstellung auch die Durchf&uuml;hrung von Regressionstests sowie das Entwickeln und Ausf&uuml;hren automatisierter Komponenten- und Systemtests geh&ouml;rt</li><br /><li>Sie leisten professionelle Unterst&uuml;tzung f&uuml;r unsere Teamleiter und Product Owner in technischen Fragen und sind akzeptierter Ansprechpartner f&uuml;r unser Produkt- und L&ouml;sungsportfolio</li><br /><li>Sie bringen sich aktiv in Architektur- und Designdiskussionen ein</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Was Sie daf&uuml;r auszeichnet:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>Sie haben Ihr Hochschulstudium im Bereich Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Mathematik oder Physik erfolgreich abgeschlossen oder verf&uuml;gen &uuml;ber eine vergleichbare Ausbildung</li><br /><li>Sie verf&uuml;gen &uuml;ber mindestens 2 Jahre Berufserfahrung in der Softwareentwicklung und haben Kenntnisse in der Anwendung aktueller Java Frameworks und Web-Technologien (z.B. Java, BPM, JEE, Spring, REST, XML, JSON, XSLT, SQL etc.)</li><br /><li>Sie bringen ein hohes Qualit&auml;tsbewusstsein und praktische Erfahrung im Einsatz von Qualit&auml;tssicherungsma&szlig;nahmen mit (z.B. Unit- und Integrationstests, statische Codeanalyse, Code Reviews)</li><br /><li>Sie sind ein Teamplayer, motiviert neue Technologien zu erlernen und verf&uuml;gen &uuml;ber gute analytische und konzeptionelle F&auml;higkeiten</li><br /><li>Sie haben eine schnelle Auffassungsgabe und kommunizieren sicher in Deutsch und Englisch</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Haben wir Ihr Interesse geweckt? - Dann starten Sie mit uns durch - denn jeder Erfolg hat seinen Anfang.</strong></p><br /><p>Nutzen Sie unser Online-Bewerbungsformular und Ihre Daten kommen schnell und sicher bei uns an.</p><br /><p><strong>Kontakt Human Resources: </strong>Ulrike Smolny, Tel.: Ulrike Smolny, Tel. +49 30 726 112 177</p>','Bosch Software Innovations GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('823','Senior iOS developer (m/f) // Berlin startup // Travel technology at conichi (Berlin, Germany)','<p>Our vision is to give hotel guests the personalized experience they truly deserve. Through&nbsp;cutting-edge beacon technology, conichi empowers hoteliers all&nbsp;over the world to recognise&nbsp;their guests hereby granting them personalized and memorable&nbsp;experiences. We provide every&nbsp;hotel with their own hotel app, able to communicate any relevant information to the guests&nbsp;they would like to share as much as mobile check-on and check-out. Each hotel is ready for&nbsp;the modern traveller through conichi. conichi is proud to have received awards from&nbsp;Initiative Mittelstand, Beacon Summit, Web Summit, VIR and TIC.</p><br /><p>We are looking for an iOS developer to support us at conichi.&nbsp;</p><br /><p>Applicants should ideally already possess a work permit for Germany.</p><br /><p><strong>What you will be doing:</strong></p><br /><p>- Designing and building applications for our iOS platform</p><br /><p>- Ensuring the performance, quality, and responsiveness of apps</p><br /><p>- Collaborating with a team to define and design new features</p><br /><p>- Identifying and correcting bottlenecks and fixing bugs</p><br /><p>- Helping to maintain code quality, organization and automatisation</p><br /><p><strong>What we can offer:</strong></p><br /><p>- An international team that passionately believes in what it does, always ready to go&nbsp;the extra mile for each other</p><br /><p>- Responsibility and space to make your own decisions</p><br /><p>- A highly innovative and interesting product</p><br /><p>- An attractive salary package</p><br /><p>- An opportunity to be part of a growing company, directly influencing its success</p><br /><p>- A stunning office in the tech-hub of Europe &amp; the trendiest part of Berlin</p><br /><p>- Free drinks, fruits and snacks</p><br /><p>- Awesome team building activities such as monthly breakfasts&nbsp;and stylish dinners</p><br /><p>- An open door policy environment and full transparency</p>','conichi');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('824','Senior Software Developer (f/m) - IoT Open Source Projects at Bosch Software Innovations GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p><strong>Take on topics that are the future. Be part of fascinating software projects and join a team that is out to move mountains. We&rsquo;re looking for bright sparks with plenty of passion and commitment.</strong></p><br /><p>We offer the topics of tomorrow. Exciting software projects. And a team that wants to work together to make a difference. We are looking for bright minds full of commitment and enthusiasm!</p><br /><p>Bosch Software Innovations, the Bosch Group''s software and system house, is a leading global technology and services provider. We design, develop, and operate innovative software and system solutions that help our customers all around the world &ndash; both in the traditional enterprise environment and in the Internet of Things (IoT).</p><br /><p>We are looking for a Senior Software Developer (f/m) for IoT Open Source projects for our location in Berlin, Immenstaad, or Waiblingen.</p><br /><p><strong>Tasks</strong><strong>:</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You participate in open source projects in the Eclipse, Apache and Cloud Foundry Foundation as a contributor, committer and development project lead</li><br /><li>You present these projects at international conferences and promote the use of the resulting software within the Bosch Group and with international partners</li><br /><li>As an experienced Senior Software Developer, you participate in architecture and design discussions in the community, perform code reviews of external contributions and support new project members as a mentor</li><br /><li>You support our service and solution developers in the selection of open source technologies and their integration and active participation in the relevant open source projects</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><br /><ul><br /><li>You have a degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or equivalent</li><br /><li>You have at least 5 years of experience in software development. In addition to in-depth knowledge of the Java programming language and the application of current Java frameworks and Web technologies (for example, REST, JavaScript), the knowledge of other programming languages (for example, C / C ++ and scripting languages) and programming concepts would be a plus</li><br /><li>You have already gained extensive knowledge in open source projects and ideally you have already successfully participated in the development of open source projects in the area of IoT or have conducted corresponding projects</li><br /><li>Excellent communication skills (both writing and speaking) in English and German</li><br /></ul><br /><p><strong>Are you interested in?</strong> Please use our online contact form to submit your application.</p><br /><p><strong>Contact human resources:</strong> Ulrike Smolny, Tel.: +49 30 726112 177</p>','Bosch Software Innovations GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('825','Android Entwickler Thalia Apps (m/w) - Java, Android SDK at Thalia Bücher GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>Welche Aufgaben erwarten Dich:</strong></p><br /><p><strong>Entwicklung von nativen Android-Apps</strong> f&uuml;r Endkunden und Buchh&auml;ndler <br> &nbsp; <br> Weiterentwicklung der <strong>Architektur </strong>und Gew&auml;hrleistung der <strong>App-Qualit&auml;t</strong> <br> &nbsp; <br> Integration von <strong>Webtechnologien </strong>wie HTML(5), CSS(3), JavaScript und HTTP-REST in die Anwendungen <br> <br> <strong>Enge Zusammenarbeit im multidisziplin&auml;ren SCRUM-Team </strong>mit UX-Kollegen, Product Owner, Design, Entwicklung und QA <br> &nbsp; <br> Mitarbeit an der Konzeption von <strong>Cross-Channel-Schnittstellen </strong>und <strong>-Prozessen</strong> <br> &nbsp; <br> Fachliche <strong>Weiterentwicklung </strong>des Teams sowie Evaluierung und <strong>Einf&uuml;hrung neuer Technologien</strong></p>','Thalia Bücher GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('826','Tired of solving boring C++ problems? at think-cell Software GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p><strong>At think-cell expect a&nbsp;wide array of extremely challenging C++ development tasks.</strong></p><br /><p>think-cell is&nbsp;looking for smart, creative C++ developers with a solid theoretical background. You should be able to look at a problem from the user''s perspective, discuss abstract concepts with fellow developers, as well as produce an elegant implementation. Developers we have hired in the past mostly hold an exceptional master''s degree in computer science or even a doctorate.</p><br /><p>We pay very competitive salaries, and offer our developers <strong>EUR 120,000 annually</strong> following one year of employment. If necessary, we will go out of our way to help you relocate to Berlin, and will do what we can to help you acquire a work permit.</p><br /><p>At think-cell, we like flat hierarchies. You will work largely independently and will be responsible for the whole range of activities when implementing a new feature. We expect each of our developers to do architecture, design, implementation, customer feedback and bug fixing,&nbsp; rather than splitting these activities between several people. We thus minimize communication losses and put everyone in control of their own work. Your ideas are welcome, even if they mean that we have to change a lot of code to make things better.</p><br /><p>We have published several scientific articles in the areas of Artificial Intelligence and Computer Graphics and we will encourage you to do the same. We sponsor visits to conferences and have close connections to universities and research institutes in the U.S. and Germany.</p><br /><p>think-cell encourages a healthy work-life balance. We do not work at night or on weekends, and support our staff''s families with a full-time company nanny. She is available for free when children are sick, or if you just feel like spending an evening out.</p>','think-cell Software GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('827','Senior QA Analyst (m/f) for an e-commerce revolution at Spryker Systems GmbH (Berlin, Deutschland)','<p>We are looking for an experienced QA Analyst who wants to take responsibility in a powerful startup environment!</p><br /><p>With Spryker we launched a new commerce framework based on Silex and Symfony2 bundles. The approach is to provide a modern architecture which ships with a set of reference implementations for the most common use cases. Every single feature can be extended or, if needed, replaced by a more specific solution. Instead of bulky generic code, Spryker provides a lean architecture and clean code.</p>','Spryker Systems GmbH');
INSERT INTO `Stackoverflow_jobs_12_june` VALUES ('828','iOS Developer at DOJO Madness at Dojo Madness GmbH (Berlin, Germany)','<p>A candidate is expected to have experience in building native &amp; hybrid apps for iOS and should be able to present examples of his/her work. <br>You will help to create and expand our upcoming iOS App and new Dojo Madness sub-products. Our ideal candidate has an excellent eye for detail, pragmatic approach and an absolute commitment to making sure features are well implemented and bug free. We make all of our decisions based on experiments and testing, so you should be excited by taking a detailed approach to development. If you are also a passionate advocate for the user and are looking to work in an agile, collaborative environment, then we would love hearing from you!</p>','Dojo Madness GmbH');
